2402
2403int igb_init_vmdq_netdevs(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
2404{
2405 int pool, err = 0, base_queue;
2406 struct net_device *vnetdev;
2407 struct igb_vmdq_adapter *vmdq_adapter;
2408
2409 for (pool = 1; pool < adapter->vmdq_pools; pool++) {
2410 int qpp = (!adapter->rss_queues ? 1 : adapter->rss_queues);
2411 base_queue = pool * qpp;
2412 vnetdev = alloc_etherdev(sizeof(struct igb_vmdq_adapter));
2413 if (!vnetdev) {
2414 err = -ENOMEM;
2415 break;
2416 }
2417 vmdq_adapter = netdev_priv(vnetdev);
2418 vmdq_adapter->vnetdev = vnetdev;
2419 vmdq_adapter->real_adapter = adapter;
2420 vmdq_adapter->rx_ring = adapter->rx_ring[base_queue];
2421 vmdq_adapter->tx_ring = adapter->tx_ring[base_queue];
2422 igb_assign_vmdq_netdev_ops(vnetdev);
2423 snprintf(vnetdev->name, IFNAMSIZ, "%sv%d",
2424 adapter->netdev->name, pool);
2425 vnetdev->features = adapter->netdev->features;
2426#ifdef HAVE_NETDEV_VLAN_FEATURES
2427 vnetdev->vlan_features = adapter->netdev->vlan_features;
2428#endif
2429 adapter->vmdq_netdev[pool-1] = vnetdev;
2430 err = register_netdev(vnetdev);
2431 if (err)
2432 break;
2433 }
2434 return err;
2435}
2436
2437int igb_remove_vmdq_netdevs(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
2438{
2439 int pool, err = 0;
2440
2441 for (pool = 1; pool < adapter->vmdq_pools; pool++) {
2442 unregister_netdev(adapter->vmdq_netdev[pool-1]);
2443 free_netdev(adapter->vmdq_netdev[pool-1]);
2444 adapter->vmdq_netdev[pool-1] = NULL;
2445 }
2446 return err;
2447}
2448#endif /* CONFIG_IGB_VMDQ_NETDEV */
2449
2450/**
2451 * igb_set_fw_version - Configure version string for ethtool
2452 * @adapter: adapter struct
2453 *
2454 **/
2455static void igb_set_fw_version(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
2456{
2457 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
2458 struct e1000_fw_version fw;
2459
2460 e1000_get_fw_version(hw, &fw);
2461
2462 switch (hw->mac.type) {
2463 case e1000_i210:
2464 case e1000_i211:
2465 if (!(e1000_get_flash_presence_i210(hw))) {
2466 snprintf(adapter->fw_version,
2467 sizeof(adapter->fw_version),
2468 "%2d.%2d-%d",
2469 fw.invm_major, fw.invm_minor, fw.invm_img_type);
2470 break;
2471 }
2472 /* fall through */
2473 default:
2474 /* if option rom is valid, display its version too*/
2475 if (fw.or_valid) {
2476 snprintf(adapter->fw_version,
2477 sizeof(adapter->fw_version),
2478 "%d.%d, 0x%08x, %d.%d.%d",
2479 fw.eep_major, fw.eep_minor, fw.etrack_id,
2480 fw.or_major, fw.or_build, fw.or_patch);
2481 /* no option rom */
2482 } else {
2483 if (fw.etrack_id != 0X0000) {
2484 snprintf(adapter->fw_version,
2485 sizeof(adapter->fw_version),
2486 "%d.%d, 0x%08x",
2487 fw.eep_major, fw.eep_minor, fw.etrack_id);
2488 } else {
2489 snprintf(adapter->fw_version,
2490 sizeof(adapter->fw_version),
2491 "%d.%d.%d",
2492 fw.eep_major, fw.eep_minor, fw.eep_build);
2493 }
2494 }
2495 break;
2496 }
2497
2498 return;
2499}
2500
2501/**
2502 * igb_init_mas - init Media Autosense feature if enabled in the NVM
2503 *
2504 * @adapter: adapter struct
2505 **/
2506static void igb_init_mas(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
2507{
2508 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
2509 u16 eeprom_data;
2510
2511 e1000_read_nvm(hw, NVM_COMPAT, 1, &eeprom_data);
2512 switch (hw->bus.func) {
2513 case E1000_FUNC_0:
2514 if (eeprom_data & IGB_MAS_ENABLE_0)
2515 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_MAS_ENABLE;
2516 break;
2517 case E1000_FUNC_1:
2518 if (eeprom_data & IGB_MAS_ENABLE_1)
2519 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_MAS_ENABLE;
2520 break;
2521 case E1000_FUNC_2:
2522 if (eeprom_data & IGB_MAS_ENABLE_2)
2523 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_MAS_ENABLE;
2524 break;
2525 case E1000_FUNC_3:
2526 if (eeprom_data & IGB_MAS_ENABLE_3)
2527 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_MAS_ENABLE;
2528 break;
2529 default:
2530 /* Shouldn't get here */
2531 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(adapter->pdev),
2532 "%s:AMS: Invalid port configuration, returning\n",
2533 adapter->netdev->name);
2534 break;
2535 }
2536}
2537
2538/**
2539 * igb_probe - Device Initialization Routine
2540 * @pdev: PCI device information struct
2541 * @ent: entry in igb_pci_tbl
2542 *
2543 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
2544 *
2545 * igb_probe initializes an adapter identified by a pci_dev structure.
2546 * The OS initialization, configuring of the adapter private structure,
2547 * and a hardware reset occur.
2548 **/
2549static int __devinit igb_probe(struct pci_dev *pdev,
2550 const struct pci_device_id *ent)
2551{
2552 struct net_device *netdev;
2553 struct igb_adapter *adapter;
2554 struct e1000_hw *hw;
2555 u16 eeprom_data = 0;
2556 u8 pba_str[E1000_PBANUM_LENGTH];
2557 s32 ret_val;
2558 static int global_quad_port_a; /* global quad port a indication */
2559 int i, err, pci_using_dac;
2560 static int cards_found;
2561
2562 err = pci_enable_device_mem(pdev);
2563 if (err)
2564 return err;
2565
2566 pci_using_dac = 0;
2567 err = dma_set_mask(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), DMA_BIT_MASK(64));
2568 if (!err) {
2569 err = dma_set_coherent_mask(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), DMA_BIT_MASK(64));
2570 if (!err)
2571 pci_using_dac = 1;
2572 } else {
2573 err = dma_set_mask(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), DMA_BIT_MASK(32));
2574 if (err) {
2575 err = dma_set_coherent_mask(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), DMA_BIT_MASK(32));
2576 if (err) {
2577 IGB_ERR("No usable DMA configuration, "
2578 "aborting\n");
2579 goto err_dma;
2580 }
2581 }
2582 }
2583
2584#ifndef HAVE_ASPM_QUIRKS
2585 /* 82575 requires that the pci-e link partner disable the L0s state */
2586 switch (pdev->device) {
2587 case E1000_DEV_ID_82575EB_COPPER:
2588 case E1000_DEV_ID_82575EB_FIBER_SERDES:
2589 case E1000_DEV_ID_82575GB_QUAD_COPPER:
2590 pci_disable_link_state(pdev, PCIE_LINK_STATE_L0S);
2591 default:
2592 break;
2593 }
2594
2595#endif /* HAVE_ASPM_QUIRKS */
2596 err = pci_request_selected_regions(pdev,
2597 pci_select_bars(pdev,
2598 IORESOURCE_MEM),
2599 igb_driver_name);
2600 if (err)
2601 goto err_pci_reg;
2602
2603 pci_enable_pcie_error_reporting(pdev);
2604
2605 pci_set_master(pdev);
2606
2607 err = -ENOMEM;
2608#ifdef HAVE_TX_MQ
2609 netdev = alloc_etherdev_mq(sizeof(struct igb_adapter),
2610 IGB_MAX_TX_QUEUES);
2611#else
2612 netdev = alloc_etherdev(sizeof(struct igb_adapter));
2613#endif /* HAVE_TX_MQ */
2614 if (!netdev)
2615 goto err_alloc_etherdev;
2616
2617 SET_MODULE_OWNER(netdev);
2618 SET_NETDEV_DEV(netdev, &pdev->dev);
2619
2620 pci_set_drvdata(pdev, netdev);
2621 adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
2622 adapter->netdev = netdev;
2623 adapter->pdev = pdev;
2624 hw = &adapter->hw;
2625 hw->back = adapter;
2626 adapter->port_num = hw->bus.func;
2627 adapter->msg_enable = (1 << debug) - 1;
2628
2629#ifdef HAVE_PCI_ERS
2630 err = pci_save_state(pdev);
2631 if (err)
2632 goto err_ioremap;
2633#endif
2634 err = -EIO;
2635 hw->hw_addr = ioremap(pci_resource_start(pdev, 0),
2636 pci_resource_len(pdev, 0));
2637 if (!hw->hw_addr)
2638 goto err_ioremap;
2639
2640#ifdef HAVE_NET_DEVICE_OPS
2641 netdev->netdev_ops = &igb_netdev_ops;
2642#else /* HAVE_NET_DEVICE_OPS */
2643 netdev->open = &igb_open;
2644 netdev->stop = &igb_close;
2645 netdev->get_stats = &igb_get_stats;
2646#ifdef HAVE_SET_RX_MODE
2647 netdev->set_rx_mode = &igb_set_rx_mode;
2648#endif
2649 netdev->set_multicast_list = &igb_set_rx_mode;
2650 netdev->set_mac_address = &igb_set_mac;
2651 netdev->change_mtu = &igb_change_mtu;
2652 netdev->do_ioctl = &igb_ioctl;
2653#ifdef HAVE_TX_TIMEOUT
2654 netdev->tx_timeout = &igb_tx_timeout;
2655#endif
2656 netdev->vlan_rx_register = igb_vlan_mode;
2657 netdev->vlan_rx_add_vid = igb_vlan_rx_add_vid;
2658 netdev->vlan_rx_kill_vid = igb_vlan_rx_kill_vid;
2659#ifdef CONFIG_NET_POLL_CONTROLLER
2660 netdev->poll_controller = igb_netpoll;
2661#endif
2662 netdev->hard_start_xmit = &igb_xmit_frame;
2663#endif /* HAVE_NET_DEVICE_OPS */
2664 igb_set_ethtool_ops(netdev);
2665#ifdef HAVE_TX_TIMEOUT
2666 netdev->watchdog_timeo = 5 * HZ;
2667#endif
2668
2669 strncpy(netdev->name, pci_name(pdev), sizeof(netdev->name) - 1);
2670
2671 adapter->bd_number = cards_found;
2672
2673 /* setup the private structure */
2674 err = igb_sw_init(adapter);
2675 if (err)
2676 goto err_sw_init;
2677
2678 e1000_get_bus_info(hw);
2679
2680 hw->phy.autoneg_wait_to_complete = FALSE;
2681 hw->mac.adaptive_ifs = FALSE;
2682
2683 /* Copper options */
2684 if (hw->phy.media_type == e1000_media_type_copper) {
2685 hw->phy.mdix = AUTO_ALL_MODES;
2686 hw->phy.disable_polarity_correction = FALSE;
2687 hw->phy.ms_type = e1000_ms_hw_default;
2688 }
2689
2690 if (e1000_check_reset_block(hw))
2691 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev),
2692 "PHY reset is blocked due to SOL/IDER session.\n");
2693
2694 /*
2695 * features is initialized to 0 in allocation, it might have bits
2696 * set by igb_sw_init so we should use an or instead of an
2697 * assignment.
2698 */
2699 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_SG |
2700 NETIF_F_IP_CSUM |
2701#ifdef NETIF_F_IPV6_CSUM
2702 NETIF_F_IPV6_CSUM |
2703#endif
2704#ifdef NETIF_F_TSO
2705 NETIF_F_TSO |
2706#ifdef NETIF_F_TSO6
2707 NETIF_F_TSO6 |
2708#endif
2709#endif /* NETIF_F_TSO */
2710#ifdef NETIF_F_RXHASH
2711 NETIF_F_RXHASH |
2712#endif
2713 NETIF_F_RXCSUM |
2714#ifdef NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX
2715 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX |
2716 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_TX;
2717#else
2718 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_RX |
2719 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_TX;
2720#endif
2721
2722 if (hw->mac.type >= e1000_82576)
2723 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_SCTP_CSUM;
2724
2725#ifdef HAVE_NDO_SET_FEATURES
2726 /* copy netdev features into list of user selectable features */
2727 netdev->hw_features |= netdev->features;
2728#ifndef IGB_NO_LRO
2729
2730 /* give us the option of enabling LRO later */
2731 netdev->hw_features |= NETIF_F_LRO;
2732#endif
2733#else
2734#ifdef NETIF_F_GRO
2735
2736 /* this is only needed on kernels prior to 2.6.39 */
2737 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_GRO;
2738#endif
2739#endif
2740
2741 /* set this bit last since it cannot be part of hw_features */
2742#ifdef NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_FILTER
2743 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_FILTER;
2744#else
2745 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_FILTER;
2746#endif
2747
2748#ifdef HAVE_NETDEV_VLAN_FEATURES
2749 netdev->vlan_features |= NETIF_F_TSO |
2750 NETIF_F_TSO6 |
2751 NETIF_F_IP_CSUM |
2752 NETIF_F_IPV6_CSUM |
2753 NETIF_F_SG;
2754
2755#endif
2756 if (pci_using_dac)
2757 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_HIGHDMA;
2758
2759 adapter->en_mng_pt = e1000_enable_mng_pass_thru(hw);
2760#ifdef DEBUG
2761 if (adapter->dmac != IGB_DMAC_DISABLE)
2762 printk("%s: DMA Coalescing is enabled..\n", netdev->name);
2763#endif
2764
2765 /* before reading the NVM, reset the controller to put the device in a
2766 * known good starting state */
2767 e1000_reset_hw(hw);
2768
2769 /* make sure the NVM is good */
2770 if (e1000_validate_nvm_checksum(hw) < 0) {
2771 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "The NVM Checksum Is Not"
2772 " Valid\n");
2773 err = -EIO;
2774 goto err_eeprom;
2775 }
2776
2777 /* copy the MAC address out of the NVM */
2778 if (e1000_read_mac_addr(hw))
2779 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "NVM Read Error\n");
2780 memcpy(netdev->dev_addr, hw->mac.addr, netdev->addr_len);
2781#ifdef ETHTOOL_GPERMADDR
2782 memcpy(netdev->perm_addr, hw->mac.addr, netdev->addr_len);
2783
2784 if (!is_valid_ether_addr(netdev->perm_addr)) {
2785#else
2786 if (!is_valid_ether_addr(netdev->dev_addr)) {
2787#endif
2788 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "Invalid MAC Address\n");
2789 err = -EIO;
2790 goto err_eeprom;
2791 }
2792
2793 memcpy(&adapter->mac_table[0].addr, hw->mac.addr, netdev->addr_len);
2794 adapter->mac_table[0].queue = adapter->vfs_allocated_count;
2795 adapter->mac_table[0].state = (IGB_MAC_STATE_DEFAULT | IGB_MAC_STATE_IN_USE);
2796 igb_rar_set(adapter, 0);
2797
2798 /* get firmware version for ethtool -i */
2799 igb_set_fw_version(adapter);
2800
2801 /* Check if Media Autosense is enabled */
2802 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_82580)
2803 igb_init_mas(adapter);
2804#ifdef HAVE_TIMER_SETUP
2805 timer_setup(&adapter->watchdog_timer, &igb_watchdog, 0);
2806 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_DETECT_BAD_DMA)
2807 timer_setup(&adapter->dma_err_timer, &igb_dma_err_timer, 0);
2808 timer_setup(&adapter->phy_info_timer, &igb_update_phy_info, 0);
2809#else
2810 setup_timer(&adapter->watchdog_timer, &igb_watchdog,
2811 (unsigned long) adapter);
2812 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_DETECT_BAD_DMA)
2813 setup_timer(&adapter->dma_err_timer, &igb_dma_err_timer,
2814 (unsigned long) adapter);
2815 setup_timer(&adapter->phy_info_timer, &igb_update_phy_info,
2816 (unsigned long) adapter);
2817#endif
2818
2819 INIT_WORK(&adapter->reset_task, igb_reset_task);
2820 INIT_WORK(&adapter->watchdog_task, igb_watchdog_task);
2821 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_DETECT_BAD_DMA)
2822 INIT_WORK(&adapter->dma_err_task, igb_dma_err_task);
2823
2824 /* Initialize link properties that are user-changeable */
2825 adapter->fc_autoneg = true;
2826 hw->mac.autoneg = true;
2827 hw->phy.autoneg_advertised = 0x2f;
2828
2829 hw->fc.requested_mode = e1000_fc_default;
2830 hw->fc.current_mode = e1000_fc_default;
2831
2832 e1000_validate_mdi_setting(hw);
2833
2834 /* By default, support wake on port A */
2835 if (hw->bus.func == 0)
2836 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED;
2837
2838 /* Check the NVM for wake support for non-port A ports */
2839 if (hw->mac.type >= e1000_82580)
2840 hw->nvm.ops.read(hw, NVM_INIT_CONTROL3_PORT_A +
2841 NVM_82580_LAN_FUNC_OFFSET(hw->bus.func), 1,
2842 &eeprom_data);
2843 else if (hw->bus.func == 1)
2844 e1000_read_nvm(hw, NVM_INIT_CONTROL3_PORT_B, 1, &eeprom_data);
2845
2846 if (eeprom_data & IGB_EEPROM_APME)
2847 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED;
2848
2849 /* now that we have the eeprom settings, apply the special cases where
2850 * the eeprom may be wrong or the board simply won't support wake on
2851 * lan on a particular port */
2852 switch (pdev->device) {
2853 case E1000_DEV_ID_82575GB_QUAD_COPPER:
2854 adapter->flags &= ~IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED;
2855 break;
2856 case E1000_DEV_ID_82575EB_FIBER_SERDES:
2857 case E1000_DEV_ID_82576_FIBER:
2858 case E1000_DEV_ID_82576_SERDES:
2859 /* Wake events only supported on port A for dual fiber
2860 * regardless of eeprom setting */
2861 if (E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_STATUS) & E1000_STATUS_FUNC_1)
2862 adapter->flags &= ~IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED;
2863 break;
2864 case E1000_DEV_ID_82576_QUAD_COPPER:
2865 case E1000_DEV_ID_82576_QUAD_COPPER_ET2:
2866 /* if quad port adapter, disable WoL on all but port A */
2867 if (global_quad_port_a != 0)
2868 adapter->flags &= ~IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED;
2869 else
2870 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_QUAD_PORT_A;
2871 /* Reset for multiple quad port adapters */
2872 if (++global_quad_port_a == 4)
2873 global_quad_port_a = 0;
2874 break;
2875 default:
2876 /* If the device can't wake, don't set software support */
2877 if (!device_can_wakeup(&adapter->pdev->dev))
2878 adapter->flags &= ~IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED;
2879 break;
2880 }
2881
2882 /* initialize the wol settings based on the eeprom settings */
2883 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED)
2884 adapter->wol |= E1000_WUFC_MAG;
2885
2886 /* Some vendors want WoL disabled by default, but still supported */
2887 if ((hw->mac.type == e1000_i350) &&
2888 (pdev->subsystem_vendor == PCI_VENDOR_ID_HP)) {
2889 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED;
2890 adapter->wol = 0;
2891 }
2892
2893 device_set_wakeup_enable(pci_dev_to_dev(adapter->pdev),
2894 adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED);
2895
2896 /* reset the hardware with the new settings */
2897 igb_reset(adapter);
2898 adapter->devrc = 0;
2899
2900#ifdef HAVE_I2C_SUPPORT
2901 /* Init the I2C interface */
2902 err = igb_init_i2c(adapter);
2903 if (err) {
2904 dev_err(&pdev->dev, "failed to init i2c interface\n");
2905 goto err_eeprom;
2906 }
2907#endif /* HAVE_I2C_SUPPORT */
2908
2909 /* let the f/w know that the h/w is now under the control of the
2910 * driver. */
2911 igb_get_hw_control(adapter);
2912
2913 strncpy(netdev->name, "eth%d", IFNAMSIZ);
2914 err = register_netdev(netdev);
2915 if (err)
2916 goto err_register;
2917
2918#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_VMDQ_NETDEV
2919 err = igb_init_vmdq_netdevs(adapter);
2920 if (err)
2921 goto err_register;
2922#endif
2923 /* carrier off reporting is important to ethtool even BEFORE open */
2924 netif_carrier_off(netdev);
2925
2926#ifdef IGB_DCA
2927 if (dca_add_requester(&pdev->dev) == E1000_SUCCESS) {
2928 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_DCA_ENABLED;
2929 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "DCA enabled\n");
2930 igb_setup_dca(adapter);
2931 }
2932
2933#endif
2934#ifdef HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK
2935 /* do hw tstamp init after resetting */
2936 igb_ptp_init(adapter);
2937#endif /* HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK */
2938
2939 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "Intel(R) Gigabit Ethernet Network Connection\n");
2940 /* print bus type/speed/width info */
2941 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "%s: (PCIe:%s:%s) ",
2942 netdev->name,
2943 ((hw->bus.speed == e1000_bus_speed_2500) ? "2.5GT/s" :
2944 (hw->bus.speed == e1000_bus_speed_5000) ? "5.0GT/s" :
2945 (hw->mac.type == e1000_i354) ? "integrated" :
2946 "unknown"),
2947 ((hw->bus.width == e1000_bus_width_pcie_x4) ? "Width x4" :
2948 (hw->bus.width == e1000_bus_width_pcie_x2) ? "Width x2" :
2949 (hw->bus.width == e1000_bus_width_pcie_x1) ? "Width x1" :
2950 (hw->mac.type == e1000_i354) ? "integrated" :
2951 "unknown"));
2952 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "%s: MAC: ", netdev->name);
2953 for (i = 0; i < 6; i++)
2954 printk("%2.2x%c", netdev->dev_addr[i], i == 5 ? '\n' : ':');
2955
2956 ret_val = e1000_read_pba_string(hw, pba_str, E1000_PBANUM_LENGTH);
2957 if (ret_val)
2958 strncpy(pba_str, "Unknown", sizeof(pba_str) - 1);
2959 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "%s: PBA No: %s\n", netdev->name,
2960 pba_str);
2961
2962
2963 /* Initialize the thermal sensor on i350 devices. */
2964 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_i350) {
2965 if (hw->bus.func == 0) {
2966 u16 ets_word;
2967
2968 /*
2969 * Read the NVM to determine if this i350 device
2970 * supports an external thermal sensor.
2971 */
2972 e1000_read_nvm(hw, NVM_ETS_CFG, 1, &ets_word);
2973 if (ets_word != 0x0000 && ets_word != 0xFFFF)
2974 adapter->ets = true;
2975 else
2976 adapter->ets = false;
2977 }
2978#ifdef IGB_HWMON
2979
2980 igb_sysfs_init(adapter);
2981#else
2982#ifdef IGB_PROCFS
2983
2984 igb_procfs_init(adapter);
2985#endif /* IGB_PROCFS */
2986#endif /* IGB_HWMON */
2987 } else {
2988 adapter->ets = false;
2989 }
2990
2991 if (hw->phy.media_type == e1000_media_type_copper) {
2992 switch (hw->mac.type) {
2993 case e1000_i350:
2994 case e1000_i210:
2995 case e1000_i211:
2996 /* Enable EEE for internal copper PHY devices */
2997 err = e1000_set_eee_i350(hw);
2998 if (!err &&
2999 (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_EEE))
3000 adapter->eee_advert =
3001 MDIO_EEE_100TX | MDIO_EEE_1000T;
3002 break;
3003 case e1000_i354:
3004 if ((E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL_EXT)) &
3005 (E1000_CTRL_EXT_LINK_MODE_SGMII)) {
3006 err = e1000_set_eee_i354(hw);
3007 if ((!err) &&
3008 (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_EEE))
3009 adapter->eee_advert =
3010 MDIO_EEE_100TX | MDIO_EEE_1000T;
3011 }
3012 break;
3013 default:
3014 break;
3015 }
3016 }
3017
3018 /* send driver version info to firmware */
3019 if (hw->mac.type >= e1000_i350)
3020 igb_init_fw(adapter);
3021
3022#ifndef IGB_NO_LRO
3023 if (netdev->features & NETIF_F_LRO)
3024 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "Internal LRO is enabled \n");
3025 else
3026 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "LRO is disabled \n");
3027#endif
3028 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev),
3029 "Using %s interrupts. %d rx queue(s), %d tx queue(s)\n",
3030 adapter->msix_entries ? "MSI-X" :
3031 (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_HAS_MSI) ? "MSI" : "legacy",
3032 adapter->num_rx_queues, adapter->num_tx_queues);
3033
3034 cards_found++;
3035
3036 pm_runtime_put_noidle(&pdev->dev);
3037 return 0;
3038
3039err_register:
3040 igb_release_hw_control(adapter);
3041#ifdef HAVE_I2C_SUPPORT
3042 memset(&adapter->i2c_adap, 0, sizeof(adapter->i2c_adap));
3043#endif /* HAVE_I2C_SUPPORT */
3044err_eeprom:
3045 if (!e1000_check_reset_block(hw))
3046 e1000_phy_hw_reset(hw);
3047
3048 if (hw->flash_address)
3049 iounmap(hw->flash_address);
3050err_sw_init:
3051 igb_clear_interrupt_scheme(adapter);
3052 igb_reset_sriov_capability(adapter);
3053 iounmap(hw->hw_addr);
3054err_ioremap:
3055 free_netdev(netdev);
3056err_alloc_etherdev:
3057 pci_release_selected_regions(pdev,
3058 pci_select_bars(pdev, IORESOURCE_MEM));
3059err_pci_reg:
3060err_dma:
3061 pci_disable_device(pdev);
3062 return err;
3063}
3064#ifdef HAVE_I2C_SUPPORT
3065/*
3066 * igb_remove_i2c - Cleanup I2C interface
3067 * @adapter: pointer to adapter structure
3068 *
3069 */
3070static void igb_remove_i2c(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
3071{
3072
3073 /* free the adapter bus structure */
3074 i2c_del_adapter(&adapter->i2c_adap);
3075}
3076#endif /* HAVE_I2C_SUPPORT */
3077
3078/**
3079 * igb_remove - Device Removal Routine
3080 * @pdev: PCI device information struct
3081 *
3082 * igb_remove is called by the PCI subsystem to alert the driver
3083 * that it should release a PCI device. The could be caused by a
3084 * Hot-Plug event, or because the driver is going to be removed from
3085 * memory.
3086 **/
3087static void __devexit igb_remove(struct pci_dev *pdev)
3088{
3089 struct net_device *netdev = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
3090 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
3091 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3092
3093 pm_runtime_get_noresume(&pdev->dev);
3094#ifdef HAVE_I2C_SUPPORT
3095 igb_remove_i2c(adapter);
3096#endif /* HAVE_I2C_SUPPORT */
3097#ifdef HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK
3098 igb_ptp_stop(adapter);
3099#endif /* HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK */
3100
3101 /* flush_scheduled work may reschedule our watchdog task, so
3102 * explicitly disable watchdog tasks from being rescheduled */
3103 set_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state);
3104 del_timer_sync(&adapter->watchdog_timer);
3105 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_DETECT_BAD_DMA)
3106 del_timer_sync(&adapter->dma_err_timer);
3107 del_timer_sync(&adapter->phy_info_timer);
3108
3109 flush_scheduled_work();
3110
3111#ifdef IGB_DCA
3112 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_DCA_ENABLED) {
3113 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "DCA disabled\n");
3114 dca_remove_requester(&pdev->dev);
3115 adapter->flags &= ~IGB_FLAG_DCA_ENABLED;
3116 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_DCA_CTRL, E1000_DCA_CTRL_DCA_DISABLE);
3117 }
3118#endif
3119
3120 /* Release control of h/w to f/w. If f/w is AMT enabled, this
3121 * would have already happened in close and is redundant. */
3122 igb_release_hw_control(adapter);
3123
3124 unregister_netdev(netdev);
3125#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_VMDQ_NETDEV
3126 igb_remove_vmdq_netdevs(adapter);
3127#endif
3128
3129 igb_clear_interrupt_scheme(adapter);
3130 igb_reset_sriov_capability(adapter);
3131
3132 iounmap(hw->hw_addr);
3133 if (hw->flash_address)
3134 iounmap(hw->flash_address);
3135 pci_release_selected_regions(pdev,
3136 pci_select_bars(pdev, IORESOURCE_MEM));
3137
3138#ifdef IGB_HWMON
3139 igb_sysfs_exit(adapter);
3140#else
3141#ifdef IGB_PROCFS
3142 igb_procfs_exit(adapter);
3143#endif /* IGB_PROCFS */
3144#endif /* IGB_HWMON */
3145 kfree(adapter->mac_table);
3146 kfree(adapter->shadow_vfta);
3147 free_netdev(netdev);
3148
3149 pci_disable_pcie_error_reporting(pdev);
3150
3151 pci_disable_device(pdev);
3152}
3153
3154/**
3155 * igb_sw_init - Initialize general software structures (struct igb_adapter)
3156 * @adapter: board private structure to initialize
3157 *
3158 * igb_sw_init initializes the Adapter private data structure.
3159 * Fields are initialized based on PCI device information and
3160 * OS network device settings (MTU size).
3161 **/
3162static int igb_sw_init(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
3163{
3164 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3165 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
3166 struct pci_dev *pdev = adapter->pdev;
3167
3168 /* PCI config space info */
3169
3170 hw->vendor_id = pdev->vendor;
3171 hw->device_id = pdev->device;
3172 hw->subsystem_vendor_id = pdev->subsystem_vendor;
3173 hw->subsystem_device_id = pdev->subsystem_device;
3174
3175 pci_read_config_byte(pdev, PCI_REVISION_ID, &hw->revision_id);
3176
3177 pci_read_config_word(pdev, PCI_COMMAND, &hw->bus.pci_cmd_word);
3178
3179 /* set default ring sizes */
3180 adapter->tx_ring_count = IGB_DEFAULT_TXD;
3181 adapter->rx_ring_count = IGB_DEFAULT_RXD;
3182
3183 /* set default work limits */
3184 adapter->tx_work_limit = IGB_DEFAULT_TX_WORK;
3185
3186 adapter->max_frame_size = netdev->mtu + ETH_HLEN + ETH_FCS_LEN +
3187 VLAN_HLEN;
3188
3189 /* Initialize the hardware-specific values */
3190 if (e1000_setup_init_funcs(hw, TRUE)) {
3191 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "Hardware Initialization Failure\n");
3192 return -EIO;
3193 }
3194
3195 adapter->mac_table = kzalloc(sizeof(struct igb_mac_addr) *
3196 hw->mac.rar_entry_count,
3197 GFP_ATOMIC);
3198
3199 /* Setup and initialize a copy of the hw vlan table array */
3200 adapter->shadow_vfta = kzalloc(sizeof(u32) * E1000_VFTA_ENTRIES,
3201 GFP_ATOMIC);
3202#ifdef NO_KNI
3203 /* These calls may decrease the number of queues */
3204 if (hw->mac.type < e1000_i210) {
3205 igb_set_sriov_capability(adapter);
3206 }
3207
3208 if (igb_init_interrupt_scheme(adapter, true)) {
3209 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "Unable to allocate memory for queues\n");
3210 return -ENOMEM;
3211 }
3212
3213 /* Explicitly disable IRQ since the NIC can be in any state. */
3214 igb_irq_disable(adapter);
3215
3216 set_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state);
3217#endif
3218 return 0;
3219}
3220
3221/**
3222 * igb_open - Called when a network interface is made active
3223 * @netdev: network interface device structure
3224 *
3225 * Returns 0 on success, negative value on failure
3226 *
3227 * The open entry point is called when a network interface is made
3228 * active by the system (IFF_UP). At this point all resources needed
3229 * for transmit and receive operations are allocated, the interrupt
3230 * handler is registered with the OS, the watchdog timer is started,
3231 * and the stack is notified that the interface is ready.
3232 **/
3233static int __igb_open(struct net_device *netdev, bool resuming)
3234{
3235 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
3236 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3237#ifdef CONFIG_PM_RUNTIME
3238 struct pci_dev *pdev = adapter->pdev;
3239#endif /* CONFIG_PM_RUNTIME */
3240 int err;
3241 int i;
3242
3243 /* disallow open during test */
3244 if (test_bit(__IGB_TESTING, &adapter->state)) {
3245 WARN_ON(resuming);
3246 return -EBUSY;
3247 }
3248
3249#ifdef CONFIG_PM_RUNTIME
3250 if (!resuming)
3251 pm_runtime_get_sync(&pdev->dev);
3252#endif /* CONFIG_PM_RUNTIME */
3253
3254 netif_carrier_off(netdev);
3255
3256 /* allocate transmit descriptors */
3257 err = igb_setup_all_tx_resources(adapter);
3258 if (err)
3259 goto err_setup_tx;
3260
3261 /* allocate receive descriptors */
3262 err = igb_setup_all_rx_resources(adapter);
3263 if (err)
3264 goto err_setup_rx;
3265
3266 igb_power_up_link(adapter);
3267
3268 /* before we allocate an interrupt, we must be ready to handle it.
3269 * Setting DEBUG_SHIRQ in the kernel makes it fire an interrupt
3270 * as soon as we call pci_request_irq, so we have to setup our
3271 * clean_rx handler before we do so. */
3272 igb_configure(adapter);
3273
3274 err = igb_request_irq(adapter);
3275 if (err)
3276 goto err_req_irq;
3277
3278 /* Notify the stack of the actual queue counts. */
3279 netif_set_real_num_tx_queues(netdev,
3280 adapter->vmdq_pools ? 1 :
3281 adapter->num_tx_queues);
3282
3283 err = netif_set_real_num_rx_queues(netdev,
3284 adapter->vmdq_pools ? 1 :
3285 adapter->num_rx_queues);
3286 if (err)
3287 goto err_set_queues;
3288
3289 /* From here on the code is the same as igb_up() */
3290 clear_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state);
3291
3292 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_q_vectors; i++)
3293 napi_enable(&(adapter->q_vector[i]->napi));
3294 igb_configure_lli(adapter);
3295
3296 /* Clear any pending interrupts. */
3297 E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ICR);
3298
3299 igb_irq_enable(adapter);
3300
3301 /* notify VFs that reset has been completed */
3302 if (adapter->vfs_allocated_count) {
3303 u32 reg_data = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL_EXT);
3304 reg_data |= E1000_CTRL_EXT_PFRSTD;
3305 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL_EXT, reg_data);
3306 }
3307
3308 netif_tx_start_all_queues(netdev);
3309
3310 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_DETECT_BAD_DMA)
3311 schedule_work(&adapter->dma_err_task);
3312
3313 /* start the watchdog. */
3314 hw->mac.get_link_status = 1;
3315 schedule_work(&adapter->watchdog_task);
3316
3317 return E1000_SUCCESS;
3318
3319err_set_queues:
3320 igb_free_irq(adapter);
3321err_req_irq:
3322 igb_release_hw_control(adapter);
3323 igb_power_down_link(adapter);
3324 igb_free_all_rx_resources(adapter);
3325err_setup_rx:
3326 igb_free_all_tx_resources(adapter);
3327err_setup_tx:
3328 igb_reset(adapter);
3329
3330#ifdef CONFIG_PM_RUNTIME
3331 if (!resuming)
3332 pm_runtime_put(&pdev->dev);
3333#endif /* CONFIG_PM_RUNTIME */
3334
3335 return err;
3336}
3337
3338static int igb_open(struct net_device *netdev)
3339{
3340 return __igb_open(netdev, false);
3341}
3342
3343/**
3344 * igb_close - Disables a network interface
3345 * @netdev: network interface device structure
3346 *
3347 * Returns 0, this is not allowed to fail
3348 *
3349 * The close entry point is called when an interface is de-activated
3350 * by the OS. The hardware is still under the driver's control, but
3351 * needs to be disabled. A global MAC reset is issued to stop the
3352 * hardware, and all transmit and receive resources are freed.
3353 **/
3354static int __igb_close(struct net_device *netdev, bool suspending)
3355{
3356 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
3357#ifdef CONFIG_PM_RUNTIME
3358 struct pci_dev *pdev = adapter->pdev;
3359#endif /* CONFIG_PM_RUNTIME */
3360
3361 WARN_ON(test_bit(__IGB_RESETTING, &adapter->state));
3362
3363#ifdef CONFIG_PM_RUNTIME
3364 if (!suspending)
3365 pm_runtime_get_sync(&pdev->dev);
3366#endif /* CONFIG_PM_RUNTIME */
3367
3368 igb_down(adapter);
3369
3370 igb_release_hw_control(adapter);
3371
3372 igb_free_irq(adapter);
3373
3374 igb_free_all_tx_resources(adapter);
3375 igb_free_all_rx_resources(adapter);
3376
3377#ifdef CONFIG_PM_RUNTIME
3378 if (!suspending)
3379 pm_runtime_put_sync(&pdev->dev);
3380#endif /* CONFIG_PM_RUNTIME */
3381
3382 return 0;
3383}
3384
3385static int igb_close(struct net_device *netdev)
3386{
3387 return __igb_close(netdev, false);
3388}
3389
3390/**
3391 * igb_setup_tx_resources - allocate Tx resources (Descriptors)
3392 * @tx_ring: tx descriptor ring (for a specific queue) to setup
3393 *
3394 * Return 0 on success, negative on failure
3395 **/
3396int igb_setup_tx_resources(struct igb_ring *tx_ring)
3397{
3398 struct device *dev = tx_ring->dev;
3399 int size;
3400
3401 size = sizeof(struct igb_tx_buffer) * tx_ring->count;
3402 tx_ring->tx_buffer_info = vzalloc(size);
3403 if (!tx_ring->tx_buffer_info)
3404 goto err;
3405
3406 /* round up to nearest 4K */
3407 tx_ring->size = tx_ring->count * sizeof(union e1000_adv_tx_desc);
3408 tx_ring->size = ALIGN(tx_ring->size, 4096);
3409
3410 tx_ring->desc = dma_alloc_coherent(dev, tx_ring->size,
3411 &tx_ring->dma, GFP_KERNEL);
3412
3413 if (!tx_ring->desc)
3414 goto err;
3415
3416 tx_ring->next_to_use = 0;
3417 tx_ring->next_to_clean = 0;
3418
3419 return 0;
3420
3421err:
3422 vfree(tx_ring->tx_buffer_info);
3423 dev_err(dev,
3424 "Unable to allocate memory for the transmit descriptor ring\n");
3425 return -ENOMEM;
3426}
3427
3428/**
3429 * igb_setup_all_tx_resources - wrapper to allocate Tx resources
3430 * (Descriptors) for all queues
3431 * @adapter: board private structure
3432 *
3433 * Return 0 on success, negative on failure
3434 **/
3435static int igb_setup_all_tx_resources(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
3436{
3437 struct pci_dev *pdev = adapter->pdev;
3438 int i, err = 0;
3439
3440 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++) {
3441 err = igb_setup_tx_resources(adapter->tx_ring[i]);
3442 if (err) {
3443 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev),
3444 "Allocation for Tx Queue %u failed\n", i);
3445 for (i--; i >= 0; i--)
3446 igb_free_tx_resources(adapter->tx_ring[i]);
3447 break;
3448 }
3449 }
3450
3451 return err;
3452}
3453
3454/**
3455 * igb_setup_tctl - configure the transmit control registers
3456 * @adapter: Board private structure
3457 **/
3458void igb_setup_tctl(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
3459{
3460 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3461 u32 tctl;
3462
3463 /* disable queue 0 which is enabled by default on 82575 and 82576 */
3464 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_TXDCTL(0), 0);
3465
3466 /* Program the Transmit Control Register */
3467 tctl = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_TCTL);
3468 tctl &= ~E1000_TCTL_CT;
3469 tctl |= E1000_TCTL_PSP | E1000_TCTL_RTLC |
3470 (E1000_COLLISION_THRESHOLD << E1000_CT_SHIFT);
3471
3472 e1000_config_collision_dist(hw);
3473
3474 /* Enable transmits */
3475 tctl |= E1000_TCTL_EN;
3476
3477 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_TCTL, tctl);
3478}
3479
3480static u32 igb_tx_wthresh(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
3481{
3482 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3483 switch (hw->mac.type) {
3484 case e1000_i354:
3485 return 4;
3486 case e1000_82576:
3487 if (adapter->msix_entries)
3488 return 1;
3489 default:
3490 break;
3491 }
3492
3493 return 16;
3494}
3495
3496/**
3497 * igb_configure_tx_ring - Configure transmit ring after Reset
3498 * @adapter: board private structure
3499 * @ring: tx ring to configure
3500 *
3501 * Configure a transmit ring after a reset.
3502 **/
3503void igb_configure_tx_ring(struct igb_adapter *adapter,
3504 struct igb_ring *ring)
3505{
3506 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3507 u32 txdctl = 0;
3508 u64 tdba = ring->dma;
3509 int reg_idx = ring->reg_idx;
3510
3511 /* disable the queue */
3512 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_TXDCTL(reg_idx), 0);
3513 E1000_WRITE_FLUSH(hw);
3514 mdelay(10);
3515
3516 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_TDLEN(reg_idx),
3517 ring->count * sizeof(union e1000_adv_tx_desc));
3518 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_TDBAL(reg_idx),
3519 tdba & 0x00000000ffffffffULL);
3520 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_TDBAH(reg_idx), tdba >> 32);
3521
3522 ring->tail = hw->hw_addr + E1000_TDT(reg_idx);
3523 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_TDH(reg_idx), 0);
3524 writel(0, ring->tail);
3525
3526 txdctl |= IGB_TX_PTHRESH;
3527 txdctl |= IGB_TX_HTHRESH << 8;
3528 txdctl |= igb_tx_wthresh(adapter) << 16;
3529
3530 txdctl |= E1000_TXDCTL_QUEUE_ENABLE;
3531 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_TXDCTL(reg_idx), txdctl);
3532}
3533
3534/**
3535 * igb_configure_tx - Configure transmit Unit after Reset
3536 * @adapter: board private structure
3537 *
3538 * Configure the Tx unit of the MAC after a reset.
3539 **/
3540static void igb_configure_tx(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
3541{
3542 int i;
3543
3544 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++)
3545 igb_configure_tx_ring(adapter, adapter->tx_ring[i]);
3546}

3548/**
3549 * igb_setup_rx_resources - allocate Rx resources (Descriptors)
3550 * @rx_ring: rx descriptor ring (for a specific queue) to setup
3551 *
3552 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
3553 **/
3554int igb_setup_rx_resources(struct igb_ring *rx_ring)
3555{
3556 struct device *dev = rx_ring->dev;
3557 int size, desc_len;
3558
3559 size = sizeof(struct igb_rx_buffer) * rx_ring->count;
3560 rx_ring->rx_buffer_info = vzalloc(size);
3561 if (!rx_ring->rx_buffer_info)
3562 goto err;
3563
3564 desc_len = sizeof(union e1000_adv_rx_desc);
3565
3566 /* Round up to nearest 4K */
3567 rx_ring->size = rx_ring->count * desc_len;
3568 rx_ring->size = ALIGN(rx_ring->size, 4096);
3569
3570 rx_ring->desc = dma_alloc_coherent(dev, rx_ring->size,
3571 &rx_ring->dma, GFP_KERNEL);
3572
3573 if (!rx_ring->desc)
3574 goto err;
3575
3576 rx_ring->next_to_alloc = 0;
3577 rx_ring->next_to_clean = 0;
3578 rx_ring->next_to_use = 0;
3579
3580 return 0;
3581
3582err:
3583 vfree(rx_ring->rx_buffer_info);
3584 rx_ring->rx_buffer_info = NULL;
3585 dev_err(dev, "Unable to allocate memory for the receive descriptor"
3586 " ring\n");
3587 return -ENOMEM;
3588}

3590/**

3592 * (Descriptors) for all queues

3596 **/
3597static int igb_setup_all_rx_resources(struct igb_adapter *adapter)

3599 struct pci_dev *pdev = adapter->pdev;
3600 int i, err = 0;
3601
3602 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++) {
3603 err = igb_setup_rx_resources(adapter->rx_ring[i]);
3604 if (err) {
3605 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev),
3606 "Allocation for Rx Queue %u failed\n", i);
3607 for (i--; i >= 0; i--)
3608 igb_free_rx_resources(adapter->rx_ring[i]);
3609 break;
3610 }
3611 }
3612
3613 return err;
3614}
3615
3616/**
3617 * igb_setup_mrqc - configure the multiple receive queue control registers
3618 * @adapter: Board private structure
3619 **/
3620static void igb_setup_mrqc(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
3621{
3622 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3623 u32 mrqc, rxcsum;
3624 u32 j, num_rx_queues, shift = 0, shift2 = 0;
3625 static const u32 rsskey[10] = { 0xDA565A6D, 0xC20E5B25, 0x3D256741,
3626 0xB08FA343, 0xCB2BCAD0, 0xB4307BAE,
3627 0xA32DCB77, 0x0CF23080, 0x3BB7426A,
3628 0xFA01ACBE };
3629
3630 /* Fill out hash function seeds */
3631 for (j = 0; j < 10; j++)
3632 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RSSRK(j), rsskey[j]);
3633
3634 num_rx_queues = adapter->rss_queues;
3635
3636 /* 82575 and 82576 supports 2 RSS queues for VMDq */
3637 switch (hw->mac.type) {
3638 case e1000_82575:
3639 if (adapter->vmdq_pools) {
3640 shift = 2;
3641 shift2 = 6;
3642 break;
3643 }
3644 shift = 6;
3645 break;
3646 case e1000_82576:
3647 /* 82576 supports 2 RSS queues for SR-IOV */
3648 if (adapter->vfs_allocated_count || adapter->vmdq_pools) {
3649 shift = 3;
3650 num_rx_queues = 2;
3651 }
3652 break;
3653 default:
3654 break;
3655 }
3656
3657 /*
3658 * Populate the redirection table 4 entries at a time. To do this
3659 * we are generating the results for n and n+2 and then interleaving
3660 * those with the results with n+1 and n+3.
3661 */
3662 for (j = 0; j < 32; j++) {
3663 /* first pass generates n and n+2 */
3664 u32 base = ((j * 0x00040004) + 0x00020000) * num_rx_queues;
3665 u32 reta = (base & 0x07800780) >> (7 - shift);
3666
3667 /* second pass generates n+1 and n+3 */
3668 base += 0x00010001 * num_rx_queues;
3669 reta |= (base & 0x07800780) << (1 + shift);
3670
3671 /* generate 2nd table for 82575 based parts */
3672 if (shift2)
3673 reta |= (0x01010101 * num_rx_queues) << shift2;
3674
3675 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RETA(j), reta);
3676 }
3677
3678 /*
3679 * Disable raw packet checksumming so that RSS hash is placed in
3680 * descriptor on writeback. No need to enable TCP/UDP/IP checksum
3681 * offloads as they are enabled by default
3682 */
3683 rxcsum = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RXCSUM);
3684 rxcsum |= E1000_RXCSUM_PCSD;
3685
3686 if (adapter->hw.mac.type >= e1000_82576)
3687 /* Enable Receive Checksum Offload for SCTP */
3688 rxcsum |= E1000_RXCSUM_CRCOFL;
3689
3690 /* Don't need to set TUOFL or IPOFL, they default to 1 */
3691 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RXCSUM, rxcsum);
3692
3693 /* Generate RSS hash based on packet types, TCP/UDP
3694 * port numbers and/or IPv4/v6 src and dst addresses
3695 */
3696 mrqc = E1000_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV4 |
3697 E1000_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV4_TCP |
3698 E1000_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV6 |
3699 E1000_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV6_TCP |
3700 E1000_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV6_TCP_EX;
3701
3702 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_RSS_FIELD_IPV4_UDP)
3703 mrqc |= E1000_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV4_UDP;
3704 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_RSS_FIELD_IPV6_UDP)
3705 mrqc |= E1000_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV6_UDP;
3706
3707 /* If VMDq is enabled then we set the appropriate mode for that, else
3708 * we default to RSS so that an RSS hash is calculated per packet even
3709 * if we are only using one queue */
3710 if (adapter->vfs_allocated_count || adapter->vmdq_pools) {
3711 if (hw->mac.type > e1000_82575) {
3712 /* Set the default pool for the PF's first queue */
3713 u32 vtctl = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_VT_CTL);
3714 vtctl &= ~(E1000_VT_CTL_DEFAULT_POOL_MASK |
3715 E1000_VT_CTL_DISABLE_DEF_POOL);
3716 vtctl |= adapter->vfs_allocated_count <<
3717 E1000_VT_CTL_DEFAULT_POOL_SHIFT;
3718 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_VT_CTL, vtctl);
3719 } else if (adapter->rss_queues > 1) {
3720 /* set default queue for pool 1 to queue 2 */
3721 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_VT_CTL,
3722 adapter->rss_queues << 7);
3723 }
3724 if (adapter->rss_queues > 1)
3725 mrqc |= E1000_MRQC_ENABLE_VMDQ_RSS_2Q;
3726 else
3727 mrqc |= E1000_MRQC_ENABLE_VMDQ;
3728 } else {
3729 mrqc |= E1000_MRQC_ENABLE_RSS_4Q;
3730 }
3731 igb_vmm_control(adapter);
3732
3733 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_MRQC, mrqc);
3734}
3735
3736/**
3737 * igb_setup_rctl - configure the receive control registers
3738 * @adapter: Board private structure
3739 **/
3740void igb_setup_rctl(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
3741{
3742 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3743 u32 rctl;
3744
3745 rctl = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RCTL);
3746
3747 rctl &= ~(3 << E1000_RCTL_MO_SHIFT);
3748 rctl &= ~(E1000_RCTL_LBM_TCVR | E1000_RCTL_LBM_MAC);
3749
3750 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_EN | E1000_RCTL_BAM | E1000_RCTL_RDMTS_HALF |
3751 (hw->mac.mc_filter_type << E1000_RCTL_MO_SHIFT);
3752
3753 /*
3754 * enable stripping of CRC. It's unlikely this will break BMC
3755 * redirection as it did with e1000. Newer features require
3756 * that the HW strips the CRC.
3757 */
3758 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_SECRC;
3759
3760 /* disable store bad packets and clear size bits. */
3761 rctl &= ~(E1000_RCTL_SBP | E1000_RCTL_SZ_256);
3762
3763 /* enable LPE to prevent packets larger than max_frame_size */
3764 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_LPE;
3765
3766 /* disable queue 0 to prevent tail write w/o re-config */
3767 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RXDCTL(0), 0);
3768
3769 /* Attention!!! For SR-IOV PF driver operations you must enable
3770 * queue drop for all VF and PF queues to prevent head of line blocking
3771 * if an un-trusted VF does not provide descriptors to hardware.
3772 */
3773 if (adapter->vfs_allocated_count) {
3774 /* set all queue drop enable bits */
3775 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_QDE, ALL_QUEUES);
3776 }
3777
3778 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RCTL, rctl);
3779}
3780
3781static inline int igb_set_vf_rlpml(struct igb_adapter *adapter, int size,
3782 int vfn)
3783{
3784 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3785 u32 vmolr;
3786
3787 /* if it isn't the PF check to see if VFs are enabled and
3788 * increase the size to support vlan tags */
3789 if (vfn < adapter->vfs_allocated_count &&
3790 adapter->vf_data[vfn].vlans_enabled)
3791 size += VLAN_HLEN;
3792
3793#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_VMDQ_NETDEV
3794 if (vfn >= adapter->vfs_allocated_count) {
3795 int queue = vfn - adapter->vfs_allocated_count;
3796 struct igb_vmdq_adapter *vadapter;
3797
3798 vadapter = netdev_priv(adapter->vmdq_netdev[queue-1]);
3799 if (vadapter->vlgrp)
3800 size += VLAN_HLEN;
3801 }
3802#endif
3803 vmolr = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_VMOLR(vfn));
3804 vmolr &= ~E1000_VMOLR_RLPML_MASK;
3805 vmolr |= size | E1000_VMOLR_LPE;
3806 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_VMOLR(vfn), vmolr);
3807
3808 return 0;
3809}
3810
3811/**
3812 * igb_rlpml_set - set maximum receive packet size
3813 * @adapter: board private structure
3814 *
3815 * Configure maximum receivable packet size.
3816 **/
3817static void igb_rlpml_set(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
3818{
3819 u32 max_frame_size = adapter->max_frame_size;
3820 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3821 u16 pf_id = adapter->vfs_allocated_count;
3822
3823 if (adapter->vmdq_pools && hw->mac.type != e1000_82575) {
3824 int i;
3825 for (i = 0; i < adapter->vmdq_pools; i++)
3826 igb_set_vf_rlpml(adapter, max_frame_size, pf_id + i);
3827 /*
3828 * If we're in VMDQ or SR-IOV mode, then set global RLPML
3829 * to our max jumbo frame size, in case we need to enable
3830 * jumbo frames on one of the rings later.
3831 * This will not pass over-length frames into the default
3832 * queue because it's gated by the VMOLR.RLPML.
3833 */
3834 max_frame_size = MAX_JUMBO_FRAME_SIZE;
3835 }
3836 /* Set VF RLPML for the PF device. */
3837 if (adapter->vfs_allocated_count)
3838 igb_set_vf_rlpml(adapter, max_frame_size, pf_id);
3839
3840 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RLPML, max_frame_size);
3841}
3842
3843static inline void igb_set_vf_vlan_strip(struct igb_adapter *adapter,
3844 int vfn, bool enable)
3845{
3846 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3847 u32 val;
3848 void __iomem *reg;
3849
3850 if (hw->mac.type < e1000_82576)
3851 return;
3852
3853 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_i350)
3854 reg = hw->hw_addr + E1000_DVMOLR(vfn);
3855 else
3856 reg = hw->hw_addr + E1000_VMOLR(vfn);
3857
3858 val = readl(reg);
3859 if (enable)
3860 val |= E1000_VMOLR_STRVLAN;
3861 else
3862 val &= ~(E1000_VMOLR_STRVLAN);
3863 writel(val, reg);
3864}
3865static inline void igb_set_vmolr(struct igb_adapter *adapter,
3866 int vfn, bool aupe)
3867{
3868 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3869 u32 vmolr;
3870
3871 /*
3872 * This register exists only on 82576 and newer so if we are older then
3873 * we should exit and do nothing
3874 */
3875 if (hw->mac.type < e1000_82576)
3876 return;
3877
3878 vmolr = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_VMOLR(vfn));
3879
3880 if (aupe)
3881 vmolr |= E1000_VMOLR_AUPE; /* Accept untagged packets */
3882 else
3883 vmolr &= ~(E1000_VMOLR_AUPE); /* Tagged packets ONLY */
3884
3885 /* clear all bits that might not be set */
3886 vmolr &= ~E1000_VMOLR_RSSE;
3887
3888 if (adapter->rss_queues > 1 && vfn == adapter->vfs_allocated_count)
3889 vmolr |= E1000_VMOLR_RSSE; /* enable RSS */
3890
3891 vmolr |= E1000_VMOLR_BAM; /* Accept broadcast */
3892 vmolr |= E1000_VMOLR_LPE; /* Accept long packets */
3893
3894 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_VMOLR(vfn), vmolr);
3895}
3896
3897/**
3898 * igb_configure_rx_ring - Configure a receive ring after Reset
3899 * @adapter: board private structure
3900 * @ring: receive ring to be configured
3901 *
3902 * Configure the Rx unit of the MAC after a reset.
3903 **/
3904void igb_configure_rx_ring(struct igb_adapter *adapter,
3905 struct igb_ring *ring)
3906{
3907 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3908 u64 rdba = ring->dma;
3909 int reg_idx = ring->reg_idx;
3910 u32 srrctl = 0, rxdctl = 0;
3911
3912#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
3913 /*
3914 * RLPML prevents us from receiving a frame larger than max_frame so
3915 * it is safe to just set the rx_buffer_len to max_frame without the
3916 * risk of an skb over panic.
3917 */
3918 ring->rx_buffer_len = max_t(u32, adapter->max_frame_size,
3919 MAXIMUM_ETHERNET_VLAN_SIZE);
3920
3921#endif
3922 /* disable the queue */
3923 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RXDCTL(reg_idx), 0);
3924
3925 /* Set DMA base address registers */
3926 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RDBAL(reg_idx),
3927 rdba & 0x00000000ffffffffULL);
3928 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RDBAH(reg_idx), rdba >> 32);
3929 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RDLEN(reg_idx),
3930 ring->count * sizeof(union e1000_adv_rx_desc));
3931
3932 /* initialize head and tail */
3933 ring->tail = hw->hw_addr + E1000_RDT(reg_idx);
3934 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RDH(reg_idx), 0);
3935 writel(0, ring->tail);
3936
3937 /* reset next-to- use/clean to place SW in sync with hardwdare */
3938 ring->next_to_clean = 0;
3939 ring->next_to_use = 0;
3940#ifndef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
3941 ring->next_to_alloc = 0;
3942
3943#endif
3944 /* set descriptor configuration */
3945#ifndef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
3946 srrctl = IGB_RX_HDR_LEN << E1000_SRRCTL_BSIZEHDRSIZE_SHIFT;
3947 srrctl |= IGB_RX_BUFSZ >> E1000_SRRCTL_BSIZEPKT_SHIFT;
3948#else /* CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT */
3949 srrctl = ALIGN(ring->rx_buffer_len, 1024) >>
3950 E1000_SRRCTL_BSIZEPKT_SHIFT;
3951#endif /* CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT */
3952 srrctl |= E1000_SRRCTL_DESCTYPE_ADV_ONEBUF;
3953#ifdef HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK
3954 if (hw->mac.type >= e1000_82580)
3955 srrctl |= E1000_SRRCTL_TIMESTAMP;
3956#endif /* HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK */
3957 /*
3958 * We should set the drop enable bit if:
3959 * SR-IOV is enabled
3960 * or
3961 * Flow Control is disabled and number of RX queues > 1
3962 *
3963 * This allows us to avoid head of line blocking for security
3964 * and performance reasons.
3965 */
3966 if (adapter->vfs_allocated_count ||
3967 (adapter->num_rx_queues > 1 &&
3968 (hw->fc.requested_mode == e1000_fc_none ||
3969 hw->fc.requested_mode == e1000_fc_rx_pause)))
3970 srrctl |= E1000_SRRCTL_DROP_EN;
3971
3972 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_SRRCTL(reg_idx), srrctl);
3973
3974 /* set filtering for VMDQ pools */
3975 igb_set_vmolr(adapter, reg_idx & 0x7, true);
3976
3977 rxdctl |= IGB_RX_PTHRESH;
3978 rxdctl |= IGB_RX_HTHRESH << 8;
3979 rxdctl |= IGB_RX_WTHRESH << 16;
3980
3981 /* enable receive descriptor fetching */
3982 rxdctl |= E1000_RXDCTL_QUEUE_ENABLE;
3983 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RXDCTL(reg_idx), rxdctl);
3984}
3985
3986/**
3987 * igb_configure_rx - Configure receive Unit after Reset
3988 * @adapter: board private structure
3989 *
3990 * Configure the Rx unit of the MAC after a reset.
3991 **/
3992static void igb_configure_rx(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
3993{
3994 int i;
3995
3996 /* set UTA to appropriate mode */
3997 igb_set_uta(adapter);
3998
3999 igb_full_sync_mac_table(adapter);
4000 /* Setup the HW Rx Head and Tail Descriptor Pointers and
4001 * the Base and Length of the Rx Descriptor Ring */
4002 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++)
4003 igb_configure_rx_ring(adapter, adapter->rx_ring[i]);
4004}
4005
4006/**
4007 * igb_free_tx_resources - Free Tx Resources per Queue
4008 * @tx_ring: Tx descriptor ring for a specific queue
4009 *
4010 * Free all transmit software resources
4011 **/
4012void igb_free_tx_resources(struct igb_ring *tx_ring)
4013{
4014 igb_clean_tx_ring(tx_ring);
4015
4016 vfree(tx_ring->tx_buffer_info);
4017 tx_ring->tx_buffer_info = NULL;
4018
4019 /* if not set, then don't free */
4020 if (!tx_ring->desc)
4021 return;
4022
4023 dma_free_coherent(tx_ring->dev, tx_ring->size,
4024 tx_ring->desc, tx_ring->dma);
4025
4026 tx_ring->desc = NULL;
4027}
4028
4029/**
4030 * igb_free_all_tx_resources - Free Tx Resources for All Queues
4031 * @adapter: board private structure
4032 *
4033 * Free all transmit software resources
4034 **/
4035static void igb_free_all_tx_resources(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
4036{
4037 int i;
4038
4039 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++)
4040 igb_free_tx_resources(adapter->tx_ring[i]);
4041}
4042
4043void igb_unmap_and_free_tx_resource(struct igb_ring *ring,
4044 struct igb_tx_buffer *tx_buffer)
4045{
4046 if (tx_buffer->skb) {
4047 dev_kfree_skb_any(tx_buffer->skb);
4048 if (dma_unmap_len(tx_buffer, len))
4049 dma_unmap_single(ring->dev,
4050 dma_unmap_addr(tx_buffer, dma),
4051 dma_unmap_len(tx_buffer, len),
4052 DMA_TO_DEVICE);
4053 } else if (dma_unmap_len(tx_buffer, len)) {
4054 dma_unmap_page(ring->dev,
4055 dma_unmap_addr(tx_buffer, dma),
4056 dma_unmap_len(tx_buffer, len),
4057 DMA_TO_DEVICE);
4058 }
4059 tx_buffer->next_to_watch = NULL;
4060 tx_buffer->skb = NULL;
4061 dma_unmap_len_set(tx_buffer, len, 0);
4062 /* buffer_info must be completely set up in the transmit path */
4063}
4064
4065/**
4066 * igb_clean_tx_ring - Free Tx Buffers
4067 * @tx_ring: ring to be cleaned
4068 **/
4069static void igb_clean_tx_ring(struct igb_ring *tx_ring)
4070{
4071 struct igb_tx_buffer *buffer_info;
4072 unsigned long size;
4073 u16 i;
4074
4075 if (!tx_ring->tx_buffer_info)
4076 return;
4077 /* Free all the Tx ring sk_buffs */
4078
4079 for (i = 0; i < tx_ring->count; i++) {
4080 buffer_info = &tx_ring->tx_buffer_info[i];
4081 igb_unmap_and_free_tx_resource(tx_ring, buffer_info);
4082 }
4083
4084 netdev_tx_reset_queue(txring_txq(tx_ring));
4085
4086 size = sizeof(struct igb_tx_buffer) * tx_ring->count;
4087 memset(tx_ring->tx_buffer_info, 0, size);
4088
4089 /* Zero out the descriptor ring */
4090 memset(tx_ring->desc, 0, tx_ring->size);
4091
4092 tx_ring->next_to_use = 0;
4093 tx_ring->next_to_clean = 0;
4094}
4095
4096/**
4097 * igb_clean_all_tx_rings - Free Tx Buffers for all queues
4098 * @adapter: board private structure
4099 **/
4100static void igb_clean_all_tx_rings(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
4101{
4102 int i;
4103
4104 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++)
4105 igb_clean_tx_ring(adapter->tx_ring[i]);
4106}

4127

4144
4145/**
4146 * igb_clean_rx_ring - Free Rx Buffers per Queue
4147 * @rx_ring: ring to free buffers from
4148 **/
4149void igb_clean_rx_ring(struct igb_ring *rx_ring)
4150{
4151 unsigned long size;
4152 u16 i;
4153
4154 if (!rx_ring->rx_buffer_info)
4155 return;
4156
4157#ifndef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
4158 if (rx_ring->skb)
4159 dev_kfree_skb(rx_ring->skb);
4160 rx_ring->skb = NULL;
4161
4162#endif
4163 /* Free all the Rx ring sk_buffs */
4164 for (i = 0; i < rx_ring->count; i++) {
4165 struct igb_rx_buffer *buffer_info = &rx_ring->rx_buffer_info[i];
4166#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
4167 if (buffer_info->dma) {
4168 dma_unmap_single(rx_ring->dev,
4169 buffer_info->dma,
4170 rx_ring->rx_buffer_len,
4171 DMA_FROM_DEVICE);
4172 buffer_info->dma = 0;
4173 }
4174
4175 if (buffer_info->skb) {
4176 dev_kfree_skb(buffer_info->skb);
4177 buffer_info->skb = NULL;
4178 }
4179#else
4180 if (!buffer_info->page)
4181 continue;
4182
4183 dma_unmap_page(rx_ring->dev,
4184 buffer_info->dma,
4185 PAGE_SIZE,
4186 DMA_FROM_DEVICE);
4187 __free_page(buffer_info->page);
4188
4189 buffer_info->page = NULL;
4190#endif
4191 }
4192
4193 size = sizeof(struct igb_rx_buffer) * rx_ring->count;
4194 memset(rx_ring->rx_buffer_info, 0, size);
4195
4196 /* Zero out the descriptor ring */
4197 memset(rx_ring->desc, 0, rx_ring->size);
4198
4199 rx_ring->next_to_alloc = 0;
4200 rx_ring->next_to_clean = 0;
4201 rx_ring->next_to_use = 0;
4202}
4203
4204/**
4205 * igb_clean_all_rx_rings - Free Rx Buffers for all queues
4206 * @adapter: board private structure
4207 **/
4208static void igb_clean_all_rx_rings(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
4209{
4210 int i;
4211
4212 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++)
4213 igb_clean_rx_ring(adapter->rx_ring[i]);
4214}
