4216/**
4217 * igb_set_mac - Change the Ethernet Address of the NIC
4218 * @netdev: network interface device structure
4219 * @p: pointer to an address structure
4220 *
4221 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
4222 **/
4223static int igb_set_mac(struct net_device *netdev, void *p)
4224{
4225 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
4226 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4227 struct sockaddr *addr = p;
4228
4229 if (!is_valid_ether_addr(addr->sa_data))
4230 return -EADDRNOTAVAIL;
4231
4232 igb_del_mac_filter(adapter, hw->mac.addr,
4233 adapter->vfs_allocated_count);
4234 memcpy(netdev->dev_addr, addr->sa_data, netdev->addr_len);
4235 memcpy(hw->mac.addr, addr->sa_data, netdev->addr_len);
4236
4237 /* set the correct pool for the new PF MAC address in entry 0 */
4238 return igb_add_mac_filter(adapter, hw->mac.addr,
4239 adapter->vfs_allocated_count);
4240}
4241
4242/**
4243 * igb_write_mc_addr_list - write multicast addresses to MTA
4244 * @netdev: network interface device structure
4245 *
4246 * Writes multicast address list to the MTA hash table.
4247 * Returns: -ENOMEM on failure
4248 * 0 on no addresses written
4249 * X on writing X addresses to MTA
4250 **/
4251int igb_write_mc_addr_list(struct net_device *netdev)
4252{
4253 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
4254 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4255#ifdef NETDEV_HW_ADDR_T_MULTICAST
4256 struct netdev_hw_addr *ha;
4257#else
4258 struct dev_mc_list *ha;
4259#endif
4260 u8 *mta_list;
4261 int i, count;
4262#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_VMDQ_NETDEV
4263 int vm;
4264#endif
4265 count = netdev_mc_count(netdev);
4266#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_VMDQ_NETDEV
4267 for (vm = 1; vm < adapter->vmdq_pools; vm++) {
4268 if (!adapter->vmdq_netdev[vm])
4269 break;
4270 if (!netif_running(adapter->vmdq_netdev[vm]))
4271 continue;
4272 count += netdev_mc_count(adapter->vmdq_netdev[vm]);
4273 }
4274#endif
4275
4276 if (!count) {
4277 e1000_update_mc_addr_list(hw, NULL, 0);
4278 return 0;
4279 }
4280 mta_list = kzalloc(count * 6, GFP_ATOMIC);
4281 if (!mta_list)
4282 return -ENOMEM;
4283
4284 /* The shared function expects a packed array of only addresses. */
4285 i = 0;
4286 netdev_for_each_mc_addr(ha, netdev)
4287#ifdef NETDEV_HW_ADDR_T_MULTICAST
4288 memcpy(mta_list + (i++ * ETH_ALEN), ha->addr, ETH_ALEN);
4289#else
4290 memcpy(mta_list + (i++ * ETH_ALEN), ha->dmi_addr, ETH_ALEN);
4291#endif
4292#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_VMDQ_NETDEV
4293 for (vm = 1; vm < adapter->vmdq_pools; vm++) {
4294 if (!adapter->vmdq_netdev[vm])
4295 break;
4296 if (!netif_running(adapter->vmdq_netdev[vm]) ||
4297 !netdev_mc_count(adapter->vmdq_netdev[vm]))
4298 continue;
4299 netdev_for_each_mc_addr(ha, adapter->vmdq_netdev[vm])
4300#ifdef NETDEV_HW_ADDR_T_MULTICAST
4301 memcpy(mta_list + (i++ * ETH_ALEN),
4302 ha->addr, ETH_ALEN);
4303#else
4304 memcpy(mta_list + (i++ * ETH_ALEN),
4305 ha->dmi_addr, ETH_ALEN);
4306#endif
4307 }
4308#endif
4309 e1000_update_mc_addr_list(hw, mta_list, i);
4310 kfree(mta_list);
4311
4312 return count;
4313}
4314
4315void igb_rar_set(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u32 index)
4316{
4317 u32 rar_low, rar_high;
4318 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4319 u8 *addr = adapter->mac_table[index].addr;
4320 /* HW expects these in little endian so we reverse the byte order
4321 * from network order (big endian) to little endian
4322 */
4323 rar_low = ((u32) addr[0] | ((u32) addr[1] << 8) |
4324 ((u32) addr[2] << 16) | ((u32) addr[3] << 24));
4325 rar_high = ((u32) addr[4] | ((u32) addr[5] << 8));
4326
4327 /* Indicate to hardware the Address is Valid. */
4328 if (adapter->mac_table[index].state & IGB_MAC_STATE_IN_USE)
4329 rar_high |= E1000_RAH_AV;
4330
4331 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_82575)
4332 rar_high |= E1000_RAH_POOL_1 * adapter->mac_table[index].queue;
4333 else
4334 rar_high |= E1000_RAH_POOL_1 << adapter->mac_table[index].queue;
4335
4336 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RAL(index), rar_low);
4337 E1000_WRITE_FLUSH(hw);
4338 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RAH(index), rar_high);
4339 E1000_WRITE_FLUSH(hw);
4340}
4341
4342void igb_full_sync_mac_table(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
4343{
4344 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4345 int i;
4346 for (i = 0; i < hw->mac.rar_entry_count; i++) {
4347 igb_rar_set(adapter, i);
4348 }
4349}
4350
4351void igb_sync_mac_table(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
4352{
4353 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4354 int i;
4355 for (i = 0; i < hw->mac.rar_entry_count; i++) {
4356 if (adapter->mac_table[i].state & IGB_MAC_STATE_MODIFIED)
4357 igb_rar_set(adapter, i);
4358 adapter->mac_table[i].state &= ~(IGB_MAC_STATE_MODIFIED);
4359 }
4360}
4361
4362int igb_available_rars(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
4363{
4364 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4365 int i, count = 0;
4366
4367 for (i = 0; i < hw->mac.rar_entry_count; i++) {
4368 if (adapter->mac_table[i].state == 0)
4369 count++;
4370 }
4371 return count;
4372}
4373
4374#ifdef HAVE_SET_RX_MODE
4375/**
4376 * igb_write_uc_addr_list - write unicast addresses to RAR table
4377 * @netdev: network interface device structure
4378 *
4379 * Writes unicast address list to the RAR table.
4380 * Returns: -ENOMEM on failure/insufficient address space
4381 * 0 on no addresses written
4382 * X on writing X addresses to the RAR table
4383 **/
4384static int igb_write_uc_addr_list(struct net_device *netdev)
4385{
4386 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
4387 unsigned int vfn = adapter->vfs_allocated_count;
4388 int count = 0;
4389
4390 /* return ENOMEM indicating insufficient memory for addresses */
4391 if (netdev_uc_count(netdev) > igb_available_rars(adapter))
4392 return -ENOMEM;
4393 if (!netdev_uc_empty(netdev)) {
4394#ifdef NETDEV_HW_ADDR_T_UNICAST
4395 struct netdev_hw_addr *ha;
4396#else
4397 struct dev_mc_list *ha;
4398#endif
4399 netdev_for_each_uc_addr(ha, netdev) {
4400#ifdef NETDEV_HW_ADDR_T_UNICAST
4401 igb_del_mac_filter(adapter, ha->addr, vfn);
4402 igb_add_mac_filter(adapter, ha->addr, vfn);
4403#else
4404 igb_del_mac_filter(adapter, ha->da_addr, vfn);
4405 igb_add_mac_filter(adapter, ha->da_addr, vfn);
4406#endif
4407 count++;
4408 }
4409 }
4410 return count;
4411}
4412
4413#endif /* HAVE_SET_RX_MODE */
4414/**
4415 * igb_set_rx_mode - Secondary Unicast, Multicast and Promiscuous mode set
4416 * @netdev: network interface device structure
4417 *
4418 * The set_rx_mode entry point is called whenever the unicast or multicast
4419 * address lists or the network interface flags are updated. This routine is
4420 * responsible for configuring the hardware for proper unicast, multicast,
4421 * promiscuous mode, and all-multi behavior.
4422 **/
4423static void igb_set_rx_mode(struct net_device *netdev)
4424{
4425 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
4426 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4427 unsigned int vfn = adapter->vfs_allocated_count;
4428 u32 rctl, vmolr = 0;
4429 int count;
4430
4431 /* Check for Promiscuous and All Multicast modes */
4432 rctl = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RCTL);
4433
4434 /* clear the effected bits */
4435 rctl &= ~(E1000_RCTL_UPE | E1000_RCTL_MPE | E1000_RCTL_VFE);
4436
4437 if (netdev->flags & IFF_PROMISC) {
4438 rctl |= (E1000_RCTL_UPE | E1000_RCTL_MPE);
4439 vmolr |= (E1000_VMOLR_ROPE | E1000_VMOLR_MPME);
4440 /* retain VLAN HW filtering if in VT mode */
4441 if (adapter->vfs_allocated_count || adapter->vmdq_pools)
4442 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_VFE;
4443 } else {
4444 if (netdev->flags & IFF_ALLMULTI) {
4445 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_MPE;
4446 vmolr |= E1000_VMOLR_MPME;
4447 } else {
4448 /*
4449 * Write addresses to the MTA, if the attempt fails
4450 * then we should just turn on promiscuous mode so
4451 * that we can at least receive multicast traffic
4452 */
4453 count = igb_write_mc_addr_list(netdev);
4454 if (count < 0) {
4455 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_MPE;
4456 vmolr |= E1000_VMOLR_MPME;
4457 } else if (count) {
4458 vmolr |= E1000_VMOLR_ROMPE;
4459 }
4460 }
4461#ifdef HAVE_SET_RX_MODE
4462 /*
4463 * Write addresses to available RAR registers, if there is not
4464 * sufficient space to store all the addresses then enable
4465 * unicast promiscuous mode
4466 */
4467 count = igb_write_uc_addr_list(netdev);
4468 if (count < 0) {
4469 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_UPE;
4470 vmolr |= E1000_VMOLR_ROPE;
4471 }
4472#endif /* HAVE_SET_RX_MODE */
4473 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_VFE;
4474 }
4475 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RCTL, rctl);
4476
4477 /*
4478 * In order to support SR-IOV and eventually VMDq it is necessary to set
4479 * the VMOLR to enable the appropriate modes. Without this workaround
4480 * we will have issues with VLAN tag stripping not being done for frames
4481 * that are only arriving because we are the default pool
4482 */
4483 if (hw->mac.type < e1000_82576)
4484 return;
4485
4486 vmolr |= E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_VMOLR(vfn)) &
4487 ~(E1000_VMOLR_ROPE | E1000_VMOLR_MPME | E1000_VMOLR_ROMPE);
4488 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_VMOLR(vfn), vmolr);
4489 igb_restore_vf_multicasts(adapter);
4490}
4491
4492static void igb_check_wvbr(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
4493{
4494 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4495 u32 wvbr = 0;
4496
4497 switch (hw->mac.type) {
4498 case e1000_82576:
4499 case e1000_i350:
4500 if (!(wvbr = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_WVBR)))
4501 return;
4502 break;
4503 default:
4504 break;
4505 }
4506
4507 adapter->wvbr |= wvbr;
4508}
4509
4510#define IGB_STAGGERED_QUEUE_OFFSET 8
4511
4512static void igb_spoof_check(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
4513{
4514 int j;
4515
4516 if (!adapter->wvbr)
4517 return;
4518
4519 switch (adapter->hw.mac.type) {
4520 case e1000_82576:
4521 for (j = 0; j < adapter->vfs_allocated_count; j++) {
4522 if (adapter->wvbr & (1 << j) ||
4523 adapter->wvbr & (1 << (j + IGB_STAGGERED_QUEUE_OFFSET))) {
4524 DPRINTK(DRV, WARNING,
4525 "Spoof event(s) detected on VF %d\n", j);
4526 adapter->wvbr &=
4527 ~((1 << j) |
4528 (1 << (j + IGB_STAGGERED_QUEUE_OFFSET)));
4529 }
4530 }
4531 break;
4532 case e1000_i350:
4533 for (j = 0; j < adapter->vfs_allocated_count; j++) {
4534 if (adapter->wvbr & (1 << j)) {
4535 DPRINTK(DRV, WARNING,
4536 "Spoof event(s) detected on VF %d\n", j);
4537 adapter->wvbr &= ~(1 << j);
4538 }
4539 }
4540 break;
4541 default:
4542 break;
4543 }
4544}
4545
4546/* Need to wait a few seconds after link up to get diagnostic information from
4547 * the phy */
4548#ifdef HAVE_TIMER_SETUP
4549static void igb_update_phy_info(struct timer_list *t)
4550{
4551 struct igb_adapter *adapter = from_timer(adapter, t, phy_info_timer);
4552#else
4553static void igb_update_phy_info(unsigned long data)
4554{
4555 struct igb_adapter *adapter = (struct igb_adapter *) data;
4556#endif
4557 e1000_get_phy_info(&adapter->hw);
4558}
4559
4560/**
4561 * igb_has_link - check shared code for link and determine up/down
4562 * @adapter: pointer to driver private info
4563 **/
4564bool igb_has_link(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
4565{
4566 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4567 bool link_active = FALSE;
4568
4569 /* get_link_status is set on LSC (link status) interrupt or
4570 * rx sequence error interrupt. get_link_status will stay
4571 * false until the e1000_check_for_link establishes link
4572 * for copper adapters ONLY
4573 */
4574 switch (hw->phy.media_type) {
4575 case e1000_media_type_copper:
4576 if (!hw->mac.get_link_status)
4577 return true;
4578 case e1000_media_type_internal_serdes:
4579 e1000_check_for_link(hw);
4580 link_active = !hw->mac.get_link_status;
4581 break;
4582 case e1000_media_type_unknown:
4583 default:
4584 break;
4585 }
4586
4587 if (((hw->mac.type == e1000_i210) ||
4588 (hw->mac.type == e1000_i211)) &&
4589 (hw->phy.id == I210_I_PHY_ID)) {
4590 if (!netif_carrier_ok(adapter->netdev)) {
4591 adapter->flags &= ~IGB_FLAG_NEED_LINK_UPDATE;
4592 } else if (!(adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_NEED_LINK_UPDATE)) {
4593 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_NEED_LINK_UPDATE;
4594 adapter->link_check_timeout = jiffies;
4595 }
4596 }
4597
4598 return link_active;
4599}
4600
4601/**
4602 * igb_watchdog - Timer Call-back
4603 * @data: pointer to adapter cast into an unsigned long
4604 **/
4605#ifdef HAVE_TIMER_SETUP
4606static void igb_watchdog(struct timer_list *t)
4607{
4608 struct igb_adapter *adapter = from_timer(adapter, t, watchdog_timer);
4609#else
4610static void igb_watchdog(unsigned long data)
4611{
4612 struct igb_adapter *adapter = (struct igb_adapter *)data;
4613#endif
4614 /* Do the rest outside of interrupt context */
4615 schedule_work(&adapter->watchdog_task);
4616}
4617
4618static void igb_watchdog_task(struct work_struct *work)
4619{
4620 struct igb_adapter *adapter = container_of(work,
4621 struct igb_adapter,
4622 watchdog_task);
4623 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4624 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
4625 u32 link;
4626 int i;
4627 u32 thstat, ctrl_ext;
4628 u32 connsw;
4629
4630 link = igb_has_link(adapter);
4631 /* Force link down if we have fiber to swap to */
4632 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_MAS_ENABLE) {
4633 if (hw->phy.media_type == e1000_media_type_copper) {
4634 connsw = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CONNSW);
4635 if (!(connsw & E1000_CONNSW_AUTOSENSE_EN))
4636 link = 0;
4637 }
4638 }
4639
4640 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_NEED_LINK_UPDATE) {
4641 if (time_after(jiffies, (adapter->link_check_timeout + HZ)))
4642 adapter->flags &= ~IGB_FLAG_NEED_LINK_UPDATE;
4643 else
4644 link = FALSE;
4645 }
4646
4647 if (link) {
4648 /* Perform a reset if the media type changed. */
4649 if (hw->dev_spec._82575.media_changed) {
4650 hw->dev_spec._82575.media_changed = false;
4651 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_MEDIA_RESET;
4652 igb_reset(adapter);
4653 }
4654
4655 /* Cancel scheduled suspend requests. */
4656 pm_runtime_resume(netdev->dev.parent);
4657
4658 if (!netif_carrier_ok(netdev)) {
4659 u32 ctrl;
4660 e1000_get_speed_and_duplex(hw,
4661 &adapter->link_speed,
4662 &adapter->link_duplex);
4663
4664 ctrl = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL);
4665 /* Links status message must follow this format */
4666 printk(KERN_INFO "igb: %s NIC Link is Up %d Mbps %s, "
4667 "Flow Control: %s\n",
4668 netdev->name,
4669 adapter->link_speed,
4670 adapter->link_duplex == FULL_DUPLEX ?
4671 "Full Duplex" : "Half Duplex",
4672 ((ctrl & E1000_CTRL_TFCE) &&
4673 (ctrl & E1000_CTRL_RFCE)) ? "RX/TX":
4674 ((ctrl & E1000_CTRL_RFCE) ? "RX" :
4675 ((ctrl & E1000_CTRL_TFCE) ? "TX" : "None")));
4676 /* adjust timeout factor according to speed/duplex */
4677 adapter->tx_timeout_factor = 1;
4678 switch (adapter->link_speed) {
4679 case SPEED_10:
4680 adapter->tx_timeout_factor = 14;
4681 break;
4682 case SPEED_100:
4683 /* maybe add some timeout factor ? */
4684 break;
4685 default:
4686 break;
4687 }
4688
4689 netif_carrier_on(netdev);
4690 netif_tx_wake_all_queues(netdev);
4691
4692 igb_ping_all_vfs(adapter);
4693#ifdef IFLA_VF_MAX
4694 igb_check_vf_rate_limit(adapter);
4695#endif /* IFLA_VF_MAX */
4696
4697 /* link state has changed, schedule phy info update */
4698 if (!test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state))
4699 mod_timer(&adapter->phy_info_timer,
4700 round_jiffies(jiffies + 2 * HZ));
4701 }
4702 } else {
4703 if (netif_carrier_ok(netdev)) {
4704 adapter->link_speed = 0;
4705 adapter->link_duplex = 0;
4706 /* check for thermal sensor event on i350 */
4707 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_i350) {
4708 thstat = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_THSTAT);
4709 ctrl_ext = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL_EXT);
4710 if ((hw->phy.media_type ==
4711 e1000_media_type_copper) &&
4712 !(ctrl_ext &
4713 E1000_CTRL_EXT_LINK_MODE_SGMII)) {
4714 if (thstat & E1000_THSTAT_PWR_DOWN) {
4715 printk(KERN_ERR "igb: %s The "
4716 "network adapter was stopped "
4717 "because it overheated.\n",
4718 netdev->name);
4719 }
4720 if (thstat & E1000_THSTAT_LINK_THROTTLE) {
4721 printk(KERN_INFO
4722 "igb: %s The network "
4723 "adapter supported "
4724 "link speed "
4725 "was downshifted "
4726 "because it "
4727 "overheated.\n",
4728 netdev->name);
4729 }
4730 }
4731 }
4732
4733 /* Links status message must follow this format */
4734 printk(KERN_INFO "igb: %s NIC Link is Down\n",
4735 netdev->name);
4736 netif_carrier_off(netdev);
4737 netif_tx_stop_all_queues(netdev);
4738
4739 igb_ping_all_vfs(adapter);
4740
4741 /* link state has changed, schedule phy info update */
4742 if (!test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state))
4743 mod_timer(&adapter->phy_info_timer,
4744 round_jiffies(jiffies + 2 * HZ));
4745 /* link is down, time to check for alternate media */
4746 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_MAS_ENABLE) {
4747 igb_check_swap_media(adapter);
4748 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_MEDIA_RESET) {
4749 schedule_work(&adapter->reset_task);
4750 /* return immediately */
4751 return;
4752 }
4753 }
4754 pm_schedule_suspend(netdev->dev.parent,
4755 MSEC_PER_SEC * 5);
4756
4757 /* also check for alternate media here */
4758 } else if (!netif_carrier_ok(netdev) &&
4759 (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_MAS_ENABLE)) {
4760 hw->mac.ops.power_up_serdes(hw);
4761 igb_check_swap_media(adapter);
4762 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_MEDIA_RESET) {
4763 schedule_work(&adapter->reset_task);
4764 /* return immediately */
4765 return;
4766 }
4767 }
4768 }
4769
4770 igb_update_stats(adapter);
4771
4772 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++) {
4773 struct igb_ring *tx_ring = adapter->tx_ring[i];
4774 if (!netif_carrier_ok(netdev)) {
4775 /* We've lost link, so the controller stops DMA,
4776 * but we've got queued Tx work that's never going
4777 * to get done, so reset controller to flush Tx.
4778 * (Do the reset outside of interrupt context). */
4779 if (igb_desc_unused(tx_ring) + 1 < tx_ring->count) {
4780 adapter->tx_timeout_count++;
4781 schedule_work(&adapter->reset_task);
4782 /* return immediately since reset is imminent */
4783 return;
4784 }
4785 }
4786
4787 /* Force detection of hung controller every watchdog period */
4788 set_bit(IGB_RING_FLAG_TX_DETECT_HANG, &tx_ring->flags);
4789 }
4790
4791 /* Cause software interrupt to ensure rx ring is cleaned */
4792 if (adapter->msix_entries) {
4793 u32 eics = 0;
4794 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_q_vectors; i++)
4795 eics |= adapter->q_vector[i]->eims_value;
4796 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_EICS, eics);
4797 } else {
4798 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_ICS, E1000_ICS_RXDMT0);
4799 }
4800
4801 igb_spoof_check(adapter);
4802
4803 /* Reset the timer */
4804 if (!test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state)) {
4805 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_NEED_LINK_UPDATE)
4806 mod_timer(&adapter->watchdog_timer,
4807 round_jiffies(jiffies + HZ));
4808 else
4809 mod_timer(&adapter->watchdog_timer,
4810 round_jiffies(jiffies + 2 * HZ));
4811 }
4812}
4813
4814static void igb_dma_err_task(struct work_struct *work)
4815{
4816 struct igb_adapter *adapter = container_of(work,
4817 struct igb_adapter,
4818 dma_err_task);
4819 int vf;
4820 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4821 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
4822 u32 hgptc;
4823 u32 ciaa, ciad;
4824
4825 hgptc = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_HGPTC);
4826 if (hgptc) /* If incrementing then no need for the check below */
4827 goto dma_timer_reset;
4828 /*
4829 * Check to see if a bad DMA write target from an errant or
4830 * malicious VF has caused a PCIe error. If so then we can
4831 * issue a VFLR to the offending VF(s) and then resume without
4832 * requesting a full slot reset.
4833 */
4834
4835 for (vf = 0; vf < adapter->vfs_allocated_count; vf++) {
4836 ciaa = (vf << 16) | 0x80000000;
4837 /* 32 bit read so align, we really want status at offset 6 */
4838 ciaa |= PCI_COMMAND;
4839 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CIAA, ciaa);
4840 ciad = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CIAD);
4841 ciaa &= 0x7FFFFFFF;
4842 /* disable debug mode asap after reading data */
4843 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CIAA, ciaa);
4844 /* Get the upper 16 bits which will be the PCI status reg */
4845 ciad >>= 16;
4846 if (ciad & (PCI_STATUS_REC_MASTER_ABORT |
4847 PCI_STATUS_REC_TARGET_ABORT |
4848 PCI_STATUS_SIG_SYSTEM_ERROR)) {
4849 netdev_err(netdev, "VF %d suffered error\n", vf);
4850 /* Issue VFLR */
4851 ciaa = (vf << 16) | 0x80000000;
4852 ciaa |= 0xA8;
4853 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CIAA, ciaa);
4854 ciad = 0x00008000; /* VFLR */
4855 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CIAD, ciad);
4856 ciaa &= 0x7FFFFFFF;
4857 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CIAA, ciaa);
4858 }
4859 }
4860dma_timer_reset:
4861 /* Reset the timer */
4862 if (!test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state))
4863 mod_timer(&adapter->dma_err_timer,
4864 round_jiffies(jiffies + HZ / 10));
4865}
4866
4867/**
4868 * igb_dma_err_timer - Timer Call-back
4869 * @data: pointer to adapter cast into an unsigned long
4870 **/
4871#ifdef HAVE_TIMER_SETUP
4872static void igb_dma_err_timer(struct timer_list *t)
4873{
4874 struct igb_adapter *adapter = from_timer(adapter, t, dma_err_timer);
4875#else
4876static void igb_dma_err_timer(unsigned long data)
4877{
4878 struct igb_adapter *adapter = (struct igb_adapter *)data;
4879#endif
4880 /* Do the rest outside of interrupt context */
4881 schedule_work(&adapter->dma_err_task);
4882}
4883
4884enum latency_range {
4885 lowest_latency = 0,
4886 low_latency = 1,
4887 bulk_latency = 2,
4888 latency_invalid = 255
4889};
4890
4891/**
4892 * igb_update_ring_itr - update the dynamic ITR value based on packet size
4893 *
4894 * Stores a new ITR value based on strictly on packet size. This
4895 * algorithm is less sophisticated than that used in igb_update_itr,
4896 * due to the difficulty of synchronizing statistics across multiple
4897 * receive rings. The divisors and thresholds used by this function
4898 * were determined based on theoretical maximum wire speed and testing
4899 * data, in order to minimize response time while increasing bulk
4900 * throughput.
4901 * This functionality is controlled by the InterruptThrottleRate module
4902 * parameter (see igb_param.c)
4903 * NOTE: This function is called only when operating in a multiqueue
4904 * receive environment.
4905 * @q_vector: pointer to q_vector
4906 **/
4907static void igb_update_ring_itr(struct igb_q_vector *q_vector)
4908{
4909 int new_val = q_vector->itr_val;
4910 int avg_wire_size = 0;
4911 struct igb_adapter *adapter = q_vector->adapter;
4912 unsigned int packets;
4913
4914 /* For non-gigabit speeds, just fix the interrupt rate at 4000
4915 * ints/sec - ITR timer value of 120 ticks.
4916 */
4917 switch (adapter->link_speed) {
4918 case SPEED_10:
4919 case SPEED_100:
4920 new_val = IGB_4K_ITR;
4921 goto set_itr_val;
4922 default:
4923 break;
4924 }
4925
4926 packets = q_vector->rx.total_packets;
4927 if (packets)
4928 avg_wire_size = q_vector->rx.total_bytes / packets;
4929
4930 packets = q_vector->tx.total_packets;
4931 if (packets)
4932 avg_wire_size = max_t(u32, avg_wire_size,
4933 q_vector->tx.total_bytes / packets);
4934
4935 /* if avg_wire_size isn't set no work was done */
4936 if (!avg_wire_size)
4937 goto clear_counts;
4938
4939 /* Add 24 bytes to size to account for CRC, preamble, and gap */
4940 avg_wire_size += 24;
4941
4942 /* Don't starve jumbo frames */
4943 avg_wire_size = min(avg_wire_size, 3000);
4944
4945 /* Give a little boost to mid-size frames */
4946 if ((avg_wire_size > 300) && (avg_wire_size < 1200))
4947 new_val = avg_wire_size / 3;
4948 else
4949 new_val = avg_wire_size / 2;
4950
4951 /* conservative mode (itr 3) eliminates the lowest_latency setting */
4952 if (new_val < IGB_20K_ITR &&
4953 ((q_vector->rx.ring && adapter->rx_itr_setting == 3) ||
4954 (!q_vector->rx.ring && adapter->tx_itr_setting == 3)))
4955 new_val = IGB_20K_ITR;
4956
4957set_itr_val:
4958 if (new_val != q_vector->itr_val) {
4959 q_vector->itr_val = new_val;
4960 q_vector->set_itr = 1;
4961 }
4962clear_counts:
4963 q_vector->rx.total_bytes = 0;
4964 q_vector->rx.total_packets = 0;
4965 q_vector->tx.total_bytes = 0;
4966 q_vector->tx.total_packets = 0;
4967}
4968
4969/**
4970 * igb_update_itr - update the dynamic ITR value based on statistics
4971 * Stores a new ITR value based on packets and byte
4972 * counts during the last interrupt. The advantage of per interrupt
4973 * computation is faster updates and more accurate ITR for the current
4974 * traffic pattern. Constants in this function were computed
4975 * based on theoretical maximum wire speed and thresholds were set based
4976 * on testing data as well as attempting to minimize response time
4977 * while increasing bulk throughput.
4978 * this functionality is controlled by the InterruptThrottleRate module
4979 * parameter (see igb_param.c)
4980 * NOTE: These calculations are only valid when operating in a single-
4981 * queue environment.
4982 * @q_vector: pointer to q_vector
4983 * @ring_container: ring info to update the itr for
4984 **/
4985static void igb_update_itr(struct igb_q_vector *q_vector,
4986 struct igb_ring_container *ring_container)
4987{
4988 unsigned int packets = ring_container->total_packets;
4989 unsigned int bytes = ring_container->total_bytes;
4990 u8 itrval = ring_container->itr;
4991
4992 /* no packets, exit with status unchanged */
4993 if (packets == 0)
4994 return;
4995
4996 switch (itrval) {
4997 case lowest_latency:
4998 /* handle TSO and jumbo frames */
4999 if (bytes/packets > 8000)
5000 itrval = bulk_latency;
5001 else if ((packets < 5) && (bytes > 512))
5002 itrval = low_latency;
5003 break;
5004 case low_latency: /* 50 usec aka 20000 ints/s */
5005 if (bytes > 10000) {
5006 /* this if handles the TSO accounting */
5007 if (bytes/packets > 8000) {
5008 itrval = bulk_latency;
5009 } else if ((packets < 10) || ((bytes/packets) > 1200)) {
5010 itrval = bulk_latency;
5011 } else if (packets > 35) {
5012 itrval = lowest_latency;
5013 }
5014 } else if (bytes/packets > 2000) {
5015 itrval = bulk_latency;
5016 } else if (packets <= 2 && bytes < 512) {
5017 itrval = lowest_latency;
5018 }
5019 break;
5020 case bulk_latency: /* 250 usec aka 4000 ints/s */
5021 if (bytes > 25000) {
5022 if (packets > 35)
5023 itrval = low_latency;
5024 } else if (bytes < 1500) {
5025 itrval = low_latency;
5026 }
5027 break;
5028 }
5029
5030 /* clear work counters since we have the values we need */
5031 ring_container->total_bytes = 0;
5032 ring_container->total_packets = 0;
5033
5034 /* write updated itr to ring container */
5035 ring_container->itr = itrval;
5036}
5037
5038static void igb_set_itr(struct igb_q_vector *q_vector)
5039{
5040 struct igb_adapter *adapter = q_vector->adapter;
5041 u32 new_itr = q_vector->itr_val;
5042 u8 current_itr = 0;
5043
5044 /* for non-gigabit speeds, just fix the interrupt rate at 4000 */
5045 switch (adapter->link_speed) {
5046 case SPEED_10:
5047 case SPEED_100:
5048 current_itr = 0;
5049 new_itr = IGB_4K_ITR;
5050 goto set_itr_now;
5051 default:
5052 break;
5053 }
5054
5055 igb_update_itr(q_vector, &q_vector->tx);
5056 igb_update_itr(q_vector, &q_vector->rx);
5057
5058 current_itr = max(q_vector->rx.itr, q_vector->tx.itr);
5059
5060 /* conservative mode (itr 3) eliminates the lowest_latency setting */
5061 if (current_itr == lowest_latency &&
5062 ((q_vector->rx.ring && adapter->rx_itr_setting == 3) ||
5063 (!q_vector->rx.ring && adapter->tx_itr_setting == 3)))
5064 current_itr = low_latency;
5065
5066 switch (current_itr) {
5067 /* counts and packets in update_itr are dependent on these numbers */
5068 case lowest_latency:
5069 new_itr = IGB_70K_ITR; /* 70,000 ints/sec */
5070 break;
5071 case low_latency:
5072 new_itr = IGB_20K_ITR; /* 20,000 ints/sec */
5073 break;
5074 case bulk_latency:
5075 new_itr = IGB_4K_ITR; /* 4,000 ints/sec */
5076 break;
5077 default:
5078 break;
5079 }
5080
5081set_itr_now:
5082 if (new_itr != q_vector->itr_val) {
5083 /* this attempts to bias the interrupt rate towards Bulk
5084 * by adding intermediate steps when interrupt rate is
5085 * increasing */
5086 new_itr = new_itr > q_vector->itr_val ?
5087 max((new_itr * q_vector->itr_val) /
5088 (new_itr + (q_vector->itr_val >> 2)),
5089 new_itr) :
5090 new_itr;
5091 /* Don't write the value here; it resets the adapter's
5092 * internal timer, and causes us to delay far longer than
5093 * we should between interrupts. Instead, we write the ITR
5094 * value at the beginning of the next interrupt so the timing
5095 * ends up being correct.
5096 */
5097 q_vector->itr_val = new_itr;
5098 q_vector->set_itr = 1;
5099 }
5100}
5101
5102void igb_tx_ctxtdesc(struct igb_ring *tx_ring, u32 vlan_macip_lens,
5103 u32 type_tucmd, u32 mss_l4len_idx)
5104{
5105 struct e1000_adv_tx_context_desc *context_desc;
5106 u16 i = tx_ring->next_to_use;
5107
5108 context_desc = IGB_TX_CTXTDESC(tx_ring, i);
5109
5110 i++;
5111 tx_ring->next_to_use = (i < tx_ring->count) ? i : 0;
5112
5113 /* set bits to identify this as an advanced context descriptor */
5114 type_tucmd |= E1000_TXD_CMD_DEXT | E1000_ADVTXD_DTYP_CTXT;
5115
5116 /* For 82575, context index must be unique per ring. */
5117 if (test_bit(IGB_RING_FLAG_TX_CTX_IDX, &tx_ring->flags))
5118 mss_l4len_idx |= tx_ring->reg_idx << 4;
5119
5120 context_desc->vlan_macip_lens = cpu_to_le32(vlan_macip_lens);
5121 context_desc->seqnum_seed = 0;
5122 context_desc->type_tucmd_mlhl = cpu_to_le32(type_tucmd);
5123 context_desc->mss_l4len_idx = cpu_to_le32(mss_l4len_idx);
5124}
5125
5126static int igb_tso(struct igb_ring *tx_ring,
5127 struct igb_tx_buffer *first,
5128 u8 *hdr_len)
5129{
5130#ifdef NETIF_F_TSO
5131 struct sk_buff *skb = first->skb;
5132 u32 vlan_macip_lens, type_tucmd;
5133 u32 mss_l4len_idx, l4len;
5134
5135 if (skb->ip_summed != CHECKSUM_PARTIAL)
5136 return 0;
5137
5138 if (!skb_is_gso(skb))
5139#endif /* NETIF_F_TSO */
5140 return 0;
5141#ifdef NETIF_F_TSO
5142
5143 if (skb_header_cloned(skb)) {
5144 int err = pskb_expand_head(skb, 0, 0, GFP_ATOMIC);
5145 if (err)
5146 return err;
5147 }
5148
5149 /* ADV DTYP TUCMD MKRLOC/ISCSIHEDLEN */
5150 type_tucmd = E1000_ADVTXD_TUCMD_L4T_TCP;
5151
5152 if (first->protocol == __constant_htons(ETH_P_IP)) {
5153 struct iphdr *iph = ip_hdr(skb);
5154 iph->tot_len = 0;
5155 iph->check = 0;
5156 tcp_hdr(skb)->check = ~csum_tcpudp_magic(iph->saddr,
5157 iph->daddr, 0,
5158 IPPROTO_TCP,
5159 0);
5160 type_tucmd |= E1000_ADVTXD_TUCMD_IPV4;
5161 first->tx_flags |= IGB_TX_FLAGS_TSO |
5162 IGB_TX_FLAGS_CSUM |
5163 IGB_TX_FLAGS_IPV4;
5164#ifdef NETIF_F_TSO6
5165 } else if (skb_is_gso_v6(skb)) {
5166 ipv6_hdr(skb)->payload_len = 0;
5167 tcp_hdr(skb)->check = ~csum_ipv6_magic(&ipv6_hdr(skb)->saddr,
5168 &ipv6_hdr(skb)->daddr,
5169 0, IPPROTO_TCP, 0);
5170 first->tx_flags |= IGB_TX_FLAGS_TSO |
5171 IGB_TX_FLAGS_CSUM;
5172#endif
5173 }
5174
5175 /* compute header lengths */
5176 l4len = tcp_hdrlen(skb);
5177 *hdr_len = skb_transport_offset(skb) + l4len;
5178
5179 /* update gso size and bytecount with header size */
5180 first->gso_segs = skb_shinfo(skb)->gso_segs;
5181 first->bytecount += (first->gso_segs - 1) * *hdr_len;
5182
5183 /* MSS L4LEN IDX */
5184 mss_l4len_idx = l4len << E1000_ADVTXD_L4LEN_SHIFT;
5185 mss_l4len_idx |= skb_shinfo(skb)->gso_size << E1000_ADVTXD_MSS_SHIFT;
5186
5187 /* VLAN MACLEN IPLEN */
5188 vlan_macip_lens = skb_network_header_len(skb);
5189 vlan_macip_lens |= skb_network_offset(skb) << E1000_ADVTXD_MACLEN_SHIFT;
5190 vlan_macip_lens |= first->tx_flags & IGB_TX_FLAGS_VLAN_MASK;
5191
5192 igb_tx_ctxtdesc(tx_ring, vlan_macip_lens, type_tucmd, mss_l4len_idx);
5193
5194 return 1;
5195#endif /* NETIF_F_TSO */
5196}
5197
5198static void igb_tx_csum(struct igb_ring *tx_ring, struct igb_tx_buffer *first)
5199{
5200 struct sk_buff *skb = first->skb;
5201 u32 vlan_macip_lens = 0;
5202 u32 mss_l4len_idx = 0;
5203 u32 type_tucmd = 0;
5204
5205 if (skb->ip_summed != CHECKSUM_PARTIAL) {
5206 if (!(first->tx_flags & IGB_TX_FLAGS_VLAN))
5207 return;
5208 } else {
5209 u8 nexthdr = 0;
5210 switch (first->protocol) {
5211 case __constant_htons(ETH_P_IP):
5212 vlan_macip_lens |= skb_network_header_len(skb);
5213 type_tucmd |= E1000_ADVTXD_TUCMD_IPV4;
5214 nexthdr = ip_hdr(skb)->protocol;
5215 break;
5216#ifdef NETIF_F_IPV6_CSUM
5217 case __constant_htons(ETH_P_IPV6):
5218 vlan_macip_lens |= skb_network_header_len(skb);
5219 nexthdr = ipv6_hdr(skb)->nexthdr;
5220 break;
5221#endif
5222 default:
5223 if (unlikely(net_ratelimit())) {
5224 dev_warn(tx_ring->dev,
5225 "partial checksum but proto=%x!\n",
5226 first->protocol);
5227 }
5228 break;
5229 }
5230
5231 switch (nexthdr) {
5232 case IPPROTO_TCP:
5233 type_tucmd |= E1000_ADVTXD_TUCMD_L4T_TCP;
5234 mss_l4len_idx = tcp_hdrlen(skb) <<
5235 E1000_ADVTXD_L4LEN_SHIFT;
5236 break;
5237#ifdef HAVE_SCTP
5238 case IPPROTO_SCTP:
5239 type_tucmd |= E1000_ADVTXD_TUCMD_L4T_SCTP;
5240 mss_l4len_idx = sizeof(struct sctphdr) <<
5241 E1000_ADVTXD_L4LEN_SHIFT;
5242 break;
5243#endif
5244 case IPPROTO_UDP:
5245 mss_l4len_idx = sizeof(struct udphdr) <<
5246 E1000_ADVTXD_L4LEN_SHIFT;
5247 break;
5248 default:
5249 if (unlikely(net_ratelimit())) {
5250 dev_warn(tx_ring->dev,
5251 "partial checksum but l4 proto=%x!\n",
5252 nexthdr);
5253 }
5254 break;
5255 }
5256
5257 /* update TX checksum flag */
5258 first->tx_flags |= IGB_TX_FLAGS_CSUM;
5259 }
5260
5261 vlan_macip_lens |= skb_network_offset(skb) << E1000_ADVTXD_MACLEN_SHIFT;
5262 vlan_macip_lens |= first->tx_flags & IGB_TX_FLAGS_VLAN_MASK;
5263
5264 igb_tx_ctxtdesc(tx_ring, vlan_macip_lens, type_tucmd, mss_l4len_idx);
5265}
5266
5267#define IGB_SET_FLAG(_input, _flag, _result) \
5268 ((_flag <= _result) ? \
5269 ((u32)(_input & _flag) * (_result / _flag)) : \
5270 ((u32)(_input & _flag) / (_flag / _result)))
5271
5272static u32 igb_tx_cmd_type(struct sk_buff *skb, u32 tx_flags)
5273{
5274 /* set type for advanced descriptor with frame checksum insertion */
5275 u32 cmd_type = E1000_ADVTXD_DTYP_DATA |
5276 E1000_ADVTXD_DCMD_DEXT |
5277 E1000_ADVTXD_DCMD_IFCS;
5278
5279 /* set HW vlan bit if vlan is present */
5280 cmd_type |= IGB_SET_FLAG(tx_flags, IGB_TX_FLAGS_VLAN,
5281 (E1000_ADVTXD_DCMD_VLE));
5282
5283 /* set segmentation bits for TSO */
5284 cmd_type |= IGB_SET_FLAG(tx_flags, IGB_TX_FLAGS_TSO,
5285 (E1000_ADVTXD_DCMD_TSE));
5286
5287 /* set timestamp bit if present */
5288 cmd_type |= IGB_SET_FLAG(tx_flags, IGB_TX_FLAGS_TSTAMP,
5289 (E1000_ADVTXD_MAC_TSTAMP));
5290
5291 return cmd_type;
5292}
5293
5294static void igb_tx_olinfo_status(struct igb_ring *tx_ring,
5295 union e1000_adv_tx_desc *tx_desc,
5296 u32 tx_flags, unsigned int paylen)
5297{
5298 u32 olinfo_status = paylen << E1000_ADVTXD_PAYLEN_SHIFT;
5299
5300 /* 82575 requires a unique index per ring */
5301 if (test_bit(IGB_RING_FLAG_TX_CTX_IDX, &tx_ring->flags))
5302 olinfo_status |= tx_ring->reg_idx << 4;
5303
5304 /* insert L4 checksum */
5305 olinfo_status |= IGB_SET_FLAG(tx_flags,
5306 IGB_TX_FLAGS_CSUM,
5307 (E1000_TXD_POPTS_TXSM << 8));
5308
5309 /* insert IPv4 checksum */
5310 olinfo_status |= IGB_SET_FLAG(tx_flags,
5311 IGB_TX_FLAGS_IPV4,
5312 (E1000_TXD_POPTS_IXSM << 8));
5313
5314 tx_desc->read.olinfo_status = cpu_to_le32(olinfo_status);
5315}
5316
5317static void igb_tx_map(struct igb_ring *tx_ring,
5318 struct igb_tx_buffer *first,
5319 const u8 hdr_len)
5320{
5321 struct sk_buff *skb = first->skb;
5322 struct igb_tx_buffer *tx_buffer;
5323 union e1000_adv_tx_desc *tx_desc;
5324 struct skb_frag_struct *frag;
5325 dma_addr_t dma;
5326 unsigned int data_len, size;
5327 u32 tx_flags = first->tx_flags;
5328 u32 cmd_type = igb_tx_cmd_type(skb, tx_flags);
5329 u16 i = tx_ring->next_to_use;
5330
5331 tx_desc = IGB_TX_DESC(tx_ring, i);
5332
5333 igb_tx_olinfo_status(tx_ring, tx_desc, tx_flags, skb->len - hdr_len);
5334
5335 size = skb_headlen(skb);
5336 data_len = skb->data_len;
5337
5338 dma = dma_map_single(tx_ring->dev, skb->data, size, DMA_TO_DEVICE);
5339
5340 tx_buffer = first;
5341
5342 for (frag = &skb_shinfo(skb)->frags[0];; frag++) {
5343 if (dma_mapping_error(tx_ring->dev, dma))
5344 goto dma_error;
5345
5346 /* record length, and DMA address */
5347 dma_unmap_len_set(tx_buffer, len, size);
5348 dma_unmap_addr_set(tx_buffer, dma, dma);
5349
5350 tx_desc->read.buffer_addr = cpu_to_le64(dma);
5351
5352 while (unlikely(size > IGB_MAX_DATA_PER_TXD)) {
5353 tx_desc->read.cmd_type_len =
5354 cpu_to_le32(cmd_type ^ IGB_MAX_DATA_PER_TXD);
5355
5356 i++;
5357 tx_desc++;
5358 if (i == tx_ring->count) {
5359 tx_desc = IGB_TX_DESC(tx_ring, 0);
5360 i = 0;
5361 }
5362 tx_desc->read.olinfo_status = 0;
5363
5364 dma += IGB_MAX_DATA_PER_TXD;
5365 size -= IGB_MAX_DATA_PER_TXD;
5366
5367 tx_desc->read.buffer_addr = cpu_to_le64(dma);
5368 }
5369
5370 if (likely(!data_len))
5371 break;
5372
5373 tx_desc->read.cmd_type_len = cpu_to_le32(cmd_type ^ size);
5374
5375 i++;
5376 tx_desc++;
5377 if (i == tx_ring->count) {
5378 tx_desc = IGB_TX_DESC(tx_ring, 0);
5379 i = 0;
5380 }
5381 tx_desc->read.olinfo_status = 0;
5382
5383 size = skb_frag_size(frag);
5384 data_len -= size;
5385
5386 dma = skb_frag_dma_map(tx_ring->dev, frag, 0,
5387 size, DMA_TO_DEVICE);
5388
5389 tx_buffer = &tx_ring->tx_buffer_info[i];
5390 }
5391
5392 /* write last descriptor with RS and EOP bits */
5393 cmd_type |= size | IGB_TXD_DCMD;
5394 tx_desc->read.cmd_type_len = cpu_to_le32(cmd_type);
5395
5396 netdev_tx_sent_queue(txring_txq(tx_ring), first->bytecount);
5397 /* set the timestamp */
5398 first->time_stamp = jiffies;
5399
5400 /*
5401 * Force memory writes to complete before letting h/w know there
5402 * are new descriptors to fetch. (Only applicable for weak-ordered
5403 * memory model archs, such as IA-64).
5404 *
5405 * We also need this memory barrier to make certain all of the
5406 * status bits have been updated before next_to_watch is written.
5407 */
5408 wmb();
5409
5410 /* set next_to_watch value indicating a packet is present */
5411 first->next_to_watch = tx_desc;
5412
5413 i++;
5414 if (i == tx_ring->count)
5415 i = 0;
5416
5417 tx_ring->next_to_use = i;
5418
5419 writel(i, tx_ring->tail);
5420
5421 /* we need this if more than one processor can write to our tail
5422 * at a time, it syncronizes IO on IA64/Altix systems */
5423 mmiowb();
5424
5425 return;
5426
5427dma_error:
5428 dev_err(tx_ring->dev, "TX DMA map failed\n");
5429
5430 /* clear dma mappings for failed tx_buffer_info map */
5431 for (;;) {
5432 tx_buffer = &tx_ring->tx_buffer_info[i];
5433 igb_unmap_and_free_tx_resource(tx_ring, tx_buffer);
5434 if (tx_buffer == first)
5435 break;
5436 if (i == 0)
5437 i = tx_ring->count;
5438 i--;
5439 }
5440
5441 tx_ring->next_to_use = i;
5442}
5443
5444static int __igb_maybe_stop_tx(struct igb_ring *tx_ring, const u16 size)
5445{
5446 struct net_device *netdev = netdev_ring(tx_ring);
5447
5448 if (netif_is_multiqueue(netdev))
5449 netif_stop_subqueue(netdev, ring_queue_index(tx_ring));
5450 else
5451 netif_stop_queue(netdev);
5452
5453 /* Herbert's original patch had:
5454 * smp_mb__after_netif_stop_queue();
5455 * but since that doesn't exist yet, just open code it. */
5456 smp_mb();
5457
5458 /* We need to check again in a case another CPU has just
5459 * made room available. */
5460 if (igb_desc_unused(tx_ring) < size)
5461 return -EBUSY;
5462
5463 /* A reprieve! */
5464 if (netif_is_multiqueue(netdev))
5465 netif_wake_subqueue(netdev, ring_queue_index(tx_ring));
5466 else
5467 netif_wake_queue(netdev);
5468
5469 tx_ring->tx_stats.restart_queue++;
5470
5471 return 0;
5472}
5473
5474static inline int igb_maybe_stop_tx(struct igb_ring *tx_ring, const u16 size)
5475{
5476 if (igb_desc_unused(tx_ring) >= size)
5477 return 0;
5478 return __igb_maybe_stop_tx(tx_ring, size);
5479}
5480
5481netdev_tx_t igb_xmit_frame_ring(struct sk_buff *skb,
5482 struct igb_ring *tx_ring)
5483{
5484 struct igb_tx_buffer *first;
5485 int tso;
5486 u32 tx_flags = 0;
5487#if PAGE_SIZE > IGB_MAX_DATA_PER_TXD
5488 unsigned short f;
5489#endif
5490 u16 count = TXD_USE_COUNT(skb_headlen(skb));
5491 __be16 protocol = vlan_get_protocol(skb);
5492 u8 hdr_len = 0;
5493
5494 /*
5495 * need: 1 descriptor per page * PAGE_SIZE/IGB_MAX_DATA_PER_TXD,
5496 * + 1 desc for skb_headlen/IGB_MAX_DATA_PER_TXD,
5497 * + 2 desc gap to keep tail from touching head,
5498 * + 1 desc for context descriptor,
5499 * otherwise try next time
5500 */
5501#if PAGE_SIZE > IGB_MAX_DATA_PER_TXD
5502 for (f = 0; f < skb_shinfo(skb)->nr_frags; f++)
5503 count += TXD_USE_COUNT(skb_shinfo(skb)->frags[f].size);
5504#else
5505 count += skb_shinfo(skb)->nr_frags;
5506#endif
5507 if (igb_maybe_stop_tx(tx_ring, count + 3)) {
5508 /* this is a hard error */
5509 return NETDEV_TX_BUSY;
5510 }
5511
5512 /* record the location of the first descriptor for this packet */
5513 first = &tx_ring->tx_buffer_info[tx_ring->next_to_use];
5514 first->skb = skb;
5515 first->bytecount = skb->len;
5516 first->gso_segs = 1;
5517
5518 skb_tx_timestamp(skb);
5519
5520#ifdef HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK
5521 if (unlikely(skb_shinfo(skb)->tx_flags & SKBTX_HW_TSTAMP)) {
5522 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(tx_ring->netdev);
5523 if (!adapter->ptp_tx_skb) {
5524 skb_shinfo(skb)->tx_flags |= SKBTX_IN_PROGRESS;
5525 tx_flags |= IGB_TX_FLAGS_TSTAMP;
5526
5527 adapter->ptp_tx_skb = skb_get(skb);
5528 adapter->ptp_tx_start = jiffies;
5529 if (adapter->hw.mac.type == e1000_82576)
5530 schedule_work(&adapter->ptp_tx_work);
5531 }
5532 }
5533#endif /* HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK */
5534
5535 if (vlan_tx_tag_present(skb)) {
5536 tx_flags |= IGB_TX_FLAGS_VLAN;
5537 tx_flags |= (vlan_tx_tag_get(skb) << IGB_TX_FLAGS_VLAN_SHIFT);
5538 }
5539
5540 /* record initial flags and protocol */
5541 first->tx_flags = tx_flags;
5542 first->protocol = protocol;
5543
5544 tso = igb_tso(tx_ring, first, &hdr_len);
5545 if (tso < 0)
5546 goto out_drop;
5547 else if (!tso)
5548 igb_tx_csum(tx_ring, first);
5549
5550 igb_tx_map(tx_ring, first, hdr_len);
5551
5552#ifndef HAVE_TRANS_START_IN_QUEUE
5553 netdev_ring(tx_ring)->trans_start = jiffies;
5554
5555#endif
5556 /* Make sure there is space in the ring for the next send. */
5557 igb_maybe_stop_tx(tx_ring, DESC_NEEDED);
5558
5559 return NETDEV_TX_OK;
5560
5561out_drop:
5562 igb_unmap_and_free_tx_resource(tx_ring, first);
5563
5564 return NETDEV_TX_OK;
5565}
5566
5567#ifdef HAVE_TX_MQ
5568static inline struct igb_ring *igb_tx_queue_mapping(struct igb_adapter *adapter,
5569 struct sk_buff *skb)
5570{
5571 unsigned int r_idx = skb->queue_mapping;
5572
5573 if (r_idx >= adapter->num_tx_queues)
5574 r_idx = r_idx % adapter->num_tx_queues;
5575
5576 return adapter->tx_ring[r_idx];
5577}
5578#else
5579#define igb_tx_queue_mapping(_adapter, _skb) (_adapter)->tx_ring[0]
5580#endif
5581
5582static netdev_tx_t igb_xmit_frame(struct sk_buff *skb,
5583 struct net_device *netdev)
5584{
5585 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
5586
5587 if (test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state)) {
5588 dev_kfree_skb_any(skb);
5589 return NETDEV_TX_OK;
5590 }
5591
5592 if (skb->len <= 0) {
5593 dev_kfree_skb_any(skb);
5594 return NETDEV_TX_OK;
5595 }
5596
5597 /*
5598 * The minimum packet size with TCTL.PSP set is 17 so pad the skb
5599 * in order to meet this minimum size requirement.
5600 */
5601 if (skb->len < 17) {
5602 if (skb_padto(skb, 17))
5603 return NETDEV_TX_OK;
5604 skb->len = 17;
5605 }
5606
5607 return igb_xmit_frame_ring(skb, igb_tx_queue_mapping(adapter, skb));
5608}
5609
5610/**
5611 * igb_tx_timeout - Respond to a Tx Hang
5612 * @netdev: network interface device structure
5613 **/
5614static void igb_tx_timeout(struct net_device *netdev)
5615{
5616 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
5617 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5618
5619 /* Do the reset outside of interrupt context */
5620 adapter->tx_timeout_count++;
5621
5622 if (hw->mac.type >= e1000_82580)
5623 hw->dev_spec._82575.global_device_reset = true;
5624
5625 schedule_work(&adapter->reset_task);
5626 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_EICS,
5627 (adapter->eims_enable_mask & ~adapter->eims_other));
5628}
5629
5630static void igb_reset_task(struct work_struct *work)
5631{
5632 struct igb_adapter *adapter;
5633 adapter = container_of(work, struct igb_adapter, reset_task);
5634
5635 igb_reinit_locked(adapter);
5636}
5637
5638/**
5639 * igb_get_stats - Get System Network Statistics
5640 * @netdev: network interface device structure
5641 *
5642 * Returns the address of the device statistics structure.
5643 * The statistics are updated here and also from the timer callback.
5644 **/
5645static struct net_device_stats *igb_get_stats(struct net_device *netdev)
5646{
5647 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
5648
5649 if (!test_bit(__IGB_RESETTING, &adapter->state))
5650 igb_update_stats(adapter);
5651
5652#ifdef HAVE_NETDEV_STATS_IN_NETDEV
5653 /* only return the current stats */
5654 return &netdev->stats;
5655#else
5656 /* only return the current stats */
5657 return &adapter->net_stats;
5658#endif /* HAVE_NETDEV_STATS_IN_NETDEV */
5659}
5660
5661/**
5662 * igb_change_mtu - Change the Maximum Transfer Unit
5663 * @netdev: network interface device structure
5664 * @new_mtu: new value for maximum frame size
5665 *
5666 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
5667 **/
5668static int igb_change_mtu(struct net_device *netdev, int new_mtu)
5669{
5670 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
5671 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5672 struct pci_dev *pdev = adapter->pdev;
5673 int max_frame = new_mtu + ETH_HLEN + ETH_FCS_LEN + VLAN_HLEN;
5674
5675 if ((new_mtu < 68) || (max_frame > MAX_JUMBO_FRAME_SIZE)) {
5676 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "Invalid MTU setting\n");
5677 return -EINVAL;
5678 }
5679
5680#define MAX_STD_JUMBO_FRAME_SIZE 9238
5681 if (max_frame > MAX_STD_JUMBO_FRAME_SIZE) {
5682 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "MTU > 9216 not supported.\n");
5683 return -EINVAL;
5684 }
5685
5686 /* adjust max frame to be at least the size of a standard frame */
5687 if (max_frame < (ETH_FRAME_LEN + ETH_FCS_LEN))
5688 max_frame = ETH_FRAME_LEN + ETH_FCS_LEN;
5689
5690 while (test_and_set_bit(__IGB_RESETTING, &adapter->state))
5691 usleep_range(1000, 2000);
5692
5693 /* igb_down has a dependency on max_frame_size */
5694 adapter->max_frame_size = max_frame;
5695
5696 if (netif_running(netdev))
5697 igb_down(adapter);
5698
5699 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "changing MTU from %d to %d\n",
5700 netdev->mtu, new_mtu);
5701 netdev->mtu = new_mtu;
5702 hw->dev_spec._82575.mtu = new_mtu;
5703
5704 if (netif_running(netdev))
5705 igb_up(adapter);
5706 else
5707 igb_reset(adapter);
5708
5709 clear_bit(__IGB_RESETTING, &adapter->state);
5710
5711 return 0;
5712}
5713
5714/**
5715 * igb_update_stats - Update the board statistics counters
5716 * @adapter: board private structure
5717 **/
5718
5719void igb_update_stats(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
5720{
5721#ifdef HAVE_NETDEV_STATS_IN_NETDEV
5722 struct net_device_stats *net_stats = &adapter->netdev->stats;
5723#else
5724 struct net_device_stats *net_stats = &adapter->net_stats;
5725#endif /* HAVE_NETDEV_STATS_IN_NETDEV */
5726 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5727#ifdef HAVE_PCI_ERS
5728 struct pci_dev *pdev = adapter->pdev;
5729#endif
5730 u32 reg, mpc;
5731 u16 phy_tmp;
5732 int i;
5733 u64 bytes, packets;
5734#ifndef IGB_NO_LRO
5735 u32 flushed = 0, coal = 0;
5736 struct igb_q_vector *q_vector;
5737#endif
5738
5739#define PHY_IDLE_ERROR_COUNT_MASK 0x00FF
5740
5741 /*
5742 * Prevent stats update while adapter is being reset, or if the pci
5743 * connection is down.
5744 */
5745 if (adapter->link_speed == 0)
5746 return;
5747#ifdef HAVE_PCI_ERS
5748 if (pci_channel_offline(pdev))
5749 return;
5750
5751#endif
5752#ifndef IGB_NO_LRO
5753 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_q_vectors; i++) {
5754 q_vector = adapter->q_vector[i];
5755 if (!q_vector)
5756 continue;
5757 flushed += q_vector->lrolist.stats.flushed;
5758 coal += q_vector->lrolist.stats.coal;
5759 }
5760 adapter->lro_stats.flushed = flushed;
5761 adapter->lro_stats.coal = coal;
5762
5763#endif
5764 bytes = 0;
5765 packets = 0;
5766 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_rx_queues; i++) {
5767 u32 rqdpc_tmp = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RQDPC(i)) & 0x0FFF;
5768 struct igb_ring *ring = adapter->rx_ring[i];
5769 ring->rx_stats.drops += rqdpc_tmp;
5770 net_stats->rx_fifo_errors += rqdpc_tmp;
5771#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_VMDQ_NETDEV
5772 if (!ring->vmdq_netdev) {
5773 bytes += ring->rx_stats.bytes;
5774 packets += ring->rx_stats.packets;
5775 }
5776#else
5777 bytes += ring->rx_stats.bytes;
5778 packets += ring->rx_stats.packets;
5779#endif
5780 }
5781
5782 net_stats->rx_bytes = bytes;
5783 net_stats->rx_packets = packets;
5784
5785 bytes = 0;
5786 packets = 0;
5787 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_tx_queues; i++) {
5788 struct igb_ring *ring = adapter->tx_ring[i];
5789#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_VMDQ_NETDEV
5790 if (!ring->vmdq_netdev) {
5791 bytes += ring->tx_stats.bytes;
5792 packets += ring->tx_stats.packets;
5793 }
5794#else
5795 bytes += ring->tx_stats.bytes;
5796 packets += ring->tx_stats.packets;
5797#endif
5798 }
5799 net_stats->tx_bytes = bytes;
5800 net_stats->tx_packets = packets;
5801
5802 /* read stats registers */
5803 adapter->stats.crcerrs += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CRCERRS);
5804 adapter->stats.gprc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_GPRC);
5805 adapter->stats.gorc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_GORCL);
5806 E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_GORCH); /* clear GORCL */
5807 adapter->stats.bprc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_BPRC);
5808 adapter->stats.mprc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_MPRC);
5809 adapter->stats.roc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ROC);
5810
5811 adapter->stats.prc64 += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PRC64);
5812 adapter->stats.prc127 += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PRC127);
5813 adapter->stats.prc255 += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PRC255);
5814 adapter->stats.prc511 += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PRC511);
5815 adapter->stats.prc1023 += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PRC1023);
5816 adapter->stats.prc1522 += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PRC1522);
5817 adapter->stats.symerrs += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_SYMERRS);
5818 adapter->stats.sec += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_SEC);
5819
5820 mpc = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_MPC);
5821 adapter->stats.mpc += mpc;
5822 net_stats->rx_fifo_errors += mpc;
5823 adapter->stats.scc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_SCC);
5824 adapter->stats.ecol += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ECOL);
5825 adapter->stats.mcc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_MCC);
5826 adapter->stats.latecol += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_LATECOL);
5827 adapter->stats.dc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_DC);
5828 adapter->stats.rlec += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RLEC);
5829 adapter->stats.xonrxc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_XONRXC);
5830 adapter->stats.xontxc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_XONTXC);
5831 adapter->stats.xoffrxc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_XOFFRXC);
5832 adapter->stats.xofftxc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_XOFFTXC);
5833 adapter->stats.fcruc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_FCRUC);
5834 adapter->stats.gptc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_GPTC);
5835 adapter->stats.gotc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_GOTCL);
5836 E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_GOTCH); /* clear GOTCL */
5837 adapter->stats.rnbc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RNBC);
5838 adapter->stats.ruc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RUC);
5839 adapter->stats.rfc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RFC);
5840 adapter->stats.rjc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RJC);
5841 adapter->stats.tor += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_TORH);
5842 adapter->stats.tot += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_TOTH);
5843 adapter->stats.tpr += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_TPR);
5844
5845 adapter->stats.ptc64 += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PTC64);
5846 adapter->stats.ptc127 += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PTC127);
5847 adapter->stats.ptc255 += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PTC255);
5848 adapter->stats.ptc511 += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PTC511);
5849 adapter->stats.ptc1023 += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PTC1023);
5850 adapter->stats.ptc1522 += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PTC1522);
5851
5852 adapter->stats.mptc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_MPTC);
5853 adapter->stats.bptc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_BPTC);
5854
5855 adapter->stats.tpt += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_TPT);
5856 adapter->stats.colc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_COLC);
5857
5858 adapter->stats.algnerrc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ALGNERRC);
5859 /* read internal phy sepecific stats */
5860 reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL_EXT);
5861 if (!(reg & E1000_CTRL_EXT_LINK_MODE_MASK)) {
5862 adapter->stats.rxerrc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RXERRC);
5863
5864 /* this stat has invalid values on i210/i211 */
5865 if ((hw->mac.type != e1000_i210) &&
5866 (hw->mac.type != e1000_i211))
5867 adapter->stats.tncrs += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_TNCRS);
5868 }
5869 adapter->stats.tsctc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_TSCTC);
5870 adapter->stats.tsctfc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_TSCTFC);
5871
5872 adapter->stats.iac += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_IAC);
5873 adapter->stats.icrxoc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ICRXOC);
5874 adapter->stats.icrxptc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ICRXPTC);
5875 adapter->stats.icrxatc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ICRXATC);
5876 adapter->stats.ictxptc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ICTXPTC);
5877 adapter->stats.ictxatc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ICTXATC);
5878 adapter->stats.ictxqec += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ICTXQEC);
5879 adapter->stats.ictxqmtc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ICTXQMTC);
5880 adapter->stats.icrxdmtc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ICRXDMTC);
5881
5882 /* Fill out the OS statistics structure */
5883 net_stats->multicast = adapter->stats.mprc;
5884 net_stats->collisions = adapter->stats.colc;
5885
5886 /* Rx Errors */
5887
5888 /* RLEC on some newer hardware can be incorrect so build
5889 * our own version based on RUC and ROC */
5890 net_stats->rx_errors = adapter->stats.rxerrc +
5891 adapter->stats.crcerrs + adapter->stats.algnerrc +
5892 adapter->stats.ruc + adapter->stats.roc +
5893 adapter->stats.cexterr;
5894 net_stats->rx_length_errors = adapter->stats.ruc +
5895 adapter->stats.roc;
5896 net_stats->rx_crc_errors = adapter->stats.crcerrs;
5897 net_stats->rx_frame_errors = adapter->stats.algnerrc;
5898 net_stats->rx_missed_errors = adapter->stats.mpc;
5899
5900 /* Tx Errors */
5901 net_stats->tx_errors = adapter->stats.ecol +
5902 adapter->stats.latecol;
5903 net_stats->tx_aborted_errors = adapter->stats.ecol;
5904 net_stats->tx_window_errors = adapter->stats.latecol;
5905 net_stats->tx_carrier_errors = adapter->stats.tncrs;
5906
5907 /* Tx Dropped needs to be maintained elsewhere */
5908
5909 /* Phy Stats */
5910 if (hw->phy.media_type == e1000_media_type_copper) {
5911 if ((adapter->link_speed == SPEED_1000) &&
5912 (!e1000_read_phy_reg(hw, PHY_1000T_STATUS, &phy_tmp))) {
5913 phy_tmp &= PHY_IDLE_ERROR_COUNT_MASK;
5914 adapter->phy_stats.idle_errors += phy_tmp;
5915 }
5916 }
5917
5918 /* Management Stats */
5919 adapter->stats.mgptc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_MGTPTC);
5920 adapter->stats.mgprc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_MGTPRC);
5921 if (hw->mac.type > e1000_82580) {
5922 adapter->stats.o2bgptc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_O2BGPTC);
5923 adapter->stats.o2bspc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_O2BSPC);
5924 adapter->stats.b2ospc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_B2OSPC);
5925 adapter->stats.b2ogprc += E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_B2OGPRC);
5926 }
5927}
5928
5929static irqreturn_t igb_msix_other(int irq, void *data)
5930{
5931 struct igb_adapter *adapter = data;
5932 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5933 u32 icr = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ICR);
5934 /* reading ICR causes bit 31 of EICR to be cleared */
5935
5936 if (icr & E1000_ICR_DRSTA)
5937 schedule_work(&adapter->reset_task);
5938
5939 if (icr & E1000_ICR_DOUTSYNC) {
5940 /* HW is reporting DMA is out of sync */
5941 adapter->stats.doosync++;
5942 /* The DMA Out of Sync is also indication of a spoof event
5943 * in IOV mode. Check the Wrong VM Behavior register to
5944 * see if it is really a spoof event. */
5945 igb_check_wvbr(adapter);
5946 }
5947
5948 /* Check for a mailbox event */
5949 if (icr & E1000_ICR_VMMB)
5950 igb_msg_task(adapter);
5951
5952 if (icr & E1000_ICR_LSC) {
5953 hw->mac.get_link_status = 1;
5954 /* guard against interrupt when we're going down */
5955 if (!test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state))
5956 mod_timer(&adapter->watchdog_timer, jiffies + 1);
5957 }
5958
5959#ifdef HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK
5960 if (icr & E1000_ICR_TS) {
5961 u32 tsicr = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_TSICR);
5962
5963 if (tsicr & E1000_TSICR_TXTS) {
5964 /* acknowledge the interrupt */
5965 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_TSICR, E1000_TSICR_TXTS);
5966 /* retrieve hardware timestamp */
5967 schedule_work(&adapter->ptp_tx_work);
5968 }
5969 }
5970#endif /* HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK */
5971
5972 /* Check for MDD event */
5973 if (icr & E1000_ICR_MDDET)
5974 igb_process_mdd_event(adapter);
5975
5976 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_EIMS, adapter->eims_other);
5977
5978 return IRQ_HANDLED;
5979}
5980
5981static void igb_write_itr(struct igb_q_vector *q_vector)
5982{
5983 struct igb_adapter *adapter = q_vector->adapter;
5984 u32 itr_val = q_vector->itr_val & 0x7FFC;
5985
5986 if (!q_vector->set_itr)
5987 return;
5988
5989 if (!itr_val)
5990 itr_val = 0x4;
5991
5992 if (adapter->hw.mac.type == e1000_82575)
5993 itr_val |= itr_val << 16;
5994 else
5995 itr_val |= E1000_EITR_CNT_IGNR;
5996
5997 writel(itr_val, q_vector->itr_register);
5998 q_vector->set_itr = 0;
5999}
6000
6001static irqreturn_t igb_msix_ring(int irq, void *data)
6002{
6003 struct igb_q_vector *q_vector = data;
6004
6005 /* Write the ITR value calculated from the previous interrupt. */
6006 igb_write_itr(q_vector);
6007
6008 napi_schedule(&q_vector->napi);
6009
6010 return IRQ_HANDLED;
6011}
6012
6013#ifdef IGB_DCA
6014static void igb_update_tx_dca(struct igb_adapter *adapter,
6015 struct igb_ring *tx_ring,
6016 int cpu)
6017{
6018 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6019 u32 txctrl = dca3_get_tag(tx_ring->dev, cpu);
6020
6021 if (hw->mac.type != e1000_82575)
6022 txctrl <<= E1000_DCA_TXCTRL_CPUID_SHIFT_82576;
6023
6024 /*
6025 * We can enable relaxed ordering for reads, but not writes when
6026 * DCA is enabled. This is due to a known issue in some chipsets
6027 * which will cause the DCA tag to be cleared.
6028 */
6029 txctrl |= E1000_DCA_TXCTRL_DESC_RRO_EN |
6030 E1000_DCA_TXCTRL_DATA_RRO_EN |
6031 E1000_DCA_TXCTRL_DESC_DCA_EN;
6032
6033 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_DCA_TXCTRL(tx_ring->reg_idx), txctrl);
6034}
6035
6036static void igb_update_rx_dca(struct igb_adapter *adapter,
6037 struct igb_ring *rx_ring,
6038 int cpu)
6039{
6040 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6041 u32 rxctrl = dca3_get_tag(&adapter->pdev->dev, cpu);
6042
6043 if (hw->mac.type != e1000_82575)
6044 rxctrl <<= E1000_DCA_RXCTRL_CPUID_SHIFT_82576;
6045
6046 /*
6047 * We can enable relaxed ordering for reads, but not writes when
6048 * DCA is enabled. This is due to a known issue in some chipsets
6049 * which will cause the DCA tag to be cleared.
6050 */
6051 rxctrl |= E1000_DCA_RXCTRL_DESC_RRO_EN |
6052 E1000_DCA_RXCTRL_DESC_DCA_EN;
6053
6054 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_DCA_RXCTRL(rx_ring->reg_idx), rxctrl);
6055}
6056
6057static void igb_update_dca(struct igb_q_vector *q_vector)
6058{
6059 struct igb_adapter *adapter = q_vector->adapter;
6060 int cpu = get_cpu();
6061
6062 if (q_vector->cpu == cpu)
6063 goto out_no_update;
6064
6065 if (q_vector->tx.ring)
6066 igb_update_tx_dca(adapter, q_vector->tx.ring, cpu);
6067
6068 if (q_vector->rx.ring)
6069 igb_update_rx_dca(adapter, q_vector->rx.ring, cpu);
6070
6071 q_vector->cpu = cpu;
6072out_no_update:
6073 put_cpu();
6074}
6075
6076static void igb_setup_dca(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
6077{
6078 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6079 int i;
6080
6081 if (!(adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_DCA_ENABLED))
6082 return;
6083
6084 /* Always use CB2 mode, difference is masked in the CB driver. */
6085 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_DCA_CTRL, E1000_DCA_CTRL_DCA_MODE_CB2);
6086
6087 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_q_vectors; i++) {
6088 adapter->q_vector[i]->cpu = -1;
6089 igb_update_dca(adapter->q_vector[i]);
6090 }
6091}
6092
6093static int __igb_notify_dca(struct device *dev, void *data)
6094{
6095 struct net_device *netdev = dev_get_drvdata(dev);
6096 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
6097 struct pci_dev *pdev = adapter->pdev;
6098 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6099 unsigned long event = *(unsigned long *)data;
6100
6101 switch (event) {
6102 case DCA_PROVIDER_ADD:
6103 /* if already enabled, don't do it again */
6104 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_DCA_ENABLED)
6105 break;
6106 if (dca_add_requester(dev) == E1000_SUCCESS) {
6107 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_DCA_ENABLED;
6108 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "DCA enabled\n");
6109 igb_setup_dca(adapter);
6110 break;
6111 }
6112 /* Fall Through since DCA is disabled. */
6113 case DCA_PROVIDER_REMOVE:
6114 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_DCA_ENABLED) {
6115 /* without this a class_device is left
6116 * hanging around in the sysfs model */
6117 dca_remove_requester(dev);
6118 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "DCA disabled\n");
6119 adapter->flags &= ~IGB_FLAG_DCA_ENABLED;
6120 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_DCA_CTRL, E1000_DCA_CTRL_DCA_DISABLE);
6121 }
6122 break;
6123 }
6124
6125 return E1000_SUCCESS;
6126}
6127
6128static int igb_notify_dca(struct notifier_block *nb, unsigned long event,
6129 void *p)
6130{
6131 int ret_val;
6132
6133 ret_val = driver_for_each_device(&igb_driver.driver, NULL, &event,
6134 __igb_notify_dca);
6135
6136 return ret_val ? NOTIFY_BAD : NOTIFY_DONE;
6137}
6138#endif /* IGB_DCA */

6140static int igb_vf_configure(struct igb_adapter *adapter, int vf)
6141{
6142 unsigned char mac_addr[ETH_ALEN];
6143
6144 random_ether_addr(mac_addr);
6145 igb_set_vf_mac(adapter, vf, mac_addr);
6146
6147#ifdef IFLA_VF_MAX
6148#ifdef HAVE_VF_SPOOFCHK_CONFIGURE
6149 /* By default spoof check is enabled for all VFs */
6150 adapter->vf_data[vf].spoofchk_enabled = true;
6151#endif
6152#endif
6153
6154 return true;
6155}
6156
6157static void igb_ping_all_vfs(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
6158{
6159 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6160 u32 ping;
6161 int i;
6162
6163 for (i = 0 ; i < adapter->vfs_allocated_count; i++) {
6164 ping = E1000_PF_CONTROL_MSG;
6165 if (adapter->vf_data[i].flags & IGB_VF_FLAG_CTS)
6166 ping |= E1000_VT_MSGTYPE_CTS;
6167 e1000_write_mbx(hw, &ping, 1, i);
6168 }
6169}
6170
6171/**
6172 * igb_mta_set_ - Set multicast filter table address
6173 * @adapter: pointer to the adapter structure
6174 * @hash_value: determines the MTA register and bit to set
6175 *
6176 * The multicast table address is a register array of 32-bit registers.
6177 * The hash_value is used to determine what register the bit is in, the
6178 * current value is read, the new bit is OR'd in and the new value is
6179 * written back into the register.
6180 **/
6181void igb_mta_set(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u32 hash_value)
6182{
6183 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6184 u32 hash_bit, hash_reg, mta;
6185
6186 /*
6187 * The MTA is a register array of 32-bit registers. It is
6188 * treated like an array of (32*mta_reg_count) bits. We want to
6189 * set bit BitArray[hash_value]. So we figure out what register
6190 * the bit is in, read it, OR in the new bit, then write
6191 * back the new value. The (hw->mac.mta_reg_count - 1) serves as a
6192 * mask to bits 31:5 of the hash value which gives us the
6193 * register we're modifying. The hash bit within that register
6194 * is determined by the lower 5 bits of the hash value.
6195 */
6196 hash_reg = (hash_value >> 5) & (hw->mac.mta_reg_count - 1);
6197 hash_bit = hash_value & 0x1F;
6198
6199 mta = E1000_READ_REG_ARRAY(hw, E1000_MTA, hash_reg);
6200
6201 mta |= (1 << hash_bit);
6202
6203 E1000_WRITE_REG_ARRAY(hw, E1000_MTA, hash_reg, mta);
6204 E1000_WRITE_FLUSH(hw);
6205}
6206
6207static int igb_set_vf_promisc(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u32 *msgbuf, u32 vf)
6208{
6209
6210 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6211 u32 vmolr = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_VMOLR(vf));
6212 struct vf_data_storage *vf_data = &adapter->vf_data[vf];
6213
6214 vf_data->flags &= ~(IGB_VF_FLAG_UNI_PROMISC |
6215 IGB_VF_FLAG_MULTI_PROMISC);
6216 vmolr &= ~(E1000_VMOLR_ROPE | E1000_VMOLR_ROMPE | E1000_VMOLR_MPME);
6217
6218#ifdef IGB_ENABLE_VF_PROMISC
6219 if (*msgbuf & E1000_VF_SET_PROMISC_UNICAST) {
6220 vmolr |= E1000_VMOLR_ROPE;
6221 vf_data->flags |= IGB_VF_FLAG_UNI_PROMISC;
6222 *msgbuf &= ~E1000_VF_SET_PROMISC_UNICAST;
6223 }
6224#endif
6225 if (*msgbuf & E1000_VF_SET_PROMISC_MULTICAST) {
6226 vmolr |= E1000_VMOLR_MPME;
6227 vf_data->flags |= IGB_VF_FLAG_MULTI_PROMISC;
6228 *msgbuf &= ~E1000_VF_SET_PROMISC_MULTICAST;
6229 } else {
6230 /*
6231 * if we have hashes and we are clearing a multicast promisc
6232 * flag we need to write the hashes to the MTA as this step
6233 * was previously skipped
6234 */
6235 if (vf_data->num_vf_mc_hashes > 30) {
6236 vmolr |= E1000_VMOLR_MPME;
6237 } else if (vf_data->num_vf_mc_hashes) {
6238 int j;
6239 vmolr |= E1000_VMOLR_ROMPE;
6240 for (j = 0; j < vf_data->num_vf_mc_hashes; j++)
6241 igb_mta_set(adapter, vf_data->vf_mc_hashes[j]);
6242 }
6243 }
6244
6245 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_VMOLR(vf), vmolr);
6246
6247 /* there are flags left unprocessed, likely not supported */
6248 if (*msgbuf & E1000_VT_MSGINFO_MASK)
6249 return -EINVAL;
6250
6251 return 0;
6252
6253}
6254
6255static int igb_set_vf_multicasts(struct igb_adapter *adapter,
6256 u32 *msgbuf, u32 vf)
6257{
6258 int n = (msgbuf[0] & E1000_VT_MSGINFO_MASK) >> E1000_VT_MSGINFO_SHIFT;
6259 u16 *hash_list = (u16 *)&msgbuf[1];
6260 struct vf_data_storage *vf_data = &adapter->vf_data[vf];
6261 int i;
6262
6263 /* salt away the number of multicast addresses assigned
6264 * to this VF for later use to restore when the PF multi cast
6265 * list changes
6266 */
6267 vf_data->num_vf_mc_hashes = n;
6268
6269 /* only up to 30 hash values supported */
6270 if (n > 30)
6271 n = 30;
6272
6273 /* store the hashes for later use */
6274 for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
6275 vf_data->vf_mc_hashes[i] = hash_list[i];
6276
6277 /* Flush and reset the mta with the new values */
6278 igb_set_rx_mode(adapter->netdev);
6279
6280 return 0;
6281}
6282
6283static void igb_restore_vf_multicasts(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
6284{
6285 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6286 struct vf_data_storage *vf_data;
6287 int i, j;
6288
6289 for (i = 0; i < adapter->vfs_allocated_count; i++) {
6290 u32 vmolr = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_VMOLR(i));
6291 vmolr &= ~(E1000_VMOLR_ROMPE | E1000_VMOLR_MPME);
6292
6293 vf_data = &adapter->vf_data[i];
6294
6295 if ((vf_data->num_vf_mc_hashes > 30) ||
6296 (vf_data->flags & IGB_VF_FLAG_MULTI_PROMISC)) {
6297 vmolr |= E1000_VMOLR_MPME;
6298 } else if (vf_data->num_vf_mc_hashes) {
6299 vmolr |= E1000_VMOLR_ROMPE;
6300 for (j = 0; j < vf_data->num_vf_mc_hashes; j++)
6301 igb_mta_set(adapter, vf_data->vf_mc_hashes[j]);
6302 }
6303 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_VMOLR(i), vmolr);
6304 }
6305}
6306
6307static void igb_clear_vf_vfta(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u32 vf)
6308{
6309 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6310 u32 pool_mask, reg, vid;
6311 u16 vlan_default;
6312 int i;
6313
6314 pool_mask = 1 << (E1000_VLVF_POOLSEL_SHIFT + vf);
6315
6316 /* Find the vlan filter for this id */
6317 for (i = 0; i < E1000_VLVF_ARRAY_SIZE; i++) {
6318 reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_VLVF(i));
6319
6320 /* remove the vf from the pool */
6321 reg &= ~pool_mask;
6322
6323 /* if pool is empty then remove entry from vfta */
6324 if (!(reg & E1000_VLVF_POOLSEL_MASK) &&
6325 (reg & E1000_VLVF_VLANID_ENABLE)) {
6326 reg = 0;
6327 vid = reg & E1000_VLVF_VLANID_MASK;
6328 igb_vfta_set(adapter, vid, FALSE);
6329 }
6330
6331 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_VLVF(i), reg);
6332 }
6333
6334 adapter->vf_data[vf].vlans_enabled = 0;
6335
6336 vlan_default = adapter->vf_data[vf].default_vf_vlan_id;
6337 if (vlan_default)
6338 igb_vlvf_set(adapter, vlan_default, true, vf);
6339}
6340
6341s32 igb_vlvf_set(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u32 vid, bool add, u32 vf)
6342{
6343 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6344 u32 reg, i;
6345
6346 /* The vlvf table only exists on 82576 hardware and newer */
6347 if (hw->mac.type < e1000_82576)
6348 return -1;
6349
6350 /* we only need to do this if VMDq is enabled */
6351 if (!adapter->vmdq_pools)
6352 return -1;
6353
6354 /* Find the vlan filter for this id */
6355 for (i = 0; i < E1000_VLVF_ARRAY_SIZE; i++) {
6356 reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_VLVF(i));
6357 if ((reg & E1000_VLVF_VLANID_ENABLE) &&
6358 vid == (reg & E1000_VLVF_VLANID_MASK))
6359 break;
6360 }
6361
6362 if (add) {
6363 if (i == E1000_VLVF_ARRAY_SIZE) {
6364 /* Did not find a matching VLAN ID entry that was
6365 * enabled. Search for a free filter entry, i.e.
6366 * one without the enable bit set
6367 */
6368 for (i = 0; i < E1000_VLVF_ARRAY_SIZE; i++) {
6369 reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_VLVF(i));
6370 if (!(reg & E1000_VLVF_VLANID_ENABLE))
6371 break;
6372 }
6373 }
6374 if (i < E1000_VLVF_ARRAY_SIZE) {
6375 /* Found an enabled/available entry */
6376 reg |= 1 << (E1000_VLVF_POOLSEL_SHIFT + vf);
6377
6378 /* if !enabled we need to set this up in vfta */
6379 if (!(reg & E1000_VLVF_VLANID_ENABLE)) {
6380 /* add VID to filter table */
6381 igb_vfta_set(adapter, vid, TRUE);
6382 reg |= E1000_VLVF_VLANID_ENABLE;
6383 }
6384 reg &= ~E1000_VLVF_VLANID_MASK;
6385 reg |= vid;
6386 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_VLVF(i), reg);
6387
6388 /* do not modify RLPML for PF devices */
6389 if (vf >= adapter->vfs_allocated_count)
6390 return E1000_SUCCESS;
6391
6392 if (!adapter->vf_data[vf].vlans_enabled) {
6393 u32 size;
6394 reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_VMOLR(vf));
6395 size = reg & E1000_VMOLR_RLPML_MASK;
6396 size += 4;
6397 reg &= ~E1000_VMOLR_RLPML_MASK;
6398 reg |= size;
6399 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_VMOLR(vf), reg);
6400 }
6401
6402 adapter->vf_data[vf].vlans_enabled++;
6403 }
6404 } else {
6405 if (i < E1000_VLVF_ARRAY_SIZE) {
6406 /* remove vf from the pool */
6407 reg &= ~(1 << (E1000_VLVF_POOLSEL_SHIFT + vf));
6408 /* if pool is empty then remove entry from vfta */
6409 if (!(reg & E1000_VLVF_POOLSEL_MASK)) {
6410 reg = 0;
6411 igb_vfta_set(adapter, vid, FALSE);
6412 }
6413 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_VLVF(i), reg);
6414
6415 /* do not modify RLPML for PF devices */
6416 if (vf >= adapter->vfs_allocated_count)
6417 return E1000_SUCCESS;
6418
6419 adapter->vf_data[vf].vlans_enabled--;
6420 if (!adapter->vf_data[vf].vlans_enabled) {
6421 u32 size;
6422 reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_VMOLR(vf));
6423 size = reg & E1000_VMOLR_RLPML_MASK;
6424 size -= 4;
6425 reg &= ~E1000_VMOLR_RLPML_MASK;
6426 reg |= size;
6427 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_VMOLR(vf), reg);
6428 }
6429 }
6430 }
6431 return E1000_SUCCESS;
6432}
6433
6434#ifdef IFLA_VF_MAX
6435static void igb_set_vmvir(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u32 vid, u32 vf)
6436{
6437 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6438
6439 if (vid)
6440 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_VMVIR(vf), (vid | E1000_VMVIR_VLANA_DEFAULT));
6441 else
6442 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_VMVIR(vf), 0);
6443}
6444
6445static int igb_ndo_set_vf_vlan(struct net_device *netdev,
6446#ifdef HAVE_VF_VLAN_PROTO
6447 int vf, u16 vlan, u8 qos, __be16 vlan_proto)
6448#else
6449 int vf, u16 vlan, u8 qos)
6450#endif
6451{
6452 int err = 0;
6453 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
6454
6455 /* VLAN IDs accepted range 0-4094 */
6456 if ((vf >= adapter->vfs_allocated_count) || (vlan > VLAN_VID_MASK-1) || (qos > 7))
6457 return -EINVAL;
6458
6459#ifdef HAVE_VF_VLAN_PROTO
6460 if (vlan_proto != htons(ETH_P_8021Q))
6461 return -EPROTONOSUPPORT;
6462#endif
6463
6464 if (vlan || qos) {
6465 err = igb_vlvf_set(adapter, vlan, !!vlan, vf);
6466 if (err)
6467 goto out;
6468 igb_set_vmvir(adapter, vlan | (qos << VLAN_PRIO_SHIFT), vf);
6469 igb_set_vmolr(adapter, vf, !vlan);
6470 adapter->vf_data[vf].pf_vlan = vlan;
6471 adapter->vf_data[vf].pf_qos = qos;
6472 igb_set_vf_vlan_strip(adapter, vf, true);
6473 dev_info(&adapter->pdev->dev,
6474 "Setting VLAN %d, QOS 0x%x on VF %d\n", vlan, qos, vf);
6475 if (test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state)) {
6476 dev_warn(&adapter->pdev->dev,
6477 "The VF VLAN has been set,"
6478 " but the PF device is not up.\n");
6479 dev_warn(&adapter->pdev->dev,
6480 "Bring the PF device up before"
6481 " attempting to use the VF device.\n");
6482 }
6483 } else {
6484 if (adapter->vf_data[vf].pf_vlan)
6485 dev_info(&adapter->pdev->dev,
6486 "Clearing VLAN on VF %d\n", vf);
6487 igb_vlvf_set(adapter, adapter->vf_data[vf].pf_vlan,
6488 false, vf);
6489 igb_set_vmvir(adapter, vlan, vf);
6490 igb_set_vmolr(adapter, vf, true);
6491 igb_set_vf_vlan_strip(adapter, vf, false);
6492 adapter->vf_data[vf].pf_vlan = 0;
6493 adapter->vf_data[vf].pf_qos = 0;
6494 }
6495out:
6496 return err;
6497}
6498
6499#ifdef HAVE_VF_SPOOFCHK_CONFIGURE
6500static int igb_ndo_set_vf_spoofchk(struct net_device *netdev, int vf,
6501 bool setting)
6502{
6503 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
6504 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6505 u32 dtxswc, reg_offset;
6506
6507 if (!adapter->vfs_allocated_count)
6508 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
6509
6510 if (vf >= adapter->vfs_allocated_count)
6511 return -EINVAL;
6512
6513 reg_offset = (hw->mac.type == e1000_82576) ? E1000_DTXSWC : E1000_TXSWC;
6514 dtxswc = E1000_READ_REG(hw, reg_offset);
6515 if (setting)
6516 dtxswc |= ((1 << vf) |
6517 (1 << (vf + E1000_DTXSWC_VLAN_SPOOF_SHIFT)));
6518 else
6519 dtxswc &= ~((1 << vf) |
6520 (1 << (vf + E1000_DTXSWC_VLAN_SPOOF_SHIFT)));
6521 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, reg_offset, dtxswc);
6522
6523 adapter->vf_data[vf].spoofchk_enabled = setting;
6524 return E1000_SUCCESS;
6525}
6526#endif /* HAVE_VF_SPOOFCHK_CONFIGURE */
6527#endif /* IFLA_VF_MAX */
6528
6529static int igb_find_vlvf_entry(struct igb_adapter *adapter, int vid)
6530{
6531 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6532 int i;
6533 u32 reg;
6534
6535 /* Find the vlan filter for this id */
6536 for (i = 0; i < E1000_VLVF_ARRAY_SIZE; i++) {
6537 reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_VLVF(i));
6538 if ((reg & E1000_VLVF_VLANID_ENABLE) &&
6539 vid == (reg & E1000_VLVF_VLANID_MASK))
6540 break;
6541 }
6542
6543 if (i >= E1000_VLVF_ARRAY_SIZE)
6544 i = -1;
6545
6546 return i;
6547}
6548
6549static int igb_set_vf_vlan(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u32 *msgbuf, u32 vf)
6550{
6551 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6552 int add = (msgbuf[0] & E1000_VT_MSGINFO_MASK) >> E1000_VT_MSGINFO_SHIFT;
6553 int vid = (msgbuf[1] & E1000_VLVF_VLANID_MASK);
6554 int err = 0;
6555
6556 if (vid)
6557 igb_set_vf_vlan_strip(adapter, vf, true);
6558 else
6559 igb_set_vf_vlan_strip(adapter, vf, false);
6560
6561 /* If in promiscuous mode we need to make sure the PF also has
6562 * the VLAN filter set.
6563 */
6564 if (add && (adapter->netdev->flags & IFF_PROMISC))
6565 err = igb_vlvf_set(adapter, vid, add,
6566 adapter->vfs_allocated_count);
6567 if (err)
6568 goto out;
6569
6570 err = igb_vlvf_set(adapter, vid, add, vf);
6571
6572 if (err)
6573 goto out;
6574
6575 /* Go through all the checks to see if the VLAN filter should
6576 * be wiped completely.
6577 */
6578 if (!add && (adapter->netdev->flags & IFF_PROMISC)) {
6579 u32 vlvf, bits;
6580
6581 int regndx = igb_find_vlvf_entry(adapter, vid);
6582 if (regndx < 0)
6583 goto out;
6584 /* See if any other pools are set for this VLAN filter
6585 * entry other than the PF.
6586 */
6587 vlvf = bits = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_VLVF(regndx));
6588 bits &= 1 << (E1000_VLVF_POOLSEL_SHIFT +
6589 adapter->vfs_allocated_count);
6590 /* If the filter was removed then ensure PF pool bit
6591 * is cleared if the PF only added itself to the pool
6592 * because the PF is in promiscuous mode.
6593 */
6594 if ((vlvf & VLAN_VID_MASK) == vid &&
6595#ifndef HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER
6596 !test_bit(vid, adapter->active_vlans) &&
6597#endif
6598 !bits)
6599 igb_vlvf_set(adapter, vid, add,
6600 adapter->vfs_allocated_count);
6601 }
6602
6603out:
6604 return err;
6605}
6606
6607static inline void igb_vf_reset(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u32 vf)
6608{
6609 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6610
6611 /* clear flags except flag that the PF has set the MAC */
6612 adapter->vf_data[vf].flags &= IGB_VF_FLAG_PF_SET_MAC;
6613 adapter->vf_data[vf].last_nack = jiffies;
6614
6615 /* reset offloads to defaults */
6616 igb_set_vmolr(adapter, vf, true);
6617
6618 /* reset vlans for device */
6619 igb_clear_vf_vfta(adapter, vf);
6620#ifdef IFLA_VF_MAX
6621 if (adapter->vf_data[vf].pf_vlan)
6622 igb_ndo_set_vf_vlan(adapter->netdev, vf,
6623 adapter->vf_data[vf].pf_vlan,
6624#ifdef HAVE_VF_VLAN_PROTO
6625 adapter->vf_data[vf].pf_qos,
6626 htons(ETH_P_8021Q));
6627#else
6628 adapter->vf_data[vf].pf_qos);
6629#endif
6630 else
6631 igb_clear_vf_vfta(adapter, vf);
6632#endif
6633
6634 /* reset multicast table array for vf */
6635 adapter->vf_data[vf].num_vf_mc_hashes = 0;
6636
6637 /* Flush and reset the mta with the new values */
6638 igb_set_rx_mode(adapter->netdev);
6639
6640 /*
6641 * Reset the VFs TDWBAL and TDWBAH registers which are not
6642 * cleared by a VFLR
6643 */
6644 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_TDWBAH(vf), 0);
6645 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_TDWBAL(vf), 0);
6646 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_82576) {
6647 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_TDWBAH(IGB_MAX_VF_FUNCTIONS + vf), 0);
6648 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_TDWBAL(IGB_MAX_VF_FUNCTIONS + vf), 0);
6649 }
6650}
6651
6652static void igb_vf_reset_event(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u32 vf)
6653{
6654 unsigned char *vf_mac = adapter->vf_data[vf].vf_mac_addresses;
6655
6656 /* generate a new mac address as we were hotplug removed/added */
6657 if (!(adapter->vf_data[vf].flags & IGB_VF_FLAG_PF_SET_MAC))
6658 random_ether_addr(vf_mac);
6659
6660 /* process remaining reset events */
6661 igb_vf_reset(adapter, vf);
6662}
6663
6664static void igb_vf_reset_msg(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u32 vf)
6665{
6666 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6667 unsigned char *vf_mac = adapter->vf_data[vf].vf_mac_addresses;
6668 u32 reg, msgbuf[3];
6669 u8 *addr = (u8 *)(&msgbuf[1]);
6670
6671 /* process all the same items cleared in a function level reset */
6672 igb_vf_reset(adapter, vf);
6673
6674 /* set vf mac address */
6675 igb_del_mac_filter(adapter, vf_mac, vf);
6676 igb_add_mac_filter(adapter, vf_mac, vf);
6677
6678 /* enable transmit and receive for vf */
6679 reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_VFTE);
6680 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_VFTE, reg | (1 << vf));
6681 reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_VFRE);
6682 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_VFRE, reg | (1 << vf));
6683
6684 adapter->vf_data[vf].flags |= IGB_VF_FLAG_CTS;
6685
6686 /* reply to reset with ack and vf mac address */
6687 msgbuf[0] = E1000_VF_RESET | E1000_VT_MSGTYPE_ACK;
6688 memcpy(addr, vf_mac, 6);
6689 e1000_write_mbx(hw, msgbuf, 3, vf);
6690}
6691
6692static int igb_set_vf_mac_addr(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u32 *msg, int vf)
6693{
6694 /*
6695 * The VF MAC Address is stored in a packed array of bytes
6696 * starting at the second 32 bit word of the msg array
6697 */
6698 unsigned char *addr = (unsigned char *)&msg[1];
6699 int err = -1;
6700
6701 if (is_valid_ether_addr(addr))
6702 err = igb_set_vf_mac(adapter, vf, addr);
6703
6704 return err;
6705}
6706
6707static void igb_rcv_ack_from_vf(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u32 vf)
6708{
6709 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6710 struct vf_data_storage *vf_data = &adapter->vf_data[vf];
6711 u32 msg = E1000_VT_MSGTYPE_NACK;
6712
6713 /* if device isn't clear to send it shouldn't be reading either */
6714 if (!(vf_data->flags & IGB_VF_FLAG_CTS) &&
6715 time_after(jiffies, vf_data->last_nack + (2 * HZ))) {
6716 e1000_write_mbx(hw, &msg, 1, vf);
6717 vf_data->last_nack = jiffies;
6718 }
6719}
6720
6721static void igb_rcv_msg_from_vf(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u32 vf)
6722{
6723 struct pci_dev *pdev = adapter->pdev;
6724 u32 msgbuf[E1000_VFMAILBOX_SIZE];
6725 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6726 struct vf_data_storage *vf_data = &adapter->vf_data[vf];
6727 s32 retval;
6728
6729 retval = e1000_read_mbx(hw, msgbuf, E1000_VFMAILBOX_SIZE, vf);
6730
6731 if (retval) {
6732 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "Error receiving message from VF\n");
6733 return;
6734 }
6735
6736 /* this is a message we already processed, do nothing */
6737 if (msgbuf[0] & (E1000_VT_MSGTYPE_ACK | E1000_VT_MSGTYPE_NACK))
6738 return;
6739
6740 /*
6741 * until the vf completes a reset it should not be
6742 * allowed to start any configuration.
6743 */
6744
6745 if (msgbuf[0] == E1000_VF_RESET) {
6746 igb_vf_reset_msg(adapter, vf);
6747 return;
6748 }
6749
6750 if (!(vf_data->flags & IGB_VF_FLAG_CTS)) {
6751 msgbuf[0] = E1000_VT_MSGTYPE_NACK;
6752 if (time_after(jiffies, vf_data->last_nack + (2 * HZ))) {
6753 e1000_write_mbx(hw, msgbuf, 1, vf);
6754 vf_data->last_nack = jiffies;
6755 }
6756 return;
6757 }
6758
6759 switch ((msgbuf[0] & 0xFFFF)) {
6760 case E1000_VF_SET_MAC_ADDR:
6761 retval = -EINVAL;
6762#ifndef IGB_DISABLE_VF_MAC_SET
6763 if (!(vf_data->flags & IGB_VF_FLAG_PF_SET_MAC))
6764 retval = igb_set_vf_mac_addr(adapter, msgbuf, vf);
6765 else
