6766 DPRINTK(DRV, INFO,
6767 "VF %d attempted to override administratively "
6768 "set MAC address\nReload the VF driver to "
6769 "resume operations\n", vf);
6770#endif
6771 break;
6772 case E1000_VF_SET_PROMISC:
6773 retval = igb_set_vf_promisc(adapter, msgbuf, vf);
6774 break;
6775 case E1000_VF_SET_MULTICAST:
6776 retval = igb_set_vf_multicasts(adapter, msgbuf, vf);
6777 break;
6778 case E1000_VF_SET_LPE:
6779 retval = igb_set_vf_rlpml(adapter, msgbuf[1], vf);
6780 break;
6781 case E1000_VF_SET_VLAN:
6782 retval = -1;
6783#ifdef IFLA_VF_MAX
6784 if (vf_data->pf_vlan)
6785 DPRINTK(DRV, INFO,
6786 "VF %d attempted to override administratively "
6787 "set VLAN tag\nReload the VF driver to "
6788 "resume operations\n", vf);
6789 else
6790#endif
6791 retval = igb_set_vf_vlan(adapter, msgbuf, vf);
6792 break;
6793 default:
6794 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "Unhandled Msg %08x\n", msgbuf[0]);
6795 retval = -E1000_ERR_MBX;
6796 break;
6797 }
6798
6799 /* notify the VF of the results of what it sent us */
6800 if (retval)
6801 msgbuf[0] |= E1000_VT_MSGTYPE_NACK;
6802 else
6803 msgbuf[0] |= E1000_VT_MSGTYPE_ACK;
6804
6805 msgbuf[0] |= E1000_VT_MSGTYPE_CTS;
6806
6807 e1000_write_mbx(hw, msgbuf, 1, vf);
6808}
6809
6810static void igb_msg_task(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
6811{
6812 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6813 u32 vf;
6814
6815 for (vf = 0; vf < adapter->vfs_allocated_count; vf++) {
6816 /* process any reset requests */
6817 if (!e1000_check_for_rst(hw, vf))
6818 igb_vf_reset_event(adapter, vf);
6819
6820 /* process any messages pending */
6821 if (!e1000_check_for_msg(hw, vf))
6822 igb_rcv_msg_from_vf(adapter, vf);
6823
6824 /* process any acks */
6825 if (!e1000_check_for_ack(hw, vf))
6826 igb_rcv_ack_from_vf(adapter, vf);
6827 }
6828}
6829
6830/**
6831 * igb_set_uta - Set unicast filter table address
6832 * @adapter: board private structure
6833 *
6834 * The unicast table address is a register array of 32-bit registers.
6835 * The table is meant to be used in a way similar to how the MTA is used
6836 * however due to certain limitations in the hardware it is necessary to
6837 * set all the hash bits to 1 and use the VMOLR ROPE bit as a promiscuous
6838 * enable bit to allow vlan tag stripping when promiscuous mode is enabled
6839 **/
6840static void igb_set_uta(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
6841{
6842 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6843 int i;
6844
6845 /* The UTA table only exists on 82576 hardware and newer */
6846 if (hw->mac.type < e1000_82576)
6847 return;
6848
6849 /* we only need to do this if VMDq is enabled */
6850 if (!adapter->vmdq_pools)
6851 return;
6852
6853 for (i = 0; i < hw->mac.uta_reg_count; i++)
6854 E1000_WRITE_REG_ARRAY(hw, E1000_UTA, i, ~0);
6855}
6856
6857/**
6858 * igb_intr_msi - Interrupt Handler
6859 * @irq: interrupt number
6860 * @data: pointer to a network interface device structure
6861 **/
6862static irqreturn_t igb_intr_msi(int irq, void *data)
6863{
6864 struct igb_adapter *adapter = data;
6865 struct igb_q_vector *q_vector = adapter->q_vector[0];
6866 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6867 /* read ICR disables interrupts using IAM */
6868 u32 icr = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ICR);
6869
6870 igb_write_itr(q_vector);
6871
6872 if (icr & E1000_ICR_DRSTA)
6873 schedule_work(&adapter->reset_task);
6874
6875 if (icr & E1000_ICR_DOUTSYNC) {
6876 /* HW is reporting DMA is out of sync */
6877 adapter->stats.doosync++;
6878 }
6879
6880 if (icr & (E1000_ICR_RXSEQ | E1000_ICR_LSC)) {
6881 hw->mac.get_link_status = 1;
6882 if (!test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state))
6883 mod_timer(&adapter->watchdog_timer, jiffies + 1);
6884 }
6885
6886#ifdef HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK
6887 if (icr & E1000_ICR_TS) {
6888 u32 tsicr = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_TSICR);
6889
6890 if (tsicr & E1000_TSICR_TXTS) {
6891 /* acknowledge the interrupt */
6892 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_TSICR, E1000_TSICR_TXTS);
6893 /* retrieve hardware timestamp */
6894 schedule_work(&adapter->ptp_tx_work);
6895 }
6896 }
6897#endif /* HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK */
6898
6899 napi_schedule(&q_vector->napi);
6900
6901 return IRQ_HANDLED;
6902}
6903
6904/**
6905 * igb_intr - Legacy Interrupt Handler
6906 * @irq: interrupt number
6907 * @data: pointer to a network interface device structure
6908 **/
6909static irqreturn_t igb_intr(int irq, void *data)
6910{
6911 struct igb_adapter *adapter = data;
6912 struct igb_q_vector *q_vector = adapter->q_vector[0];
6913 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6914 /* Interrupt Auto-Mask...upon reading ICR, interrupts are masked. No
6915 * need for the IMC write */
6916 u32 icr = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ICR);
6917
6918 /* IMS will not auto-mask if INT_ASSERTED is not set, and if it is
6919 * not set, then the adapter didn't send an interrupt */
6920 if (!(icr & E1000_ICR_INT_ASSERTED))
6921 return IRQ_NONE;
6922
6923 igb_write_itr(q_vector);
6924
6925 if (icr & E1000_ICR_DRSTA)
6926 schedule_work(&adapter->reset_task);
6927
6928 if (icr & E1000_ICR_DOUTSYNC) {
6929 /* HW is reporting DMA is out of sync */
6930 adapter->stats.doosync++;
6931 }
6932
6933 if (icr & (E1000_ICR_RXSEQ | E1000_ICR_LSC)) {
6934 hw->mac.get_link_status = 1;
6935 /* guard against interrupt when we're going down */
6936 if (!test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state))
6937 mod_timer(&adapter->watchdog_timer, jiffies + 1);
6938 }
6939
6940#ifdef HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK
6941 if (icr & E1000_ICR_TS) {
6942 u32 tsicr = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_TSICR);
6943
6944 if (tsicr & E1000_TSICR_TXTS) {
6945 /* acknowledge the interrupt */
6946 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_TSICR, E1000_TSICR_TXTS);
6947 /* retrieve hardware timestamp */
6948 schedule_work(&adapter->ptp_tx_work);
6949 }
6950 }
6951#endif /* HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK */
6952
6953 napi_schedule(&q_vector->napi);
6954
6955 return IRQ_HANDLED;
6956}
6957
6958void igb_ring_irq_enable(struct igb_q_vector *q_vector)
6959{
6960 struct igb_adapter *adapter = q_vector->adapter;
6961 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
6962
6963 if ((q_vector->rx.ring && (adapter->rx_itr_setting & 3)) ||
6964 (!q_vector->rx.ring && (adapter->tx_itr_setting & 3))) {
6965 if ((adapter->num_q_vectors == 1) && !adapter->vf_data)
6966 igb_set_itr(q_vector);
6967 else
6968 igb_update_ring_itr(q_vector);
6969 }
6970
6971 if (!test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state)) {
6972 if (adapter->msix_entries)
6973 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_EIMS, q_vector->eims_value);
6974 else
6975 igb_irq_enable(adapter);
6976 }
6977}
6978
6979/**
6980 * igb_poll - NAPI Rx polling callback
6981 * @napi: napi polling structure
6982 * @budget: count of how many packets we should handle
6983 **/
6984static int igb_poll(struct napi_struct *napi, int budget)
6985{
6986 struct igb_q_vector *q_vector = container_of(napi, struct igb_q_vector, napi);
6987 bool clean_complete = true;
6988
6989#ifdef IGB_DCA
6990 if (q_vector->adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_DCA_ENABLED)
6991 igb_update_dca(q_vector);
6992#endif
6993 if (q_vector->tx.ring)
6994 clean_complete = igb_clean_tx_irq(q_vector);
6995
6996 if (q_vector->rx.ring)
6997 clean_complete &= igb_clean_rx_irq(q_vector, budget);
6998
6999#ifndef HAVE_NETDEV_NAPI_LIST
7000 /* if netdev is disabled we need to stop polling */
7001 if (!netif_running(q_vector->adapter->netdev))
7002 clean_complete = true;
7003
7004#endif
7005 /* If all work not completed, return budget and keep polling */
7006 if (!clean_complete)
7007 return budget;
7008
7009 /* If not enough Rx work done, exit the polling mode */
7010 napi_complete(napi);
7011 igb_ring_irq_enable(q_vector);
7012
7013 return 0;
7014}
7015
7016/**
7017 * igb_clean_tx_irq - Reclaim resources after transmit completes
7018 * @q_vector: pointer to q_vector containing needed info
7019 * returns TRUE if ring is completely cleaned
7020 **/
7021static bool igb_clean_tx_irq(struct igb_q_vector *q_vector)
7022{
7023 struct igb_adapter *adapter = q_vector->adapter;
7024 struct igb_ring *tx_ring = q_vector->tx.ring;
7025 struct igb_tx_buffer *tx_buffer;
7026 union e1000_adv_tx_desc *tx_desc;
7027 unsigned int total_bytes = 0, total_packets = 0;
7028 unsigned int budget = q_vector->tx.work_limit;
7029 unsigned int i = tx_ring->next_to_clean;
7030
7031 if (test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state))
7032 return true;
7033
7034 tx_buffer = &tx_ring->tx_buffer_info[i];
7035 tx_desc = IGB_TX_DESC(tx_ring, i);
7036 i -= tx_ring->count;
7037
7038 do {
7039 union e1000_adv_tx_desc *eop_desc = tx_buffer->next_to_watch;
7040
7041 /* if next_to_watch is not set then there is no work pending */
7042 if (!eop_desc)
7043 break;
7044
7045 /* prevent any other reads prior to eop_desc */
7046 read_barrier_depends();
7047
7048 /* if DD is not set pending work has not been completed */
7049 if (!(eop_desc->wb.status & cpu_to_le32(E1000_TXD_STAT_DD)))
7050 break;
7051
7052 /* clear next_to_watch to prevent false hangs */
7053 tx_buffer->next_to_watch = NULL;
7054
7055 /* update the statistics for this packet */
7056 total_bytes += tx_buffer->bytecount;
7057 total_packets += tx_buffer->gso_segs;
7058
7059 /* free the skb */
7060 dev_kfree_skb_any(tx_buffer->skb);
7061
7062 /* unmap skb header data */
7063 dma_unmap_single(tx_ring->dev,
7064 dma_unmap_addr(tx_buffer, dma),
7065 dma_unmap_len(tx_buffer, len),
7066 DMA_TO_DEVICE);
7067
7068 /* clear tx_buffer data */
7069 tx_buffer->skb = NULL;
7070 dma_unmap_len_set(tx_buffer, len, 0);
7071
7072 /* clear last DMA location and unmap remaining buffers */
7073 while (tx_desc != eop_desc) {
7074 tx_buffer++;
7075 tx_desc++;
7076 i++;
7077 if (unlikely(!i)) {
7078 i -= tx_ring->count;
7079 tx_buffer = tx_ring->tx_buffer_info;
7080 tx_desc = IGB_TX_DESC(tx_ring, 0);
7081 }
7082
7083 /* unmap any remaining paged data */
7084 if (dma_unmap_len(tx_buffer, len)) {
7085 dma_unmap_page(tx_ring->dev,
7086 dma_unmap_addr(tx_buffer, dma),
7087 dma_unmap_len(tx_buffer, len),
7088 DMA_TO_DEVICE);
7089 dma_unmap_len_set(tx_buffer, len, 0);
7090 }
7091 }
7092
7093 /* move us one more past the eop_desc for start of next pkt */
7094 tx_buffer++;
7095 tx_desc++;
7096 i++;
7097 if (unlikely(!i)) {
7098 i -= tx_ring->count;
7099 tx_buffer = tx_ring->tx_buffer_info;
7100 tx_desc = IGB_TX_DESC(tx_ring, 0);
7101 }
7102
7103 /* issue prefetch for next Tx descriptor */
7104 prefetch(tx_desc);
7105
7106 /* update budget accounting */
7107 budget--;
7108 } while (likely(budget));
7109
7110 netdev_tx_completed_queue(txring_txq(tx_ring),
7111 total_packets, total_bytes);
7112
7113 i += tx_ring->count;
7114 tx_ring->next_to_clean = i;
7115 tx_ring->tx_stats.bytes += total_bytes;
7116 tx_ring->tx_stats.packets += total_packets;
7117 q_vector->tx.total_bytes += total_bytes;
7118 q_vector->tx.total_packets += total_packets;
7119
7120#ifdef DEBUG
7121 if (test_bit(IGB_RING_FLAG_TX_DETECT_HANG, &tx_ring->flags) &&
7122 !(adapter->disable_hw_reset && adapter->tx_hang_detected)) {
7123#else
7124 if (test_bit(IGB_RING_FLAG_TX_DETECT_HANG, &tx_ring->flags)) {
7125#endif
7126 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
7127
7128 /* Detect a transmit hang in hardware, this serializes the
7129 * check with the clearing of time_stamp and movement of i */
7130 clear_bit(IGB_RING_FLAG_TX_DETECT_HANG, &tx_ring->flags);
7131 if (tx_buffer->next_to_watch &&
7132 time_after(jiffies, tx_buffer->time_stamp +
7133 (adapter->tx_timeout_factor * HZ))
7134 && !(E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_STATUS) &
7135 E1000_STATUS_TXOFF)) {
7136
7137 /* detected Tx unit hang */
7138#ifdef DEBUG
7139 adapter->tx_hang_detected = TRUE;
7140 if (adapter->disable_hw_reset) {
7141 DPRINTK(DRV, WARNING,
7142 "Deactivating netdev watchdog timer\n");
7143 if (del_timer(&netdev_ring(tx_ring)->watchdog_timer))
7144 dev_put(netdev_ring(tx_ring));
7145#ifndef HAVE_NET_DEVICE_OPS
7146 netdev_ring(tx_ring)->tx_timeout = NULL;
7147#endif
7148 }
7149#endif /* DEBUG */
7150 dev_err(tx_ring->dev,
7151 "Detected Tx Unit Hang\n"
7152 " Tx Queue <%d>\n"
7153 " TDH <%x>\n"
7154 " TDT <%x>\n"
7155 " next_to_use <%x>\n"
7156 " next_to_clean <%x>\n"
7157 "buffer_info[next_to_clean]\n"
7158 " time_stamp <%lx>\n"
7159 " next_to_watch <%p>\n"
7160 " jiffies <%lx>\n"
7161 " desc.status <%x>\n",
7162 tx_ring->queue_index,
7163 E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_TDH(tx_ring->reg_idx)),
7164 readl(tx_ring->tail),
7165 tx_ring->next_to_use,
7166 tx_ring->next_to_clean,
7167 tx_buffer->time_stamp,
7168 tx_buffer->next_to_watch,
7169 jiffies,
7170 tx_buffer->next_to_watch->wb.status);
7171 if (netif_is_multiqueue(netdev_ring(tx_ring)))
7172 netif_stop_subqueue(netdev_ring(tx_ring),
7173 ring_queue_index(tx_ring));
7174 else
7175 netif_stop_queue(netdev_ring(tx_ring));
7176
7177 /* we are about to reset, no point in enabling stuff */
7178 return true;
7179 }
7180 }
7181
7182#define TX_WAKE_THRESHOLD (DESC_NEEDED * 2)
7183 if (unlikely(total_packets &&
7184 netif_carrier_ok(netdev_ring(tx_ring)) &&
7185 igb_desc_unused(tx_ring) >= TX_WAKE_THRESHOLD)) {
7186 /* Make sure that anybody stopping the queue after this
7187 * sees the new next_to_clean.
7188 */
7189 smp_mb();
7190 if (netif_is_multiqueue(netdev_ring(tx_ring))) {
7191 if (__netif_subqueue_stopped(netdev_ring(tx_ring),
7192 ring_queue_index(tx_ring)) &&
7193 !(test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state))) {
7194 netif_wake_subqueue(netdev_ring(tx_ring),
7195 ring_queue_index(tx_ring));
7196 tx_ring->tx_stats.restart_queue++;
7197 }
7198 } else {
7199 if (netif_queue_stopped(netdev_ring(tx_ring)) &&
7200 !(test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state))) {
7201 netif_wake_queue(netdev_ring(tx_ring));
7202 tx_ring->tx_stats.restart_queue++;
7203 }
7204 }
7205 }
7206
7207 return !!budget;
7208}
7209
7210#ifdef HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER
7211/**
7212 * igb_receive_skb - helper function to handle rx indications
7213 * @q_vector: structure containing interrupt and ring information
7214 * @skb: packet to send up
7215 **/
7216static void igb_receive_skb(struct igb_q_vector *q_vector,
7217 struct sk_buff *skb)
7218{
7219 struct vlan_group **vlgrp = netdev_priv(skb->dev);
7220
7221 if (IGB_CB(skb)->vid) {
7222 if (*vlgrp) {
7223 vlan_gro_receive(&q_vector->napi, *vlgrp,
7224 IGB_CB(skb)->vid, skb);
7225 } else {
7226 dev_kfree_skb_any(skb);
7227 }
7228 } else {
7229 napi_gro_receive(&q_vector->napi, skb);
7230 }
7231}
7232
7233#endif /* HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER */
7234#ifndef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
7235/**
7236 * igb_reuse_rx_page - page flip buffer and store it back on the ring
7237 * @rx_ring: rx descriptor ring to store buffers on
7238 * @old_buff: donor buffer to have page reused
7239 *
7240 * Synchronizes page for reuse by the adapter
7241 **/
7242static void igb_reuse_rx_page(struct igb_ring *rx_ring,
7243 struct igb_rx_buffer *old_buff)
7244{
7245 struct igb_rx_buffer *new_buff;
7246 u16 nta = rx_ring->next_to_alloc;
7247
7248 new_buff = &rx_ring->rx_buffer_info[nta];
7249
7250 /* update, and store next to alloc */
7251 nta++;
7252 rx_ring->next_to_alloc = (nta < rx_ring->count) ? nta : 0;
7253
7254 /* transfer page from old buffer to new buffer */
7255 memcpy(new_buff, old_buff, sizeof(struct igb_rx_buffer));
7256
7257 /* sync the buffer for use by the device */
7258 dma_sync_single_range_for_device(rx_ring->dev, old_buff->dma,
7259 old_buff->page_offset,
7260 IGB_RX_BUFSZ,
7261 DMA_FROM_DEVICE);
7262}
7263
7264static bool igb_can_reuse_rx_page(struct igb_rx_buffer *rx_buffer,
7265 struct page *page,
7266 unsigned int truesize)
7267{
7268 /* avoid re-using remote pages */
7269 if (unlikely(page_to_nid(page) != numa_node_id()))
7270 return false;
7271
7272#if (PAGE_SIZE < 8192)
7273 /* if we are only owner of page we can reuse it */
7274 if (unlikely(page_count(page) != 1))
7275 return false;
7276
7277 /* flip page offset to other buffer */
7278 rx_buffer->page_offset ^= IGB_RX_BUFSZ;
7279
7280#else
7281 /* move offset up to the next cache line */
7282 rx_buffer->page_offset += truesize;
7283
7284 if (rx_buffer->page_offset > (PAGE_SIZE - IGB_RX_BUFSZ))
7285 return false;
7286#endif
7287
7288 /* bump ref count on page before it is given to the stack */
7289 get_page(page);
7290
7291 return true;
7292}
7293
7294/**
7295 * igb_add_rx_frag - Add contents of Rx buffer to sk_buff
7296 * @rx_ring: rx descriptor ring to transact packets on
7297 * @rx_buffer: buffer containing page to add
7298 * @rx_desc: descriptor containing length of buffer written by hardware
7299 * @skb: sk_buff to place the data into
7300 *
7301 * This function will add the data contained in rx_buffer->page to the skb.
7302 * This is done either through a direct copy if the data in the buffer is
7303 * less than the skb header size, otherwise it will just attach the page as
7304 * a frag to the skb.
7305 *
7306 * The function will then update the page offset if necessary and return
7307 * true if the buffer can be reused by the adapter.
7308 **/
7309static bool igb_add_rx_frag(struct igb_ring *rx_ring,
7310 struct igb_rx_buffer *rx_buffer,
7311 union e1000_adv_rx_desc *rx_desc,
7312 struct sk_buff *skb)
7313{
7314 struct page *page = rx_buffer->page;
7315 unsigned int size = le16_to_cpu(rx_desc->wb.upper.length);
7316#if (PAGE_SIZE < 8192)
7317 unsigned int truesize = IGB_RX_BUFSZ;
7318#else
7319 unsigned int truesize = ALIGN(size, L1_CACHE_BYTES);
7320#endif
7321
7322 if ((size <= IGB_RX_HDR_LEN) && !skb_is_nonlinear(skb)) {
7323 unsigned char *va = page_address(page) + rx_buffer->page_offset;
7324
7325#ifdef HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK
7326 if (igb_test_staterr(rx_desc, E1000_RXDADV_STAT_TSIP)) {
7327 igb_ptp_rx_pktstamp(rx_ring->q_vector, va, skb);
7328 va += IGB_TS_HDR_LEN;
7329 size -= IGB_TS_HDR_LEN;
7330 }
7331#endif /* HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK */
7332
7333 memcpy(__skb_put(skb, size), va, ALIGN(size, sizeof(long)));
7334
7335 /* we can reuse buffer as-is, just make sure it is local */
7336 if (likely(page_to_nid(page) == numa_node_id()))
7337 return true;
7338
7339 /* this page cannot be reused so discard it */
7340 put_page(page);
7341 return false;
7342 }
7343
7344 skb_add_rx_frag(skb, skb_shinfo(skb)->nr_frags, page,
7345 rx_buffer->page_offset, size, truesize);
7346
7347 return igb_can_reuse_rx_page(rx_buffer, page, truesize);
7348}
7349
7350static struct sk_buff *igb_fetch_rx_buffer(struct igb_ring *rx_ring,
7351 union e1000_adv_rx_desc *rx_desc,
7352 struct sk_buff *skb)
7353{
7354 struct igb_rx_buffer *rx_buffer;
7355 struct page *page;
7356
7357 rx_buffer = &rx_ring->rx_buffer_info[rx_ring->next_to_clean];
7358
7359 page = rx_buffer->page;
7360 prefetchw(page);
7361
7362 if (likely(!skb)) {
7363 void *page_addr = page_address(page) +
7364 rx_buffer->page_offset;
7365
7366 /* prefetch first cache line of first page */
7367 prefetch(page_addr);
7368#if L1_CACHE_BYTES < 128
7369 prefetch(page_addr + L1_CACHE_BYTES);
7370#endif
7371
7372 /* allocate a skb to store the frags */
7373 skb = netdev_alloc_skb_ip_align(rx_ring->netdev,
7374 IGB_RX_HDR_LEN);
7375 if (unlikely(!skb)) {
7376 rx_ring->rx_stats.alloc_failed++;
7377 return NULL;
7378 }
7379
7380 /*
7381 * we will be copying header into skb->data in
7382 * pskb_may_pull so it is in our interest to prefetch
7383 * it now to avoid a possible cache miss
7384 */
7385 prefetchw(skb->data);
7386 }
7387
7388 /* we are reusing so sync this buffer for CPU use */
7389 dma_sync_single_range_for_cpu(rx_ring->dev,
7390 rx_buffer->dma,
7391 rx_buffer->page_offset,
7392 IGB_RX_BUFSZ,
7393 DMA_FROM_DEVICE);
7394
7395 /* pull page into skb */
7396 if (igb_add_rx_frag(rx_ring, rx_buffer, rx_desc, skb)) {
7397 /* hand second half of page back to the ring */
7398 igb_reuse_rx_page(rx_ring, rx_buffer);
7399 } else {
7400 /* we are not reusing the buffer so unmap it */
7401 dma_unmap_page(rx_ring->dev, rx_buffer->dma,
7402 PAGE_SIZE, DMA_FROM_DEVICE);
7403 }
7404
7405 /* clear contents of rx_buffer */
7406 rx_buffer->page = NULL;
7407
7408 return skb;
7409}
7410
7411#endif
7412static inline void igb_rx_checksum(struct igb_ring *ring,
7413 union e1000_adv_rx_desc *rx_desc,
7414 struct sk_buff *skb)
7415{
7416 skb_checksum_none_assert(skb);
7417
7418 /* Ignore Checksum bit is set */
7419 if (igb_test_staterr(rx_desc, E1000_RXD_STAT_IXSM))
7420 return;
7421
7422 /* Rx checksum disabled via ethtool */
7423 if (!(netdev_ring(ring)->features & NETIF_F_RXCSUM))
7424 return;
7425
7426 /* TCP/UDP checksum error bit is set */
7427 if (igb_test_staterr(rx_desc,
7428 E1000_RXDEXT_STATERR_TCPE |
7429 E1000_RXDEXT_STATERR_IPE)) {
7430 /*
7431 * work around errata with sctp packets where the TCPE aka
7432 * L4E bit is set incorrectly on 64 byte (60 byte w/o crc)
7433 * packets, (aka let the stack check the crc32c)
7434 */
7435 if (!((skb->len == 60) &&
7436 test_bit(IGB_RING_FLAG_RX_SCTP_CSUM, &ring->flags)))
7437 ring->rx_stats.csum_err++;
7438
7439 /* let the stack verify checksum errors */
7440 return;
7441 }
7442 /* It must be a TCP or UDP packet with a valid checksum */
7443 if (igb_test_staterr(rx_desc, E1000_RXD_STAT_TCPCS |
7444 E1000_RXD_STAT_UDPCS))
7445 skb->ip_summed = CHECKSUM_UNNECESSARY;
7446}
7447
7448#ifdef NETIF_F_RXHASH
7449static inline void igb_rx_hash(struct igb_ring *ring,
7450 union e1000_adv_rx_desc *rx_desc,
7451 struct sk_buff *skb)
7452{
7453 if (netdev_ring(ring)->features & NETIF_F_RXHASH)
7454 skb_set_hash(skb, le32_to_cpu(rx_desc->wb.lower.hi_dword.rss),
7455 PKT_HASH_TYPE_L3);
7456}
7457
7458#endif
7459#ifndef IGB_NO_LRO
7460#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
7461/**
7462 * igb_merge_active_tail - merge active tail into lro skb
7463 * @tail: pointer to active tail in frag_list
7464 *
7465 * This function merges the length and data of an active tail into the
7466 * skb containing the frag_list. It resets the tail's pointer to the head,
7467 * but it leaves the heads pointer to tail intact.
7468 **/
7469static inline struct sk_buff *igb_merge_active_tail(struct sk_buff *tail)
7470{
7471 struct sk_buff *head = IGB_CB(tail)->head;
7472
7473 if (!head)
7474 return tail;
7475
7476 head->len += tail->len;
7477 head->data_len += tail->len;
7478 head->truesize += tail->len;
7479
7480 IGB_CB(tail)->head = NULL;
7481
7482 return head;
7483}
7484
7485/**
7486 * igb_add_active_tail - adds an active tail into the skb frag_list
7487 * @head: pointer to the start of the skb
7488 * @tail: pointer to active tail to add to frag_list
7489 *
7490 * This function adds an active tail to the end of the frag list. This tail
7491 * will still be receiving data so we cannot yet ad it's stats to the main
7492 * skb. That is done via igb_merge_active_tail.
7493 **/
7494static inline void igb_add_active_tail(struct sk_buff *head, struct sk_buff *tail)
7495{
7496 struct sk_buff *old_tail = IGB_CB(head)->tail;
7497
7498 if (old_tail) {
7499 igb_merge_active_tail(old_tail);
7500 old_tail->next = tail;
7501 } else {
7502 skb_shinfo(head)->frag_list = tail;
7503 }
7504
7505 IGB_CB(tail)->head = head;
7506 IGB_CB(head)->tail = tail;
7507
7508 IGB_CB(head)->append_cnt++;
7509}
7510
7511/**
7512 * igb_close_active_frag_list - cleanup pointers on a frag_list skb
7513 * @head: pointer to head of an active frag list
7514 *
7515 * This function will clear the frag_tail_tracker pointer on an active
7516 * frag_list and returns true if the pointer was actually set
7517 **/
7518static inline bool igb_close_active_frag_list(struct sk_buff *head)
7519{
7520 struct sk_buff *tail = IGB_CB(head)->tail;
7521
7522 if (!tail)
7523 return false;
7524
7525 igb_merge_active_tail(tail);
7526
7527 IGB_CB(head)->tail = NULL;
7528
7529 return true;
7530}
7531
7532#endif /* CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT */
7533/**
7534 * igb_can_lro - returns true if packet is TCP/IPV4 and LRO is enabled
7535 * @adapter: board private structure
7536 * @rx_desc: pointer to the rx descriptor
7537 * @skb: pointer to the skb to be merged
7538 *
7539 **/
7540static inline bool igb_can_lro(struct igb_ring *rx_ring,
7541 union e1000_adv_rx_desc *rx_desc,
7542 struct sk_buff *skb)
7543{
7544 struct iphdr *iph = (struct iphdr *)skb->data;
7545 __le16 pkt_info = rx_desc->wb.lower.lo_dword.hs_rss.pkt_info;
7546
7547 /* verify hardware indicates this is IPv4/TCP */
7548 if((!(pkt_info & cpu_to_le16(E1000_RXDADV_PKTTYPE_TCP)) ||
7549 !(pkt_info & cpu_to_le16(E1000_RXDADV_PKTTYPE_IPV4))))
7550 return false;
7551
7552 /* .. and LRO is enabled */
7553 if (!(netdev_ring(rx_ring)->features & NETIF_F_LRO))
7554 return false;
7555
7556 /* .. and we are not in promiscuous mode */
7557 if (netdev_ring(rx_ring)->flags & IFF_PROMISC)
7558 return false;
7559
7560 /* .. and the header is large enough for us to read IP/TCP fields */
7561 if (!pskb_may_pull(skb, sizeof(struct igb_lrohdr)))
7562 return false;
7563
7564 /* .. and there are no VLANs on packet */
7565 if (skb->protocol != __constant_htons(ETH_P_IP))
7566 return false;
7567
7568 /* .. and we are version 4 with no options */
7569 if (*(u8 *)iph != 0x45)
7570 return false;
7571
7572 /* .. and the packet is not fragmented */
7573 if (iph->frag_off & htons(IP_MF | IP_OFFSET))
7574 return false;
7575
7576 /* .. and that next header is TCP */
7577 if (iph->protocol != IPPROTO_TCP)
7578 return false;
7579
7580 return true;
7581}
7582
7583static inline struct igb_lrohdr *igb_lro_hdr(struct sk_buff *skb)
7584{
7585 return (struct igb_lrohdr *)skb->data;
7586}
7587
7588/**
7589 * igb_lro_flush - Indicate packets to upper layer.
7590 *
7591 * Update IP and TCP header part of head skb if more than one
7592 * skb's chained and indicate packets to upper layer.
7593 **/
7594static void igb_lro_flush(struct igb_q_vector *q_vector,
7595 struct sk_buff *skb)
7596{
7597 struct igb_lro_list *lrolist = &q_vector->lrolist;
7598
7599 __skb_unlink(skb, &lrolist->active);
7600
7601 if (IGB_CB(skb)->append_cnt) {
7602 struct igb_lrohdr *lroh = igb_lro_hdr(skb);
7603
7604#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
7605 /* close any active lro contexts */
7606 igb_close_active_frag_list(skb);
7607
7608#endif
7609 /* incorporate ip header and re-calculate checksum */
7610 lroh->iph.tot_len = ntohs(skb->len);
7611 lroh->iph.check = 0;
7612
7613 /* header length is 5 since we know no options exist */
7614 lroh->iph.check = ip_fast_csum((u8 *)lroh, 5);
7615
7616 /* clear TCP checksum to indicate we are an LRO frame */
7617 lroh->th.check = 0;
7618
7619 /* incorporate latest timestamp into the tcp header */
7620 if (IGB_CB(skb)->tsecr) {
7621 lroh->ts[2] = IGB_CB(skb)->tsecr;
7622 lroh->ts[1] = htonl(IGB_CB(skb)->tsval);
7623 }
7624#ifdef NETIF_F_GSO
7625
7626 skb_shinfo(skb)->gso_size = IGB_CB(skb)->mss;
7627 skb_shinfo(skb)->gso_type = SKB_GSO_TCPV4;
7628#endif
7629 }
7630
7631#ifdef HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER
7632 igb_receive_skb(q_vector, skb);
7633#else
7634 napi_gro_receive(&q_vector->napi, skb);
7635#endif
7636 lrolist->stats.flushed++;
7637}
7638
7639static void igb_lro_flush_all(struct igb_q_vector *q_vector)
7640{
7641 struct igb_lro_list *lrolist = &q_vector->lrolist;
7642 struct sk_buff *skb, *tmp;
7643
7644 skb_queue_reverse_walk_safe(&lrolist->active, skb, tmp)
7645 igb_lro_flush(q_vector, skb);
7646}
7647
7648/*
7649 * igb_lro_header_ok - Main LRO function.
7650 **/
7651static void igb_lro_header_ok(struct sk_buff *skb)
7652{
7653 struct igb_lrohdr *lroh = igb_lro_hdr(skb);
7654 u16 opt_bytes, data_len;
7655
7656#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
7657 IGB_CB(skb)->tail = NULL;
7658#endif
7659 IGB_CB(skb)->tsecr = 0;
7660 IGB_CB(skb)->append_cnt = 0;
7661 IGB_CB(skb)->mss = 0;
7662
7663 /* ensure that the checksum is valid */
7664 if (skb->ip_summed != CHECKSUM_UNNECESSARY)
7665 return;
7666
7667 /* If we see CE codepoint in IP header, packet is not mergeable */
7668 if (INET_ECN_is_ce(ipv4_get_dsfield(&lroh->iph)))
7669 return;
7670
7671 /* ensure no bits set besides ack or psh */
7672 if (lroh->th.fin || lroh->th.syn || lroh->th.rst ||
7673 lroh->th.urg || lroh->th.ece || lroh->th.cwr ||
7674 !lroh->th.ack)
7675 return;
7676
7677 /* store the total packet length */
7678 data_len = ntohs(lroh->iph.tot_len);
7679
7680 /* remove any padding from the end of the skb */
7681 __pskb_trim(skb, data_len);
7682
7683 /* remove header length from data length */
7684 data_len -= sizeof(struct igb_lrohdr);
7685
7686 /*
7687 * check for timestamps. Since the only option we handle are timestamps,
7688 * we only have to handle the simple case of aligned timestamps
7689 */
7690 opt_bytes = (lroh->th.doff << 2) - sizeof(struct tcphdr);
7691 if (opt_bytes != 0) {
7692 if ((opt_bytes != TCPOLEN_TSTAMP_ALIGNED) ||
7693 !pskb_may_pull(skb, sizeof(struct igb_lrohdr) +
7694 TCPOLEN_TSTAMP_ALIGNED) ||
7695 (lroh->ts[0] != htonl((TCPOPT_NOP << 24) |
7696 (TCPOPT_NOP << 16) |
7697 (TCPOPT_TIMESTAMP << 8) |
7698 TCPOLEN_TIMESTAMP)) ||
7699 (lroh->ts[2] == 0)) {
7700 return;
7701 }
7702
7703 IGB_CB(skb)->tsval = ntohl(lroh->ts[1]);
7704 IGB_CB(skb)->tsecr = lroh->ts[2];
7705
7706 data_len -= TCPOLEN_TSTAMP_ALIGNED;
7707 }
7708
7709 /* record data_len as mss for the packet */
7710 IGB_CB(skb)->mss = data_len;
7711 IGB_CB(skb)->next_seq = ntohl(lroh->th.seq);
7712}
7713
7714#ifndef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
7715static void igb_merge_frags(struct sk_buff *lro_skb, struct sk_buff *new_skb)
7716{
7717 struct skb_shared_info *sh_info;
7718 struct skb_shared_info *new_skb_info;
7719 unsigned int data_len;
7720
7721 sh_info = skb_shinfo(lro_skb);
7722 new_skb_info = skb_shinfo(new_skb);
7723
7724 /* copy frags into the last skb */
7725 memcpy(sh_info->frags + sh_info->nr_frags,
7726 new_skb_info->frags,
7727 new_skb_info->nr_frags * sizeof(skb_frag_t));
7728
7729 /* copy size data over */
7730 sh_info->nr_frags += new_skb_info->nr_frags;
7731 data_len = IGB_CB(new_skb)->mss;
7732 lro_skb->len += data_len;
7733 lro_skb->data_len += data_len;
7734 lro_skb->truesize += data_len;
7735
7736 /* wipe record of data from new_skb */
7737 new_skb_info->nr_frags = 0;
7738 new_skb->len = new_skb->data_len = 0;
7739 dev_kfree_skb_any(new_skb);
7740}
7741
7742#endif /* CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT */
7743/**
7744 * igb_lro_receive - if able, queue skb into lro chain
7745 * @q_vector: structure containing interrupt and ring information
7746 * @new_skb: pointer to current skb being checked
7747 *
7748 * Checks whether the skb given is eligible for LRO and if that's
7749 * fine chains it to the existing lro_skb based on flowid. If an LRO for
7750 * the flow doesn't exist create one.
7751 **/
7752static void igb_lro_receive(struct igb_q_vector *q_vector,
7753 struct sk_buff *new_skb)
7754{
7755 struct sk_buff *lro_skb;
7756 struct igb_lro_list *lrolist = &q_vector->lrolist;
7757 struct igb_lrohdr *lroh = igb_lro_hdr(new_skb);
7758 __be32 saddr = lroh->iph.saddr;
7759 __be32 daddr = lroh->iph.daddr;
7760 __be32 tcp_ports = *(__be32 *)&lroh->th;
7761 u16 data_len;
7762#ifdef HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER
7763 u16 vid = IGB_CB(new_skb)->vid;
7764#else
7765 u16 vid = new_skb->vlan_tci;
7766#endif
7767
7768 igb_lro_header_ok(new_skb);
7769
7770 /*
7771 * we have a packet that might be eligible for LRO,
7772 * so see if it matches anything we might expect
7773 */
7774 skb_queue_walk(&lrolist->active, lro_skb) {
7775 if (*(__be32 *)&igb_lro_hdr(lro_skb)->th != tcp_ports ||
7776 igb_lro_hdr(lro_skb)->iph.saddr != saddr ||
7777 igb_lro_hdr(lro_skb)->iph.daddr != daddr)
7778 continue;
7779
7780#ifdef HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER
7781 if (IGB_CB(lro_skb)->vid != vid)
7782#else
7783 if (lro_skb->vlan_tci != vid)
7784#endif
7785 continue;
7786
7787 /* out of order packet */
7788 if (IGB_CB(lro_skb)->next_seq != IGB_CB(new_skb)->next_seq) {
7789 igb_lro_flush(q_vector, lro_skb);
7790 IGB_CB(new_skb)->mss = 0;
7791 break;
7792 }
7793
7794 /* TCP timestamp options have changed */
7795 if (!IGB_CB(lro_skb)->tsecr != !IGB_CB(new_skb)->tsecr) {
7796 igb_lro_flush(q_vector, lro_skb);
7797 break;
7798 }
7799
7800 /* make sure timestamp values are increasing */
7801 if (IGB_CB(lro_skb)->tsecr &&
7802 IGB_CB(lro_skb)->tsval > IGB_CB(new_skb)->tsval) {
7803 igb_lro_flush(q_vector, lro_skb);
7804 IGB_CB(new_skb)->mss = 0;
7805 break;
7806 }
7807
7808 data_len = IGB_CB(new_skb)->mss;
7809
7810 /* Check for all of the above below
7811 * malformed header
7812 * no tcp data
7813 * resultant packet would be too large
7814 * new skb is larger than our current mss
7815 * data would remain in header
7816 * we would consume more frags then the sk_buff contains
7817 * ack sequence numbers changed
7818 * window size has changed
7819 */
7820 if (data_len == 0 ||
7821 data_len > IGB_CB(lro_skb)->mss ||
7822 data_len > IGB_CB(lro_skb)->free ||
7823#ifndef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
7824 data_len != new_skb->data_len ||
7825 skb_shinfo(new_skb)->nr_frags >=
7826 (MAX_SKB_FRAGS - skb_shinfo(lro_skb)->nr_frags) ||
7827#endif
7828 igb_lro_hdr(lro_skb)->th.ack_seq != lroh->th.ack_seq ||
7829 igb_lro_hdr(lro_skb)->th.window != lroh->th.window) {
7830 igb_lro_flush(q_vector, lro_skb);
7831 break;
7832 }
7833
7834 /* Remove IP and TCP header*/
7835 skb_pull(new_skb, new_skb->len - data_len);
7836
7837 /* update timestamp and timestamp echo response */
7838 IGB_CB(lro_skb)->tsval = IGB_CB(new_skb)->tsval;
7839 IGB_CB(lro_skb)->tsecr = IGB_CB(new_skb)->tsecr;
7840
7841 /* update sequence and free space */
7842 IGB_CB(lro_skb)->next_seq += data_len;
7843 IGB_CB(lro_skb)->free -= data_len;
7844
7845 /* update append_cnt */
7846 IGB_CB(lro_skb)->append_cnt++;
7847
7848#ifndef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
7849 /* if header is empty pull pages into current skb */
7850 igb_merge_frags(lro_skb, new_skb);
7851#else
7852 /* chain this new skb in frag_list */
7853 igb_add_active_tail(lro_skb, new_skb);
7854#endif
7855
7856 if ((data_len < IGB_CB(lro_skb)->mss) || lroh->th.psh ||
7857 skb_shinfo(lro_skb)->nr_frags == MAX_SKB_FRAGS) {
7858 igb_lro_hdr(lro_skb)->th.psh |= lroh->th.psh;
7859 igb_lro_flush(q_vector, lro_skb);
7860 }
7861
7862 lrolist->stats.coal++;
7863 return;
7864 }
7865
7866 if (IGB_CB(new_skb)->mss && !lroh->th.psh) {
7867 /* if we are at capacity flush the tail */
7868 if (skb_queue_len(&lrolist->active) >= IGB_LRO_MAX) {
7869 lro_skb = skb_peek_tail(&lrolist->active);
7870 if (lro_skb)
7871 igb_lro_flush(q_vector, lro_skb);
7872 }
7873
7874 /* update sequence and free space */
7875 IGB_CB(new_skb)->next_seq += IGB_CB(new_skb)->mss;
7876 IGB_CB(new_skb)->free = 65521 - new_skb->len;
7877
7878 /* .. and insert at the front of the active list */
7879 __skb_queue_head(&lrolist->active, new_skb);
7880
7881 lrolist->stats.coal++;
7882 return;
7883 }
7884
7885 /* packet not handled by any of the above, pass it to the stack */
7886#ifdef HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER
7887 igb_receive_skb(q_vector, new_skb);
7888#else
7889 napi_gro_receive(&q_vector->napi, new_skb);
7890#endif
7891}
7892
7893#endif /* IGB_NO_LRO */
7894/**
7895 * igb_process_skb_fields - Populate skb header fields from Rx descriptor
7896 * @rx_ring: rx descriptor ring packet is being transacted on
7897 * @rx_desc: pointer to the EOP Rx descriptor
7898 * @skb: pointer to current skb being populated
7899 *
7900 * This function checks the ring, descriptor, and packet information in
7901 * order to populate the hash, checksum, VLAN, timestamp, protocol, and
7902 * other fields within the skb.
7903 **/
7904static void igb_process_skb_fields(struct igb_ring *rx_ring,
7905 union e1000_adv_rx_desc *rx_desc,
7906 struct sk_buff *skb)
7907{
7908 struct net_device *dev = rx_ring->netdev;
7909 __le16 pkt_info = rx_desc->wb.lower.lo_dword.hs_rss.pkt_info;
7910
7911#ifdef NETIF_F_RXHASH
7912 igb_rx_hash(rx_ring, rx_desc, skb);
7913
7914#endif
7915 igb_rx_checksum(rx_ring, rx_desc, skb);
7916
7917 /* update packet type stats */
7918 if (pkt_info & cpu_to_le16(E1000_RXDADV_PKTTYPE_IPV4))
7919 rx_ring->rx_stats.ipv4_packets++;
7920 else if (pkt_info & cpu_to_le16(E1000_RXDADV_PKTTYPE_IPV4_EX))
7921 rx_ring->rx_stats.ipv4e_packets++;
7922 else if (pkt_info & cpu_to_le16(E1000_RXDADV_PKTTYPE_IPV6))
7923 rx_ring->rx_stats.ipv6_packets++;
7924 else if (pkt_info & cpu_to_le16(E1000_RXDADV_PKTTYPE_IPV6_EX))
7925 rx_ring->rx_stats.ipv6e_packets++;
7926 else if (pkt_info & cpu_to_le16(E1000_RXDADV_PKTTYPE_TCP))
7927 rx_ring->rx_stats.tcp_packets++;
7928 else if (pkt_info & cpu_to_le16(E1000_RXDADV_PKTTYPE_UDP))
7929 rx_ring->rx_stats.udp_packets++;
7930 else if (pkt_info & cpu_to_le16(E1000_RXDADV_PKTTYPE_SCTP))
7931 rx_ring->rx_stats.sctp_packets++;
7932 else if (pkt_info & cpu_to_le16(E1000_RXDADV_PKTTYPE_NFS))
7933 rx_ring->rx_stats.nfs_packets++;
7934
7935#ifdef HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK
7936 igb_ptp_rx_hwtstamp(rx_ring, rx_desc, skb);
7937#endif /* HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK */
7938
7939#ifdef NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX
7940 if ((dev->features & NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX) &&
7941#else
7942 if ((dev->features & NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_RX) &&
7943#endif
7944 igb_test_staterr(rx_desc, E1000_RXD_STAT_VP)) {
7945 u16 vid = 0;
7946 if (igb_test_staterr(rx_desc, E1000_RXDEXT_STATERR_LB) &&
7947 test_bit(IGB_RING_FLAG_RX_LB_VLAN_BSWAP, &rx_ring->flags))
7948 vid = be16_to_cpu(rx_desc->wb.upper.vlan);
7949 else
7950 vid = le16_to_cpu(rx_desc->wb.upper.vlan);
7951#ifdef HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER
7952 IGB_CB(skb)->vid = vid;
7953 } else {
7954 IGB_CB(skb)->vid = 0;
7955#else
7956
7957#ifdef HAVE_VLAN_PROTOCOL
7958 __vlan_hwaccel_put_tag(skb, htons(ETH_P_8021Q), vid);
7959#else
7960 __vlan_hwaccel_put_tag(skb, htons(ETH_P_8021Q), vid);
7961#endif
7962
7963
7964#endif
7965 }
7966
7967 skb_record_rx_queue(skb, rx_ring->queue_index);
7968
7969 skb->protocol = eth_type_trans(skb, dev);
7970}
7971
7972/**
7973 * igb_is_non_eop - process handling of non-EOP buffers
7974 * @rx_ring: Rx ring being processed
7975 * @rx_desc: Rx descriptor for current buffer
7976 *
7977 * This function updates next to clean. If the buffer is an EOP buffer
7978 * this function exits returning false, otherwise it will place the
7979 * sk_buff in the next buffer to be chained and return true indicating
7980 * that this is in fact a non-EOP buffer.
7981 **/
7982static bool igb_is_non_eop(struct igb_ring *rx_ring,
7983 union e1000_adv_rx_desc *rx_desc)
7984{
7985 u32 ntc = rx_ring->next_to_clean + 1;
7986
7987 /* fetch, update, and store next to clean */
7988 ntc = (ntc < rx_ring->count) ? ntc : 0;
7989 rx_ring->next_to_clean = ntc;
7990
7991 prefetch(IGB_RX_DESC(rx_ring, ntc));
7992
7993 if (likely(igb_test_staterr(rx_desc, E1000_RXD_STAT_EOP)))
7994 return false;
7995
7996 return true;
7997}
7998
7999#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
8000/* igb_clean_rx_irq -- * legacy */
8001static bool igb_clean_rx_irq(struct igb_q_vector *q_vector, int budget)
8002{
8003 struct igb_ring *rx_ring = q_vector->rx.ring;
8004 unsigned int total_bytes = 0, total_packets = 0;
8005 u16 cleaned_count = igb_desc_unused(rx_ring);
8006
8007 do {
8008 struct igb_rx_buffer *rx_buffer;
8009 union e1000_adv_rx_desc *rx_desc;
8010 struct sk_buff *skb;
8011 u16 ntc;
8012
8013 /* return some buffers to hardware, one at a time is too slow */
8014 if (cleaned_count >= IGB_RX_BUFFER_WRITE) {
8015 igb_alloc_rx_buffers(rx_ring, cleaned_count);
8016 cleaned_count = 0;
8017 }
8018
8019 ntc = rx_ring->next_to_clean;
8020 rx_desc = IGB_RX_DESC(rx_ring, ntc);
8021 rx_buffer = &rx_ring->rx_buffer_info[ntc];
8022
8023 if (!igb_test_staterr(rx_desc, E1000_RXD_STAT_DD))
8024 break;
8025
8026 /*
8027 * This memory barrier is needed to keep us from reading
8028 * any other fields out of the rx_desc until we know the
8029 * RXD_STAT_DD bit is set
8030 */
8031 rmb();
8032
8033 skb = rx_buffer->skb;
8034
8035 prefetch(skb->data);
8036
8037 /* pull the header of the skb in */
8038 __skb_put(skb, le16_to_cpu(rx_desc->wb.upper.length));
8039
8040 /* clear skb reference in buffer info structure */
8041 rx_buffer->skb = NULL;
8042
8043 cleaned_count++;
8044
8045 BUG_ON(igb_is_non_eop(rx_ring, rx_desc));
8046
8047 dma_unmap_single(rx_ring->dev, rx_buffer->dma,
8048 rx_ring->rx_buffer_len,
8049 DMA_FROM_DEVICE);
8050 rx_buffer->dma = 0;
8051
8052 if (igb_test_staterr(rx_desc,
8053 E1000_RXDEXT_ERR_FRAME_ERR_MASK)) {
8054 dev_kfree_skb_any(skb);
8055 continue;
8056 }
8057
8058 total_bytes += skb->len;
8059
8060 /* populate checksum, timestamp, VLAN, and protocol */
8061 igb_process_skb_fields(rx_ring, rx_desc, skb);
8062
8063#ifndef IGB_NO_LRO
8064 if (igb_can_lro(rx_ring, rx_desc, skb))
8065 igb_lro_receive(q_vector, skb);
8066 else
8067#endif
8068#ifdef HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER
8069 igb_receive_skb(q_vector, skb);
8070#else
8071 napi_gro_receive(&q_vector->napi, skb);
8072#endif
8073
8074#ifndef NETIF_F_GRO
8075 netdev_ring(rx_ring)->last_rx = jiffies;
8076
8077#endif
8078 /* update budget accounting */
8079 total_packets++;
8080 } while (likely(total_packets < budget));
8081
8082 rx_ring->rx_stats.packets += total_packets;
8083 rx_ring->rx_stats.bytes += total_bytes;
8084 q_vector->rx.total_packets += total_packets;
8085 q_vector->rx.total_bytes += total_bytes;
8086
8087 if (cleaned_count)
8088 igb_alloc_rx_buffers(rx_ring, cleaned_count);
8089
8090#ifndef IGB_NO_LRO
8091 igb_lro_flush_all(q_vector);
8092
8093#endif /* IGB_NO_LRO */
8094 return total_packets < budget;
8095}
8096#else /* CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT */
8097/**
8098 * igb_get_headlen - determine size of header for LRO/GRO
8099 * @data: pointer to the start of the headers
8100 * @max_len: total length of section to find headers in
8101 *
8102 * This function is meant to determine the length of headers that will
8103 * be recognized by hardware for LRO, and GRO offloads. The main
8104 * motivation of doing this is to only perform one pull for IPv4 TCP
8105 * packets so that we can do basic things like calculating the gso_size
8106 * based on the average data per packet.
8107 **/
8108static unsigned int igb_get_headlen(unsigned char *data,
8109 unsigned int max_len)
8110{
8111 union {
8112 unsigned char *network;
8113 /* l2 headers */
8114 struct ethhdr *eth;
8115 struct vlan_hdr *vlan;
8116 /* l3 headers */
8117 struct iphdr *ipv4;
8118 struct ipv6hdr *ipv6;
8119 } hdr;
8120 __be16 protocol;
8121 u8 nexthdr = 0; /* default to not TCP */
8122 u8 hlen;
8123
8124 /* this should never happen, but better safe than sorry */
8125 if (max_len < ETH_HLEN)
8126 return max_len;
8127
8128 /* initialize network frame pointer */
8129 hdr.network = data;
8130
8131 /* set first protocol and move network header forward */
8132 protocol = hdr.eth->h_proto;
8133 hdr.network += ETH_HLEN;
8134
8135 /* handle any vlan tag if present */
8136 if (protocol == __constant_htons(ETH_P_8021Q)) {
8137 if ((hdr.network - data) > (max_len - VLAN_HLEN))
8138 return max_len;
8139
8140 protocol = hdr.vlan->h_vlan_encapsulated_proto;
8141 hdr.network += VLAN_HLEN;
8142 }
8143
8144 /* handle L3 protocols */
8145 if (protocol == __constant_htons(ETH_P_IP)) {
8146 if ((hdr.network - data) > (max_len - sizeof(struct iphdr)))
8147 return max_len;
8148
8149 /* access ihl as a u8 to avoid unaligned access on ia64 */
8150 hlen = (hdr.network[0] & 0x0F) << 2;
8151
8152 /* verify hlen meets minimum size requirements */
8153 if (hlen < sizeof(struct iphdr))
8154 return hdr.network - data;
8155
8156 /* record next protocol if header is present */
8157 if (!(hdr.ipv4->frag_off & htons(IP_OFFSET)))
8158 nexthdr = hdr.ipv4->protocol;
8159#ifdef NETIF_F_TSO6
8160 } else if (protocol == __constant_htons(ETH_P_IPV6)) {
8161 if ((hdr.network - data) > (max_len - sizeof(struct ipv6hdr)))
8162 return max_len;
8163
8164 /* record next protocol */
8165 nexthdr = hdr.ipv6->nexthdr;
8166 hlen = sizeof(struct ipv6hdr);
8167#endif /* NETIF_F_TSO6 */
8168 } else {
8169 return hdr.network - data;
8170 }
8171
8172 /* relocate pointer to start of L4 header */
8173 hdr.network += hlen;
8174
8175 /* finally sort out TCP */
8176 if (nexthdr == IPPROTO_TCP) {
8177 if ((hdr.network - data) > (max_len - sizeof(struct tcphdr)))
8178 return max_len;
8179
8180 /* access doff as a u8 to avoid unaligned access on ia64 */
8181 hlen = (hdr.network[12] & 0xF0) >> 2;
8182
8183 /* verify hlen meets minimum size requirements */
8184 if (hlen < sizeof(struct tcphdr))
8185 return hdr.network - data;
8186
8187 hdr.network += hlen;
8188 } else if (nexthdr == IPPROTO_UDP) {
8189 if ((hdr.network - data) > (max_len - sizeof(struct udphdr)))
8190 return max_len;
8191
8192 hdr.network += sizeof(struct udphdr);
8193 }
8194
8195 /*
8196 * If everything has gone correctly hdr.network should be the
8197 * data section of the packet and will be the end of the header.
8198 * If not then it probably represents the end of the last recognized
8199 * header.
8200 */
8201 if ((hdr.network - data) < max_len)
8202 return hdr.network - data;
8203 else
8204 return max_len;
8205}
8206
8207/**
8208 * igb_pull_tail - igb specific version of skb_pull_tail
8209 * @rx_ring: rx descriptor ring packet is being transacted on
8210 * @rx_desc: pointer to the EOP Rx descriptor
8211 * @skb: pointer to current skb being adjusted
8212 *
8213 * This function is an igb specific version of __pskb_pull_tail. The
8214 * main difference between this version and the original function is that
8215 * this function can make several assumptions about the state of things
8216 * that allow for significant optimizations versus the standard function.
8217 * As a result we can do things like drop a frag and maintain an accurate
8218 * truesize for the skb.
8219 */
8220static void igb_pull_tail(struct igb_ring *rx_ring,
8221 union e1000_adv_rx_desc *rx_desc,
8222 struct sk_buff *skb)
8223{
8224 struct skb_frag_struct *frag = &skb_shinfo(skb)->frags[0];
8225 unsigned char *va;
8226 unsigned int pull_len;
8227
8228 /*
8229 * it is valid to use page_address instead of kmap since we are
8230 * working with pages allocated out of the lomem pool per
8231 * alloc_page(GFP_ATOMIC)
8232 */
8233 va = skb_frag_address(frag);
8234
8235#ifdef HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK
8236 if (igb_test_staterr(rx_desc, E1000_RXDADV_STAT_TSIP)) {
8237 /* retrieve timestamp from buffer */
8238 igb_ptp_rx_pktstamp(rx_ring->q_vector, va, skb);
8239
8240 /* update pointers to remove timestamp header */
8241 skb_frag_size_sub(frag, IGB_TS_HDR_LEN);
8242 frag->page_offset += IGB_TS_HDR_LEN;
8243 skb->data_len -= IGB_TS_HDR_LEN;
8244 skb->len -= IGB_TS_HDR_LEN;
8245
8246 /* move va to start of packet data */
8247 va += IGB_TS_HDR_LEN;
8248 }
8249#endif /* HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK */
8250
8251 /*
8252 * we need the header to contain the greater of either ETH_HLEN or
8253 * 60 bytes if the skb->len is less than 60 for skb_pad.
8254 */
8255 pull_len = igb_get_headlen(va, IGB_RX_HDR_LEN);
8256
8257 /* align pull length to size of long to optimize memcpy performance */
8258 skb_copy_to_linear_data(skb, va, ALIGN(pull_len, sizeof(long)));
8259
8260 /* update all of the pointers */
8261 skb_frag_size_sub(frag, pull_len);
8262 frag->page_offset += pull_len;
8263 skb->data_len -= pull_len;
8264 skb->tail += pull_len;
8265}
8266
8267/**
8268 * igb_cleanup_headers - Correct corrupted or empty headers
8269 * @rx_ring: rx descriptor ring packet is being transacted on
8270 * @rx_desc: pointer to the EOP Rx descriptor
8271 * @skb: pointer to current skb being fixed
8272 *
8273 * Address the case where we are pulling data in on pages only
8274 * and as such no data is present in the skb header.
8275 *
8276 * In addition if skb is not at least 60 bytes we need to pad it so that
8277 * it is large enough to qualify as a valid Ethernet frame.
8278 *
8279 * Returns true if an error was encountered and skb was freed.
8280 **/
8281static bool igb_cleanup_headers(struct igb_ring *rx_ring,
8282 union e1000_adv_rx_desc *rx_desc,
8283 struct sk_buff *skb)
8284{
8285
8286 if (unlikely((igb_test_staterr(rx_desc,
8287 E1000_RXDEXT_ERR_FRAME_ERR_MASK)))) {
8288 struct net_device *netdev = rx_ring->netdev;
8289 if (!(netdev->features & NETIF_F_RXALL)) {
8290 dev_kfree_skb_any(skb);
8291 return true;
8292 }
8293 }
8294
8295 /* place header in linear portion of buffer */
8296 if (skb_is_nonlinear(skb))
8297 igb_pull_tail(rx_ring, rx_desc, skb);
8298
8299 /* if skb_pad returns an error the skb was freed */
8300 if (unlikely(skb->len < 60)) {
8301 int pad_len = 60 - skb->len;
8302
8303 if (skb_pad(skb, pad_len))
8304 return true;
8305 __skb_put(skb, pad_len);
8306 }
8307
8308 return false;
8309}
8310
8311/* igb_clean_rx_irq -- * packet split */
8312static bool igb_clean_rx_irq(struct igb_q_vector *q_vector, int budget)
8313{
8314 struct igb_ring *rx_ring = q_vector->rx.ring;
8315 struct sk_buff *skb = rx_ring->skb;
8316 unsigned int total_bytes = 0, total_packets = 0;
8317 u16 cleaned_count = igb_desc_unused(rx_ring);
8318
8319 do {
8320 union e1000_adv_rx_desc *rx_desc;
8321
8322 /* return some buffers to hardware, one at a time is too slow */
8323 if (cleaned_count >= IGB_RX_BUFFER_WRITE) {
8324 igb_alloc_rx_buffers(rx_ring, cleaned_count);
8325 cleaned_count = 0;
8326 }
8327
8328 rx_desc = IGB_RX_DESC(rx_ring, rx_ring->next_to_clean);
8329
8330 if (!igb_test_staterr(rx_desc, E1000_RXD_STAT_DD))
8331 break;
8332
8333 /*
8334 * This memory barrier is needed to keep us from reading
8335 * any other fields out of the rx_desc until we know the
8336 * RXD_STAT_DD bit is set
8337 */
8338 rmb();
8339
8340 /* retrieve a buffer from the ring */
8341 skb = igb_fetch_rx_buffer(rx_ring, rx_desc, skb);
8342
8343 /* exit if we failed to retrieve a buffer */
8344 if (!skb)
8345 break;
8346
8347 cleaned_count++;
8348
8349 /* fetch next buffer in frame if non-eop */
8350 if (igb_is_non_eop(rx_ring, rx_desc))
8351 continue;
8352
8353 /* verify the packet layout is correct */
8354 if (igb_cleanup_headers(rx_ring, rx_desc, skb)) {
8355 skb = NULL;
8356 continue;
8357 }
8358
8359 /* probably a little skewed due to removing CRC */
8360 total_bytes += skb->len;
8361
8362 /* populate checksum, timestamp, VLAN, and protocol */
8363 igb_process_skb_fields(rx_ring, rx_desc, skb);
8364
8365#ifndef IGB_NO_LRO
8366 if (igb_can_lro(rx_ring, rx_desc, skb))
8367 igb_lro_receive(q_vector, skb);
8368 else
8369#endif
8370#ifdef HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER
8371 igb_receive_skb(q_vector, skb);
8372#else
8373 napi_gro_receive(&q_vector->napi, skb);
8374#endif
8375#ifndef NETIF_F_GRO
8376
8377 netdev_ring(rx_ring)->last_rx = jiffies;
8378#endif
8379
8380 /* reset skb pointer */
8381 skb = NULL;
8382
8383 /* update budget accounting */
8384 total_packets++;
8385 } while (likely(total_packets < budget));
8386
8387 /* place incomplete frames back on ring for completion */
8388 rx_ring->skb = skb;
8389
8390 rx_ring->rx_stats.packets += total_packets;
8391 rx_ring->rx_stats.bytes += total_bytes;
8392 q_vector->rx.total_packets += total_packets;
8393 q_vector->rx.total_bytes += total_bytes;
8394
8395 if (cleaned_count)
8396 igb_alloc_rx_buffers(rx_ring, cleaned_count);
8397
8398#ifndef IGB_NO_LRO
8399 igb_lro_flush_all(q_vector);
8400
8401#endif /* IGB_NO_LRO */
8402 return total_packets < budget;
8403}
8404#endif /* CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT */
8405
8406#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
8407static bool igb_alloc_mapped_skb(struct igb_ring *rx_ring,
8408 struct igb_rx_buffer *bi)
8409{
8410 struct sk_buff *skb = bi->skb;
8411 dma_addr_t dma = bi->dma;
8412
8413 if (dma)
8414 return true;
8415
8416 if (likely(!skb)) {
8417 skb = netdev_alloc_skb_ip_align(netdev_ring(rx_ring),
8418 rx_ring->rx_buffer_len);
8419 bi->skb = skb;
8420 if (!skb) {
8421 rx_ring->rx_stats.alloc_failed++;
8422 return false;
8423 }
8424
8425 /* initialize skb for ring */
8426 skb_record_rx_queue(skb, ring_queue_index(rx_ring));
8427 }
8428
8429 dma = dma_map_single(rx_ring->dev, skb->data,
8430 rx_ring->rx_buffer_len, DMA_FROM_DEVICE);
8431
8432 /* if mapping failed free memory back to system since
8433 * there isn't much point in holding memory we can't use
8434 */
8435 if (dma_mapping_error(rx_ring->dev, dma)) {
8436 dev_kfree_skb_any(skb);
8437 bi->skb = NULL;
8438
8439 rx_ring->rx_stats.alloc_failed++;
8440 return false;
8441 }
8442
8443 bi->dma = dma;
8444 return true;
8445}
8446
8447#else /* CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT */
8448static bool igb_alloc_mapped_page(struct igb_ring *rx_ring,
8449 struct igb_rx_buffer *bi)
8450{
8451 struct page *page = bi->page;
8452 dma_addr_t dma;
8453
8454 /* since we are recycling buffers we should seldom need to alloc */
8455 if (likely(page))
8456 return true;
8457
8458 /* alloc new page for storage */
8459 page = alloc_page(GFP_ATOMIC | __GFP_COLD);
8460 if (unlikely(!page)) {
8461 rx_ring->rx_stats.alloc_failed++;
8462 return false;
8463 }
8464
8465 /* map page for use */
8466 dma = dma_map_page(rx_ring->dev, page, 0, PAGE_SIZE, DMA_FROM_DEVICE);
8467
8468 /*
8469 * if mapping failed free memory back to system since
8470 * there isn't much point in holding memory we can't use
8471 */
8472 if (dma_mapping_error(rx_ring->dev, dma)) {
8473 __free_page(page);
8474
8475 rx_ring->rx_stats.alloc_failed++;
8476 return false;
8477 }
8478
8479 bi->dma = dma;
8480 bi->page = page;
8481 bi->page_offset = 0;
8482
8483 return true;
8484}
8485
8486#endif /* CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT */
8487/**
8488 * igb_alloc_rx_buffers - Replace used receive buffers; packet split
8489 * @adapter: address of board private structure
8490 **/
8491void igb_alloc_rx_buffers(struct igb_ring *rx_ring, u16 cleaned_count)
8492{
8493 union e1000_adv_rx_desc *rx_desc;
8494 struct igb_rx_buffer *bi;
8495 u16 i = rx_ring->next_to_use;
8496
8497 /* nothing to do */
8498 if (!cleaned_count)
8499 return;
8500
8501 rx_desc = IGB_RX_DESC(rx_ring, i);
8502 bi = &rx_ring->rx_buffer_info[i];
8503 i -= rx_ring->count;
8504
8505 do {
8506#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
8507 if (!igb_alloc_mapped_skb(rx_ring, bi))
8508#else
8509 if (!igb_alloc_mapped_page(rx_ring, bi))
8510#endif /* CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT */
8511 break;
8512
8513 /*
8514 * Refresh the desc even if buffer_addrs didn't change
8515 * because each write-back erases this info.
8516 */
8517#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
8518 rx_desc->read.pkt_addr = cpu_to_le64(bi->dma);
8519#else
8520 rx_desc->read.pkt_addr = cpu_to_le64(bi->dma + bi->page_offset);
8521#endif
8522
8523 rx_desc++;
8524 bi++;
8525 i++;
8526 if (unlikely(!i)) {
8527 rx_desc = IGB_RX_DESC(rx_ring, 0);
8528 bi = rx_ring->rx_buffer_info;
8529 i -= rx_ring->count;
8530 }
8531
8532 /* clear the hdr_addr for the next_to_use descriptor */
8533 rx_desc->read.hdr_addr = 0;
8534
8535 cleaned_count--;
8536 } while (cleaned_count);
8537
8538 i += rx_ring->count;
8539
8540 if (rx_ring->next_to_use != i) {
8541 /* record the next descriptor to use */
8542 rx_ring->next_to_use = i;
8543
8544#ifndef CONFIG_IGB_DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
8545 /* update next to alloc since we have filled the ring */
8546 rx_ring->next_to_alloc = i;
8547
8548#endif
8549 /*
8550 * Force memory writes to complete before letting h/w
8551 * know there are new descriptors to fetch. (Only
8552 * applicable for weak-ordered memory model archs,
8553 * such as IA-64).
8554 */
8555 wmb();
8556 writel(i, rx_ring->tail);
8557 }
8558}
8559
8560#ifdef SIOCGMIIPHY
8561/**
8562 * igb_mii_ioctl -
8563 * @netdev:
8564 * @ifreq:
8565 * @cmd:
8566 **/
8567static int igb_mii_ioctl(struct net_device *netdev, struct ifreq *ifr, int cmd)
8568{
8569 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8570 struct mii_ioctl_data *data = if_mii(ifr);
8571
8572 if (adapter->hw.phy.media_type != e1000_media_type_copper)
8573 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
8574
8575 switch (cmd) {
8576 case SIOCGMIIPHY:
8577 data->phy_id = adapter->hw.phy.addr;
8578 break;
8579 case SIOCGMIIREG:
8580 if (!capable(CAP_NET_ADMIN))
8581 return -EPERM;
8582 if (e1000_read_phy_reg(&adapter->hw, data->reg_num & 0x1F,
8583 &data->val_out))
8584 return -EIO;
8585 break;
8586 case SIOCSMIIREG:
8587 default:
8588 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
8589 }
8590 return E1000_SUCCESS;
8591}
8592
8593#endif
8594/**
8595 * igb_ioctl -
8596 * @netdev:
8597 * @ifreq:
8598 * @cmd:
8599 **/
8600static int igb_ioctl(struct net_device *netdev, struct ifreq *ifr, int cmd)
8601{
8602 switch (cmd) {
8603#ifdef SIOCGMIIPHY
8604 case SIOCGMIIPHY:
8605 case SIOCGMIIREG:
8606 case SIOCSMIIREG:
8607 return igb_mii_ioctl(netdev, ifr, cmd);
8608#endif
8609#ifdef HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK
8610 case SIOCSHWTSTAMP:
8611 return igb_ptp_hwtstamp_ioctl(netdev, ifr, cmd);
8612#endif /* HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK */
8613#ifdef ETHTOOL_OPS_COMPAT
8614 case SIOCETHTOOL:
8615 return ethtool_ioctl(ifr);
8616#endif
8617 default:
8618 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
8619 }
8620}
8621
8622s32 e1000_read_pcie_cap_reg(struct e1000_hw *hw, u32 reg, u16 *value)
8623{
8624 struct igb_adapter *adapter = hw->back;
8625 u16 cap_offset;
8626
8627 cap_offset = pci_find_capability(adapter->pdev, PCI_CAP_ID_EXP);
8628 if (!cap_offset)
8629 return -E1000_ERR_CONFIG;
8630
8631 pci_read_config_word(adapter->pdev, cap_offset + reg, value);
8632
8633 return E1000_SUCCESS;
8634}
8635
8636s32 e1000_write_pcie_cap_reg(struct e1000_hw *hw, u32 reg, u16 *value)
8637{
8638 struct igb_adapter *adapter = hw->back;
8639 u16 cap_offset;
8640
8641 cap_offset = pci_find_capability(adapter->pdev, PCI_CAP_ID_EXP);
8642 if (!cap_offset)
8643 return -E1000_ERR_CONFIG;
8644
8645 pci_write_config_word(adapter->pdev, cap_offset + reg, *value);
8646
8647 return E1000_SUCCESS;
8648}
8649
8650#ifdef HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER
8651static void igb_vlan_mode(struct net_device *netdev, struct vlan_group *vlgrp)
8652#else
8653void igb_vlan_mode(struct net_device *netdev, u32 features)
8654#endif
8655{
8656 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8657 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
8658 u32 ctrl, rctl;
8659 int i;
8660#ifdef HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER
8661 bool enable = !!vlgrp;
8662
8663 igb_irq_disable(adapter);
8664
8665 adapter->vlgrp = vlgrp;
8666
8667 if (!test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state))
8668 igb_irq_enable(adapter);
8669#else
8670#ifdef NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX
8671 bool enable = !!(features & NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX);
8672#else
8673 bool enable = !!(features & NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_RX);
8674#endif
8675#endif
8676
8677 if (enable) {
8678 /* enable VLAN tag insert/strip */
8679 ctrl = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL);
8680 ctrl |= E1000_CTRL_VME;
8681 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL, ctrl);
8682
8683 /* Disable CFI check */
8684 rctl = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RCTL);
8685 rctl &= ~E1000_RCTL_CFIEN;
8686 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RCTL, rctl);
8687 } else {
8688 /* disable VLAN tag insert/strip */
8689 ctrl = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL);
8690 ctrl &= ~E1000_CTRL_VME;
8691 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL, ctrl);
8692 }
8693
8694#ifndef CONFIG_IGB_VMDQ_NETDEV
8695 for (i = 0; i < adapter->vmdq_pools; i++) {
8696 igb_set_vf_vlan_strip(adapter,
8697 adapter->vfs_allocated_count + i,
8698 enable);
8699 }
8700
8701#else
8702 igb_set_vf_vlan_strip(adapter,
8703 adapter->vfs_allocated_count,
8704 enable);
8705
8706 for (i = 1; i < adapter->vmdq_pools; i++) {
8707#ifdef HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER
8708 struct igb_vmdq_adapter *vadapter;
8709 vadapter = netdev_priv(adapter->vmdq_netdev[i-1]);
8710 enable = !!vadapter->vlgrp;
8711#else
8712 struct net_device *vnetdev;
8713 vnetdev = adapter->vmdq_netdev[i-1];
8714#ifdef NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX
8715 enable = !!(vnetdev->features & NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX);
8716#else
8717 enable = !!(vnetdev->features & NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_RX);
8718#endif
8719#endif
8720 igb_set_vf_vlan_strip(adapter,
8721 adapter->vfs_allocated_count + i,
8722 enable);
8723 }
8724
8725#endif
8726 igb_rlpml_set(adapter);
8727}
8728
8729#ifdef HAVE_VLAN_PROTOCOL
8730static int igb_vlan_rx_add_vid(struct net_device *netdev, __be16 proto, u16 vid)
8731#elif defined HAVE_INT_NDO_VLAN_RX_ADD_VID
8732#ifdef NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX
8733static int igb_vlan_rx_add_vid(struct net_device *netdev,
8734 __always_unused __be16 proto, u16 vid)
8735#else
8736static int igb_vlan_rx_add_vid(struct net_device *netdev, u16 vid)
8737#endif
8738#else
8739static void igb_vlan_rx_add_vid(struct net_device *netdev, u16 vid)
8740#endif
8741{
8742 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8743 int pf_id = adapter->vfs_allocated_count;
8744
8745 /* attempt to add filter to vlvf array */
8746 igb_vlvf_set(adapter, vid, TRUE, pf_id);
8747
8748 /* add the filter since PF can receive vlans w/o entry in vlvf */
8749 igb_vfta_set(adapter, vid, TRUE);
8750#ifndef HAVE_NETDEV_VLAN_FEATURES
8751
8752 /* Copy feature flags from netdev to the vlan netdev for this vid.
8753 * This allows things like TSO to bubble down to our vlan device.
8754 * There is no need to update netdev for vlan 0 (DCB), since it
8755 * wouldn't has v_netdev.
8756 */
8757 if (adapter->vlgrp) {
8758 struct vlan_group *vlgrp = adapter->vlgrp;
8759 struct net_device *v_netdev = vlan_group_get_device(vlgrp, vid);
8760 if (v_netdev) {
8761 v_netdev->features |= netdev->features;
8762 vlan_group_set_device(vlgrp, vid, v_netdev);
8763 }
8764 }
8765#endif
8766#ifndef HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER
8767
8768 set_bit(vid, adapter->active_vlans);
8769#endif
8770#ifdef HAVE_INT_NDO_VLAN_RX_ADD_VID
8771 return 0;
8772#endif
8773}
8774
8775#ifdef HAVE_VLAN_PROTOCOL
8776static int igb_vlan_rx_kill_vid(struct net_device *netdev, __be16 proto, u16 vid)
8777#elif defined HAVE_INT_NDO_VLAN_RX_ADD_VID
8778#ifdef NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX
8779static int igb_vlan_rx_kill_vid(struct net_device *netdev,
8780 __always_unused __be16 proto, u16 vid)
8781#else
8782static int igb_vlan_rx_kill_vid(struct net_device *netdev, u16 vid)
8783#endif
8784#else
8785static void igb_vlan_rx_kill_vid(struct net_device *netdev, u16 vid)
8786#endif
8787{
8788 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8789 int pf_id = adapter->vfs_allocated_count;
8790 s32 err;
8791
8792#ifdef HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER
8793 igb_irq_disable(adapter);
8794
8795 vlan_group_set_device(adapter->vlgrp, vid, NULL);
8796
8797 if (!test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state))
8798 igb_irq_enable(adapter);
8799
8800#endif /* HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER */
8801 /* remove vlan from VLVF table array */
8802 err = igb_vlvf_set(adapter, vid, FALSE, pf_id);
8803
8804 /* if vid was not present in VLVF just remove it from table */
8805 if (err)
8806 igb_vfta_set(adapter, vid, FALSE);
8807#ifndef HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER
8808
8809 clear_bit(vid, adapter->active_vlans);
8810#endif
8811#ifdef HAVE_INT_NDO_VLAN_RX_ADD_VID
8812 return 0;
8813#endif
8814}
8815
8816static void igb_restore_vlan(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
8817{
8818#ifdef HAVE_VLAN_RX_REGISTER
8819 igb_vlan_mode(adapter->netdev, adapter->vlgrp);
8820
8821 if (adapter->vlgrp) {
8822 u16 vid;
8823 for (vid = 0; vid < VLAN_N_VID; vid++) {
8824 if (!vlan_group_get_device(adapter->vlgrp, vid))
8825 continue;
8826#ifdef NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX
8827 igb_vlan_rx_add_vid(adapter->netdev,
8828 htons(ETH_P_8021Q), vid);
8829#else
8830 igb_vlan_rx_add_vid(adapter->netdev, vid);
8831#endif
8832 }
8833 }
8834#else
8835 u16 vid;
8836
8837 igb_vlan_mode(adapter->netdev, adapter->netdev->features);
8838
8839 for_each_set_bit(vid, adapter->active_vlans, VLAN_N_VID)
8840#ifdef NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX
8841 igb_vlan_rx_add_vid(adapter->netdev,
8842 htons(ETH_P_8021Q), vid);
8843#else
8844 igb_vlan_rx_add_vid(adapter->netdev, vid);
8845#endif
8846#endif
8847}
8848
8849int igb_set_spd_dplx(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u16 spddplx)
8850{
8851 struct pci_dev *pdev = adapter->pdev;
8852 struct e1000_mac_info *mac = &adapter->hw.mac;
8853
8854 mac->autoneg = 0;
8855
8856 /* SerDes device's does not support 10Mbps Full/duplex
8857 * and 100Mbps Half duplex
8858 */
8859 if (adapter->hw.phy.media_type == e1000_media_type_internal_serdes) {
8860 switch (spddplx) {
8861 case SPEED_10 + DUPLEX_HALF:
8862 case SPEED_10 + DUPLEX_FULL:
8863 case SPEED_100 + DUPLEX_HALF:
8864 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev),
8865 "Unsupported Speed/Duplex configuration\n");
8866 return -EINVAL;
8867 default:
8868 break;
8869 }
8870 }
8871
8872 switch (spddplx) {
8873 case SPEED_10 + DUPLEX_HALF:
8874 mac->forced_speed_duplex = ADVERTISE_10_HALF;
8875 break;
8876 case SPEED_10 + DUPLEX_FULL:
8877 mac->forced_speed_duplex = ADVERTISE_10_FULL;
8878 break;
8879 case SPEED_100 + DUPLEX_HALF:
8880 mac->forced_speed_duplex = ADVERTISE_100_HALF;
8881 break;
8882 case SPEED_100 + DUPLEX_FULL:
8883 mac->forced_speed_duplex = ADVERTISE_100_FULL;
8884 break;
8885 case SPEED_1000 + DUPLEX_FULL:
8886 mac->autoneg = 1;
8887 adapter->hw.phy.autoneg_advertised = ADVERTISE_1000_FULL;
8888 break;
8889 case SPEED_1000 + DUPLEX_HALF: /* not supported */
8890 default:
8891 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "Unsupported Speed/Duplex configuration\n");
8892 return -EINVAL;
8893 }
8894
8895 /* clear MDI, MDI(-X) override is only allowed when autoneg enabled */
8896 adapter->hw.phy.mdix = AUTO_ALL_MODES;
8897
8898 return 0;
8899}
8900
8901static int __igb_shutdown(struct pci_dev *pdev, bool *enable_wake,
8902 bool runtime)
8903{
8904 struct net_device *netdev = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
8905 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
8906 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
8907 u32 ctrl, rctl, status;
8908 u32 wufc = runtime ? E1000_WUFC_LNKC : adapter->wol;
8909#ifdef CONFIG_PM
8910 int retval = 0;
8911#endif
8912
8913 netif_device_detach(netdev);
8914
8915 status = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_STATUS);
8916 if (status & E1000_STATUS_LU)
8917 wufc &= ~E1000_WUFC_LNKC;
8918
8919 if (netif_running(netdev))
8920 __igb_close(netdev, true);
8921
8922 igb_clear_interrupt_scheme(adapter);
8923
8924#ifdef CONFIG_PM
8925 retval = pci_save_state(pdev);
8926 if (retval)
8927 return retval;
8928#endif
8929
8930 if (wufc) {
8931 igb_setup_rctl(adapter);
8932 igb_set_rx_mode(netdev);
8933
8934 /* turn on all-multi mode if wake on multicast is enabled */
8935 if (wufc & E1000_WUFC_MC) {
8936 rctl = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RCTL);
8937 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_MPE;
8938 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RCTL, rctl);
8939 }
8940
8941 ctrl = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL);
8942 /* phy power management enable */
8943 #define E1000_CTRL_EN_PHY_PWR_MGMT 0x00200000
8944 ctrl |= E1000_CTRL_ADVD3WUC;
8945 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL, ctrl);
8946
8947 /* Allow time for pending master requests to run */
8948 e1000_disable_pcie_master(hw);
8949
8950 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_WUC, E1000_WUC_PME_EN);
8951 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_WUFC, wufc);
8952 } else {
8953 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_WUC, 0);
8954 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_WUFC, 0);
8955 }
8956
8957 *enable_wake = wufc || adapter->en_mng_pt;
8958 if (!*enable_wake)
8959 igb_power_down_link(adapter);
8960 else
8961 igb_power_up_link(adapter);
8962
8963 /* Release control of h/w to f/w. If f/w is AMT enabled, this
8964 * would have already happened in close and is redundant. */
8965 igb_release_hw_control(adapter);
8966
8967 pci_disable_device(pdev);
8968
8969 return 0;
8970}
8971
8972#ifdef CONFIG_PM
8973#ifdef HAVE_SYSTEM_SLEEP_PM_OPS
8974static int igb_suspend(struct device *dev)
8975#else
8976static int igb_suspend(struct pci_dev *pdev, pm_message_t state)
8977#endif /* HAVE_SYSTEM_SLEEP_PM_OPS */
8978{
8979#ifdef HAVE_SYSTEM_SLEEP_PM_OPS
8980 struct pci_dev *pdev = to_pci_dev(dev);
8981#endif /* HAVE_SYSTEM_SLEEP_PM_OPS */
8982 int retval;
8983 bool wake;
8984
8985 retval = __igb_shutdown(pdev, &wake, 0);
8986 if (retval)
8987 return retval;
8988
8989 if (wake) {
8990 pci_prepare_to_sleep(pdev);
8991 } else {
8992 pci_wake_from_d3(pdev, false);
8993 pci_set_power_state(pdev, PCI_D3hot);
8994 }
8995
8996 return 0;
8997}
8998
8999#ifdef HAVE_SYSTEM_SLEEP_PM_OPS
9000static int igb_resume(struct device *dev)
9001#else
9002static int igb_resume(struct pci_dev *pdev)
9003#endif /* HAVE_SYSTEM_SLEEP_PM_OPS */
9004{
9005#ifdef HAVE_SYSTEM_SLEEP_PM_OPS
9006 struct pci_dev *pdev = to_pci_dev(dev);
9007#endif /* HAVE_SYSTEM_SLEEP_PM_OPS */
9008 struct net_device *netdev = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
9009 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
9010 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
9011 u32 err;
9012
9013 pci_set_power_state(pdev, PCI_D0);
9014 pci_restore_state(pdev);
9015 pci_save_state(pdev);
9016
9017 err = pci_enable_device_mem(pdev);
9018 if (err) {
9019 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev),
9020 "igb: Cannot enable PCI device from suspend\n");
9021 return err;
9022 }
9023 pci_set_master(pdev);
9024
9025 pci_enable_wake(pdev, PCI_D3hot, 0);
9026 pci_enable_wake(pdev, PCI_D3cold, 0);
9027
9028 if (igb_init_interrupt_scheme(adapter, true)) {
9029 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "Unable to allocate memory for queues\n");
9030 return -ENOMEM;
9031 }
9032
9033 igb_reset(adapter);
9034
9035 /* let the f/w know that the h/w is now under the control of the
9036 * driver. */
9037 igb_get_hw_control(adapter);
9038
9039 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_WUS, ~0);
9040
9041 if (netdev->flags & IFF_UP) {
9042 rtnl_lock();
9043 err = __igb_open(netdev, true);
9044 rtnl_unlock();
9045 if (err)
9046 return err;
9047 }
9048
9049 netif_device_attach(netdev);
9050
9051 return 0;
9052}
9053
9054#ifdef CONFIG_PM_RUNTIME
9055#ifdef HAVE_SYSTEM_SLEEP_PM_OPS
9056static int igb_runtime_idle(struct device *dev)
9057{
9058 struct pci_dev *pdev = to_pci_dev(dev);
9059 struct net_device *netdev = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
9060 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
9061
9062 if (!igb_has_link(adapter))
9063 pm_schedule_suspend(dev, MSEC_PER_SEC * 5);
9064
9065 return -EBUSY;
9066}
9067
9068static int igb_runtime_suspend(struct device *dev)
9069{
9070 struct pci_dev *pdev = to_pci_dev(dev);
9071 int retval;
9072 bool wake;
9073
9074 retval = __igb_shutdown(pdev, &wake, 1);
9075 if (retval)
9076 return retval;
9077
9078 if (wake) {
9079 pci_prepare_to_sleep(pdev);
9080 } else {
9081 pci_wake_from_d3(pdev, false);
9082 pci_set_power_state(pdev, PCI_D3hot);
9083 }
9084
9085 return 0;
9086}
9087
9088static int igb_runtime_resume(struct device *dev)
9089{
9090 return igb_resume(dev);
9091}
9092#endif /* HAVE_SYSTEM_SLEEP_PM_OPS */
9093#endif /* CONFIG_PM_RUNTIME */
9094#endif /* CONFIG_PM */
9095
9096#ifdef USE_REBOOT_NOTIFIER
9097/* only want to do this for 2.4 kernels? */
9098static int igb_notify_reboot(struct notifier_block *nb, unsigned long event,
9099 void *p)
9100{
9101 struct pci_dev *pdev = NULL;
9102 bool wake;
9103
9104 switch (event) {
9105 case SYS_DOWN:
9106 case SYS_HALT:
9107 case SYS_POWER_OFF:
9108 while ((pdev = pci_find_device(PCI_ANY_ID, PCI_ANY_ID, pdev))) {
9109 if (pci_dev_driver(pdev) == &igb_driver) {
9110 __igb_shutdown(pdev, &wake, 0);
9111 if (event == SYS_POWER_OFF) {
9112 pci_wake_from_d3(pdev, wake);
9113 pci_set_power_state(pdev, PCI_D3hot);
9114 }
9115 }
9116 }
9117 }
9118 return NOTIFY_DONE;
9119}
9120#else
9121static void igb_shutdown(struct pci_dev *pdev)
9122{
9123 bool wake = false;
9124
9125 __igb_shutdown(pdev, &wake, 0);
9126
9127 if (system_state == SYSTEM_POWER_OFF) {
9128 pci_wake_from_d3(pdev, wake);
9129 pci_set_power_state(pdev, PCI_D3hot);
9130 }
9131}
9132#endif /* USE_REBOOT_NOTIFIER */
9133
9134#ifdef CONFIG_NET_POLL_CONTROLLER
9135/*
9136 * Polling 'interrupt' - used by things like netconsole to send skbs
9137 * without having to re-enable interrupts. It's not called while
9138 * the interrupt routine is executing.
9139 */
9140static void igb_netpoll(struct net_device *netdev)
9141{
9142 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
9143 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
9144 struct igb_q_vector *q_vector;
9145 int i;
9146
9147 for (i = 0; i < adapter->num_q_vectors; i++) {
9148 q_vector = adapter->q_vector[i];
9149 if (adapter->msix_entries)
9150 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_EIMC, q_vector->eims_value);
9151 else
9152 igb_irq_disable(adapter);
9153 napi_schedule(&q_vector->napi);
9154 }
9155}
9156#endif /* CONFIG_NET_POLL_CONTROLLER */
9157
9158#ifdef HAVE_PCI_ERS
9159#define E1000_DEV_ID_82576_VF 0x10CA
9160/**
9161 * igb_io_error_detected - called when PCI error is detected
9162 * @pdev: Pointer to PCI device
9163 * @state: The current pci connection state
9164 *
9165 * This function is called after a PCI bus error affecting
9166 * this device has been detected.
9167 */
9168static pci_ers_result_t igb_io_error_detected(struct pci_dev *pdev,
9169 pci_channel_state_t state)
9170{
9171 struct net_device *netdev = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
9172 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
9173
9174#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_IOV__UNUSED
9175 struct pci_dev *bdev, *vfdev;
9176 u32 dw0, dw1, dw2, dw3;
9177 int vf, pos;
9178 u16 req_id, pf_func;
9179
9180 if (!(adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_DETECT_BAD_DMA))
9181 goto skip_bad_vf_detection;
9182
9183 bdev = pdev->bus->self;
9184 while (bdev && (pci_pcie_type(bdev) != PCI_EXP_TYPE_ROOT_PORT))
9185 bdev = bdev->bus->self;
9186
9187 if (!bdev)
9188 goto skip_bad_vf_detection;
9189
9190 pos = pci_find_ext_capability(bdev, PCI_EXT_CAP_ID_ERR);
9191 if (!pos)
9192 goto skip_bad_vf_detection;
9193
9194 pci_read_config_dword(bdev, pos + PCI_ERR_HEADER_LOG, &dw0);
9195 pci_read_config_dword(bdev, pos + PCI_ERR_HEADER_LOG + 4, &dw1);
9196 pci_read_config_dword(bdev, pos + PCI_ERR_HEADER_LOG + 8, &dw2);
9197 pci_read_config_dword(bdev, pos + PCI_ERR_HEADER_LOG + 12, &dw3);
9198
9199 req_id = dw1 >> 16;
9200 /* On the 82576 if bit 7 of the requestor ID is set then it's a VF */
9201 if (!(req_id & 0x0080))
9202 goto skip_bad_vf_detection;
9203
9204 pf_func = req_id & 0x01;
9205 if ((pf_func & 1) == (pdev->devfn & 1)) {
9206
9207 vf = (req_id & 0x7F) >> 1;
9208 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev),
9209 "VF %d has caused a PCIe error\n", vf);
9210 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev),
9211 "TLP: dw0: %8.8x\tdw1: %8.8x\tdw2: "
9212 "%8.8x\tdw3: %8.8x\n",
9213 dw0, dw1, dw2, dw3);
9214
9215 /* Find the pci device of the offending VF */
9216 vfdev = pci_get_device(PCI_VENDOR_ID_INTEL,
9217 E1000_DEV_ID_82576_VF, NULL);
9218 while (vfdev) {
9219 if (vfdev->devfn == (req_id & 0xFF))
9220 break;
9221 vfdev = pci_get_device(PCI_VENDOR_ID_INTEL,
9222 E1000_DEV_ID_82576_VF, vfdev);
9223 }
9224 /*
9225 * There's a slim chance the VF could have been hot plugged,
9226 * so if it is no longer present we don't need to issue the
9227 * VFLR. Just clean up the AER in that case.
9228 */
9229 if (vfdev) {
9230 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev),
9231 "Issuing VFLR to VF %d\n", vf);
9232 pci_write_config_dword(vfdev, 0xA8, 0x00008000);
9233 }
9234
9235 pci_cleanup_aer_uncorrect_error_status(pdev);
9236 }
9237
9238 /*
9239 * Even though the error may have occurred on the other port
9240 * we still need to increment the vf error reference count for
9241 * both ports because the I/O resume function will be called
9242 * for both of them.
9243 */
9244 adapter->vferr_refcount++;
9245
9246 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_RECOVERED;
9247
9248skip_bad_vf_detection:
9249#endif /* CONFIG_PCI_IOV */
9250
9251 netif_device_detach(netdev);
9252
9253 if (state == pci_channel_io_perm_failure)
9254 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_DISCONNECT;
9255
9256 if (netif_running(netdev))
9257 igb_down(adapter);
9258 pci_disable_device(pdev);
9259
9260 /* Request a slot slot reset. */
9261 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_NEED_RESET;
9262}
9263
9264/**
9265 * igb_io_slot_reset - called after the pci bus has been reset.
9266 * @pdev: Pointer to PCI device
9267 *
9268 * Restart the card from scratch, as if from a cold-boot. Implementation
9269 * resembles the first-half of the igb_resume routine.
9270 */
9271static pci_ers_result_t igb_io_slot_reset(struct pci_dev *pdev)
9272{
9273 struct net_device *netdev = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
9274 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
9275 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
9276 pci_ers_result_t result;
9277
9278 if (pci_enable_device_mem(pdev)) {
9279 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev),
9280 "Cannot re-enable PCI device after reset.\n");
9281 result = PCI_ERS_RESULT_DISCONNECT;
9282 } else {
9283 pci_set_master(pdev);
9284 pci_restore_state(pdev);
9285 pci_save_state(pdev);
9286
9287 pci_enable_wake(pdev, PCI_D3hot, 0);
9288 pci_enable_wake(pdev, PCI_D3cold, 0);
9289
9290 schedule_work(&adapter->reset_task);
9291 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_WUS, ~0);
9292 result = PCI_ERS_RESULT_RECOVERED;
9293 }
9294
9295 pci_cleanup_aer_uncorrect_error_status(pdev);
9296
9297 return result;
9298}
9299
9300/**
9301 * igb_io_resume - called when traffic can start flowing again.
9302 * @pdev: Pointer to PCI device
9303 *
9304 * This callback is called when the error recovery driver tells us that
9305 * its OK to resume normal operation. Implementation resembles the
9306 * second-half of the igb_resume routine.
9307 */
9308static void igb_io_resume(struct pci_dev *pdev)
9309{
9310 struct net_device *netdev = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
9311 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
9312
9313 if (adapter->vferr_refcount) {
9314 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "Resuming after VF err\n");
9315 adapter->vferr_refcount--;
9316 return;
9317 }
9318
9319 if (netif_running(netdev)) {
9320 if (igb_up(adapter)) {
9321 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "igb_up failed after reset\n");
9322 return;
9323 }
9324 }
9325
9326 netif_device_attach(netdev);
9327
9328 /* let the f/w know that the h/w is now under the control of the
9329 * driver. */
9330 igb_get_hw_control(adapter);
9331}
9332
9333#endif /* HAVE_PCI_ERS */
9334
9335int igb_add_mac_filter(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u8 *addr, u16 queue)
9336{
9337 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
9338 int i;
9339
9340 if (is_zero_ether_addr(addr))
9341 return 0;
9342
9343 for (i = 0; i < hw->mac.rar_entry_count; i++) {
9344 if (adapter->mac_table[i].state & IGB_MAC_STATE_IN_USE)
9345 continue;
9346 adapter->mac_table[i].state = (IGB_MAC_STATE_MODIFIED |
9347 IGB_MAC_STATE_IN_USE);
9348 memcpy(adapter->mac_table[i].addr, addr, ETH_ALEN);
9349 adapter->mac_table[i].queue = queue;
9350 igb_sync_mac_table(adapter);
9351 return 0;
9352 }
9353 return -ENOMEM;
9354}
9355int igb_del_mac_filter(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u8* addr, u16 queue)
9356{
9357 /* search table for addr, if found, set to 0 and sync */
9358 int i;
9359 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
9360
9361 if (is_zero_ether_addr(addr))
9362 return 0;
9363 for (i = 0; i < hw->mac.rar_entry_count; i++) {
9364 if (ether_addr_equal(addr, adapter->mac_table[i].addr) &&
9365 adapter->mac_table[i].queue == queue) {
9366 adapter->mac_table[i].state = IGB_MAC_STATE_MODIFIED;
9367 memset(adapter->mac_table[i].addr, 0, ETH_ALEN);
9368 adapter->mac_table[i].queue = 0;
9369 igb_sync_mac_table(adapter);
9370 return 0;
9371 }
9372 }
9373 return -ENOMEM;
9374}
9375static int igb_set_vf_mac(struct igb_adapter *adapter,
9376 int vf, unsigned char *mac_addr)
9377{
9378 igb_del_mac_filter(adapter, adapter->vf_data[vf].vf_mac_addresses, vf);
9379 memcpy(adapter->vf_data[vf].vf_mac_addresses, mac_addr, ETH_ALEN);
9380
9381 igb_add_mac_filter(adapter, mac_addr, vf);
9382
9383 return 0;
9384}
9385
9386#ifdef IFLA_VF_MAX
9387static int igb_ndo_set_vf_mac(struct net_device *netdev, int vf, u8 *mac)
9388{
9389 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
9390 if (!is_valid_ether_addr(mac) || (vf >= adapter->vfs_allocated_count))
9391 return -EINVAL;
9392 adapter->vf_data[vf].flags |= IGB_VF_FLAG_PF_SET_MAC;
9393 dev_info(&adapter->pdev->dev, "setting MAC %pM on VF %d\n", mac, vf);
9394 dev_info(&adapter->pdev->dev, "Reload the VF driver to make this"
9395 " change effective.\n");
9396 if (test_bit(__IGB_DOWN, &adapter->state)) {
9397 dev_warn(&adapter->pdev->dev, "The VF MAC address has been set,"
9398 " but the PF device is not up.\n");
9399 dev_warn(&adapter->pdev->dev, "Bring the PF device up before"
9400 " attempting to use the VF device.\n");
9401 }
9402 return igb_set_vf_mac(adapter, vf, mac);
9403}
9404
9405static int igb_link_mbps(int internal_link_speed)
9406{
9407 switch (internal_link_speed) {
9408 case SPEED_100:
9409 return 100;
9410 case SPEED_1000:
9411 return 1000;
9412 case SPEED_2500:
9413 return 2500;
9414 default:
9415 return 0;
9416 }
9417}
9418
9419static void igb_set_vf_rate_limit(struct e1000_hw *hw, int vf, int tx_rate,
9420 int link_speed)
9421{
9422 int rf_dec, rf_int;
9423 u32 bcnrc_val;
9424
9425 if (tx_rate != 0) {
9426 /* Calculate the rate factor values to set */
9427 rf_int = link_speed / tx_rate;
9428 rf_dec = (link_speed - (rf_int * tx_rate));
9429 rf_dec = (rf_dec * (1<<E1000_RTTBCNRC_RF_INT_SHIFT)) / tx_rate;
9430
9431 bcnrc_val = E1000_RTTBCNRC_RS_ENA;
9432 bcnrc_val |= ((rf_int<<E1000_RTTBCNRC_RF_INT_SHIFT) &
9433 E1000_RTTBCNRC_RF_INT_MASK);
9434 bcnrc_val |= (rf_dec & E1000_RTTBCNRC_RF_DEC_MASK);
9435 } else {
9436 bcnrc_val = 0;
9437 }
9438
9439 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RTTDQSEL, vf); /* vf X uses queue X */
9440 /*
9441 * Set global transmit compensation time to the MMW_SIZE in RTTBCNRM
