9442 * register. MMW_SIZE=0x014 if 9728-byte jumbo is supported.
9443 */
9444 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RTTBCNRM(0), 0x14);
9445 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RTTBCNRC, bcnrc_val);
9446}
9447
9448static void igb_check_vf_rate_limit(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
9449{
9450 int actual_link_speed, i;
9451 bool reset_rate = false;
9452
9453 /* VF TX rate limit was not set */
9454 if ((adapter->vf_rate_link_speed == 0) ||
9455 (adapter->hw.mac.type != e1000_82576))
9456 return;
9457
9458 actual_link_speed = igb_link_mbps(adapter->link_speed);
9459 if (actual_link_speed != adapter->vf_rate_link_speed) {
9460 reset_rate = true;
9461 adapter->vf_rate_link_speed = 0;
9462 dev_info(&adapter->pdev->dev,
9463 "Link speed has been changed. VF Transmit rate is disabled\n");
9464 }
9465
9466 for (i = 0; i < adapter->vfs_allocated_count; i++) {
9467 if (reset_rate)
9468 adapter->vf_data[i].tx_rate = 0;
9469
9470 igb_set_vf_rate_limit(&adapter->hw, i,
9471 adapter->vf_data[i].tx_rate, actual_link_speed);
9472 }
9473}
9474
9475#ifdef HAVE_VF_MIN_MAX_TXRATE
9476static int igb_ndo_set_vf_bw(struct net_device *netdev, int vf, int min_tx_rate,
9477 int tx_rate)
9478#else /* HAVE_VF_MIN_MAX_TXRATE */
9479static int igb_ndo_set_vf_bw(struct net_device *netdev, int vf, int tx_rate)
9480#endif /* HAVE_VF_MIN_MAX_TXRATE */
9481{
9482 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
9483 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
9484 int actual_link_speed;
9485
9486 if (hw->mac.type != e1000_82576)
9487 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
9488
9489#ifdef HAVE_VF_MIN_MAX_TXRATE
9490 if (min_tx_rate)
9491 return -EINVAL;
9492#endif /* HAVE_VF_MIN_MAX_TXRATE */
9493
9494 actual_link_speed = igb_link_mbps(adapter->link_speed);
9495 if ((vf >= adapter->vfs_allocated_count) ||
9496 (!(E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_STATUS) & E1000_STATUS_LU)) ||
9497 (tx_rate < 0) || (tx_rate > actual_link_speed))
9498 return -EINVAL;
9499
9500 adapter->vf_rate_link_speed = actual_link_speed;
9501 adapter->vf_data[vf].tx_rate = (u16)tx_rate;
9502 igb_set_vf_rate_limit(hw, vf, tx_rate, actual_link_speed);
9503
9504 return 0;
9505}
9506
9507static int igb_ndo_get_vf_config(struct net_device *netdev,
9508 int vf, struct ifla_vf_info *ivi)
9509{
9510 struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
9511 if (vf >= adapter->vfs_allocated_count)
9512 return -EINVAL;
9513 ivi->vf = vf;
9514 memcpy(&ivi->mac, adapter->vf_data[vf].vf_mac_addresses, ETH_ALEN);
9515#ifdef HAVE_VF_MIN_MAX_TXRATE
9516 ivi->max_tx_rate = adapter->vf_data[vf].tx_rate;
9517 ivi->min_tx_rate = 0;
9518#else /* HAVE_VF_MIN_MAX_TXRATE */
9519 ivi->tx_rate = adapter->vf_data[vf].tx_rate;
9520#endif /* HAVE_VF_MIN_MAX_TXRATE */
9521 ivi->vlan = adapter->vf_data[vf].pf_vlan;
9522 ivi->qos = adapter->vf_data[vf].pf_qos;
9523#ifdef HAVE_VF_SPOOFCHK_CONFIGURE
9524 ivi->spoofchk = adapter->vf_data[vf].spoofchk_enabled;
9525#endif
9526 return 0;
9527}
9528#endif
9529static void igb_vmm_control(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
9530{
9531 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
9532 int count;
9533 u32 reg;
9534
9535 switch (hw->mac.type) {
9536 case e1000_82575:
9537 default:
9538 /* replication is not supported for 82575 */
9539 return;
9540 case e1000_82576:
9541 /* notify HW that the MAC is adding vlan tags */
9542 reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_DTXCTL);
9543 reg |= (E1000_DTXCTL_VLAN_ADDED |
9544 E1000_DTXCTL_SPOOF_INT);
9545 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_DTXCTL, reg);
9546 case e1000_82580:
9547 /* enable replication vlan tag stripping */
9548 reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RPLOLR);
9549 reg |= E1000_RPLOLR_STRVLAN;
9550 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RPLOLR, reg);
9551 case e1000_i350:
9552 case e1000_i354:
9553 /* none of the above registers are supported by i350 */
9554 break;
9555 }
9556
9557 /* Enable Malicious Driver Detection */
9558 if ((adapter->vfs_allocated_count) &&
9559 (adapter->mdd)) {
9560 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_i350)
9561 igb_enable_mdd(adapter);
9562 }
9563
9564 /* enable replication and loopback support */
9565 count = adapter->vfs_allocated_count || adapter->vmdq_pools;
9566 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_LOOPBACK_ENABLE && count)
9567 e1000_vmdq_set_loopback_pf(hw, 1);
9568 e1000_vmdq_set_anti_spoofing_pf(hw,
9569 adapter->vfs_allocated_count || adapter->vmdq_pools,
9570 adapter->vfs_allocated_count);
9571 e1000_vmdq_set_replication_pf(hw, adapter->vfs_allocated_count ||
9572 adapter->vmdq_pools);
9573}
9574
9575static void igb_init_fw(struct igb_adapter *adapter)
9576{
9577 struct e1000_fw_drv_info fw_cmd;
9578 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
9579 int i;
9580 u16 mask;
9581
9582 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_i210)
9583 mask = E1000_SWFW_EEP_SM;
9584 else
9585 mask = E1000_SWFW_PHY0_SM;
9586 /* i211 parts do not support this feature */
9587 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_i211)
9588 hw->mac.arc_subsystem_valid = false;
9589
9590 if (!hw->mac.ops.acquire_swfw_sync(hw, mask)) {
9591 for (i = 0; i <= FW_MAX_RETRIES; i++) {
9592 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_FWSTS, E1000_FWSTS_FWRI);
9593 fw_cmd.hdr.cmd = FW_CMD_DRV_INFO;
9594 fw_cmd.hdr.buf_len = FW_CMD_DRV_INFO_LEN;
9595 fw_cmd.hdr.cmd_or_resp.cmd_resv = FW_CMD_RESERVED;
9596 fw_cmd.port_num = hw->bus.func;
9597 fw_cmd.drv_version = FW_FAMILY_DRV_VER;
9598 fw_cmd.hdr.checksum = 0;
9599 fw_cmd.hdr.checksum = e1000_calculate_checksum((u8 *)&fw_cmd,
9600 (FW_HDR_LEN +
9601 fw_cmd.hdr.buf_len));
9602 e1000_host_interface_command(hw, (u8*)&fw_cmd,
9603 sizeof(fw_cmd));
9604 if (fw_cmd.hdr.cmd_or_resp.ret_status == FW_STATUS_SUCCESS)
9605 break;
9606 }
9607 } else
9608 dev_warn(pci_dev_to_dev(adapter->pdev),
9609 "Unable to get semaphore, firmware init failed.\n");
9610 hw->mac.ops.release_swfw_sync(hw, mask);
9611}
9612
9613static void igb_init_dmac(struct igb_adapter *adapter, u32 pba)
9614{
9615 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
9616 u32 dmac_thr;
9617 u16 hwm;
9618 u32 status;
9619
9620 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_i211)
9621 return;
9622
9623 if (hw->mac.type > e1000_82580) {
9624 if (adapter->dmac != IGB_DMAC_DISABLE) {
9625 u32 reg;
9626
9627 /* force threshold to 0. */
9628 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_DMCTXTH, 0);
9629
9630 /*
9631 * DMA Coalescing high water mark needs to be greater
9632 * than the Rx threshold. Set hwm to PBA - max frame
9633 * size in 16B units, capping it at PBA - 6KB.
9634 */
9635 hwm = 64 * pba - adapter->max_frame_size / 16;
9636 if (hwm < 64 * (pba - 6))
9637 hwm = 64 * (pba - 6);
9638 reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_FCRTC);
9639 reg &= ~E1000_FCRTC_RTH_COAL_MASK;
9640 reg |= ((hwm << E1000_FCRTC_RTH_COAL_SHIFT)
9641 & E1000_FCRTC_RTH_COAL_MASK);
9642 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_FCRTC, reg);
9643
9644 /*
9645 * Set the DMA Coalescing Rx threshold to PBA - 2 * max
9646 * frame size, capping it at PBA - 10KB.
9647 */
9648 dmac_thr = pba - adapter->max_frame_size / 512;
9649 if (dmac_thr < pba - 10)
9650 dmac_thr = pba - 10;
9651 reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_DMACR);
9652 reg &= ~E1000_DMACR_DMACTHR_MASK;
9653 reg |= ((dmac_thr << E1000_DMACR_DMACTHR_SHIFT)
9654 & E1000_DMACR_DMACTHR_MASK);
9655
9656 /* transition to L0x or L1 if available..*/
9657 reg |= (E1000_DMACR_DMAC_EN | E1000_DMACR_DMAC_LX_MASK);
9658
9659 /* Check if status is 2.5Gb backplane connection
9660 * before configuration of watchdog timer, which is
9661 * in msec values in 12.8usec intervals
9662 * watchdog timer= msec values in 32usec intervals
9663 * for non 2.5Gb connection
9664 */
9665 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_i354) {
9666 status = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_STATUS);
9667 if ((status & E1000_STATUS_2P5_SKU) &&
9668 (!(status & E1000_STATUS_2P5_SKU_OVER)))
9669 reg |= ((adapter->dmac * 5) >> 6);
9670 else
9671 reg |= ((adapter->dmac) >> 5);
9672 } else {
9673 reg |= ((adapter->dmac) >> 5);
9674 }
9675
9676 /*
9677 * Disable BMC-to-OS Watchdog enable
9678 * on devices that support OS-to-BMC
9679 */
9680 if (hw->mac.type != e1000_i354)
9681 reg &= ~E1000_DMACR_DC_BMC2OSW_EN;
9682 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_DMACR, reg);
9683
9684 /* no lower threshold to disable coalescing(smart fifb)-UTRESH=0*/
9685 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_DMCRTRH, 0);
9686
9687 /* This sets the time to wait before requesting
9688 * transition to low power state to number of usecs
9689 * needed to receive 1 512 byte frame at gigabit
9690 * line rate. On i350 device, time to make transition
9691 * to Lx state is delayed by 4 usec with flush disable
9692 * bit set to avoid losing mailbox interrupts
9693 */
9694 reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_DMCTLX);
9695 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_i350)
9696 reg |= IGB_DMCTLX_DCFLUSH_DIS;
9697
9698 /* in 2.5Gb connection, TTLX unit is 0.4 usec
9699 * which is 0x4*2 = 0xA. But delay is still 4 usec
9700 */
9701 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_i354) {
9702 status = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_STATUS);
9703 if ((status & E1000_STATUS_2P5_SKU) &&
9704 (!(status & E1000_STATUS_2P5_SKU_OVER)))
9705 reg |= 0xA;
9706 else
9707 reg |= 0x4;
9708 } else {
9709 reg |= 0x4;
9710 }
9711 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_DMCTLX, reg);
9712
9713 /* free space in tx packet buffer to wake from DMA coal */
9714 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_DMCTXTH, (IGB_MIN_TXPBSIZE -
9715 (IGB_TX_BUF_4096 + adapter->max_frame_size)) >> 6);
9716
9717 /* make low power state decision controlled by DMA coal */
9718 reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PCIEMISC);
9719 reg &= ~E1000_PCIEMISC_LX_DECISION;
9720 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_PCIEMISC, reg);
9721 } /* endif adapter->dmac is not disabled */
9722 } else if (hw->mac.type == e1000_82580) {
9723 u32 reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PCIEMISC);
9724 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_PCIEMISC,
9725 reg & ~E1000_PCIEMISC_LX_DECISION);
9726 E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_DMACR, 0);
9727 }
9728}
9729
9730#ifdef HAVE_I2C_SUPPORT
9731/* igb_read_i2c_byte - Reads 8 bit word over I2C
9732 * @hw: pointer to hardware structure
9733 * @byte_offset: byte offset to read
9734 * @dev_addr: device address
9735 * @data: value read
9736 *
9737 * Performs byte read operation over I2C interface at
9738 * a specified device address.
9739 */
9740s32 igb_read_i2c_byte(struct e1000_hw *hw, u8 byte_offset,
9741 u8 dev_addr, u8 *data)
9742{
9743 struct igb_adapter *adapter = container_of(hw, struct igb_adapter, hw);
9744 struct i2c_client *this_client = adapter->i2c_client;
9745 s32 status;
9746 u16 swfw_mask = 0;
9747
9748 if (!this_client)
9749 return E1000_ERR_I2C;
9750
9751 swfw_mask = E1000_SWFW_PHY0_SM;
9752
9753 if (hw->mac.ops.acquire_swfw_sync(hw, swfw_mask)
9754 != E1000_SUCCESS)
9755 return E1000_ERR_SWFW_SYNC;
9756
9757 status = i2c_smbus_read_byte_data(this_client, byte_offset);
9758 hw->mac.ops.release_swfw_sync(hw, swfw_mask);
9759
9760 if (status < 0)
9761 return E1000_ERR_I2C;
9762 else {
9763 *data = status;
9764 return E1000_SUCCESS;
9765 }
9766}
9767
9768/* igb_write_i2c_byte - Writes 8 bit word over I2C
9769 * @hw: pointer to hardware structure
9770 * @byte_offset: byte offset to write
9771 * @dev_addr: device address
9772 * @data: value to write
9773 *
9774 * Performs byte write operation over I2C interface at
9775 * a specified device address.
9776 */
9777s32 igb_write_i2c_byte(struct e1000_hw *hw, u8 byte_offset,
9778 u8 dev_addr, u8 data)
9779{
9780 struct igb_adapter *adapter = container_of(hw, struct igb_adapter, hw);
9781 struct i2c_client *this_client = adapter->i2c_client;
9782 s32 status;
9783 u16 swfw_mask = E1000_SWFW_PHY0_SM;
9784
9785 if (!this_client)
9786 return E1000_ERR_I2C;
9787
9788 if (hw->mac.ops.acquire_swfw_sync(hw, swfw_mask) != E1000_SUCCESS)
9789 return E1000_ERR_SWFW_SYNC;
9790 status = i2c_smbus_write_byte_data(this_client, byte_offset, data);
9791 hw->mac.ops.release_swfw_sync(hw, swfw_mask);
9792
9793 if (status)
9794 return E1000_ERR_I2C;
9795 else
9796 return E1000_SUCCESS;
9797}
9798#endif /* HAVE_I2C_SUPPORT */
9799/* igb_main.c */
9800
9801
9802/**
9803 * igb_probe - Device Initialization Routine
9804 * @pdev: PCI device information struct
9805 * @ent: entry in igb_pci_tbl
9806 *
9807 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
9808 *
9809 * igb_probe initializes an adapter identified by a pci_dev structure.
9810 * The OS initialization, configuring of the adapter private structure,
9811 * and a hardware reset occur.
9812 **/
9813int igb_kni_probe(struct pci_dev *pdev,
9814 struct net_device **lad_dev)
9815{
9816 struct net_device *netdev;
9817 struct igb_adapter *adapter;
9818 struct e1000_hw *hw;
9819 u16 eeprom_data = 0;
9820 u8 pba_str[E1000_PBANUM_LENGTH];
9821 s32 ret_val;
9822 static int global_quad_port_a; /* global quad port a indication */
9823 int i, err, pci_using_dac = 0;
9824 static int cards_found;
9825
9826 err = pci_enable_device_mem(pdev);
9827 if (err)
9828 return err;
9829
9830#ifdef NO_KNI
9831 pci_using_dac = 0;
9832 err = dma_set_mask(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), DMA_BIT_MASK(64));
9833 if (!err) {
9834 err = dma_set_coherent_mask(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), DMA_BIT_MASK(64));
9835 if (!err)
9836 pci_using_dac = 1;
9837 } else {
9838 err = dma_set_mask(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), DMA_BIT_MASK(32));
9839 if (err) {
9840 err = dma_set_coherent_mask(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), DMA_BIT_MASK(32));
9841 if (err) {
9842 IGB_ERR("No usable DMA configuration, "
9843 "aborting\n");
9844 goto err_dma;
9845 }
9846 }
9847 }
9848
9849#ifndef HAVE_ASPM_QUIRKS
9850 /* 82575 requires that the pci-e link partner disable the L0s state */
9851 switch (pdev->device) {
9852 case E1000_DEV_ID_82575EB_COPPER:
9853 case E1000_DEV_ID_82575EB_FIBER_SERDES:
9854 case E1000_DEV_ID_82575GB_QUAD_COPPER:
9855 pci_disable_link_state(pdev, PCIE_LINK_STATE_L0S);
9856 default:
9857 break;
9858 }
9859
9860#endif /* HAVE_ASPM_QUIRKS */
9861 err = pci_request_selected_regions(pdev,
9862 pci_select_bars(pdev,
9863 IORESOURCE_MEM),
9864 igb_driver_name);
9865 if (err)
9866 goto err_pci_reg;
9867
9868 pci_enable_pcie_error_reporting(pdev);
9869
9870 pci_set_master(pdev);
9871
9872 err = -ENOMEM;
9873#endif /* NO_KNI */
9874#ifdef HAVE_TX_MQ
9875 netdev = alloc_etherdev_mq(sizeof(struct igb_adapter),
9876 IGB_MAX_TX_QUEUES);
9877#else
9878 netdev = alloc_etherdev(sizeof(struct igb_adapter));
9879#endif /* HAVE_TX_MQ */
9880 if (!netdev)
9881 goto err_alloc_etherdev;
9882
9883 SET_MODULE_OWNER(netdev);
9884 SET_NETDEV_DEV(netdev, &pdev->dev);
9885
9886 //pci_set_drvdata(pdev, netdev);
9887 adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
9888 adapter->netdev = netdev;
9889 adapter->pdev = pdev;
9890 hw = &adapter->hw;
9891 hw->back = adapter;
9892 adapter->port_num = hw->bus.func;
9893 adapter->msg_enable = (1 << debug) - 1;
9894
9895#ifdef HAVE_PCI_ERS
9896 err = pci_save_state(pdev);
9897 if (err)
9898 goto err_ioremap;
9899#endif
9900 err = -EIO;
9901 hw->hw_addr = ioremap(pci_resource_start(pdev, 0),
9902 pci_resource_len(pdev, 0));
9903 if (!hw->hw_addr)
9904 goto err_ioremap;
9905
9906#ifdef HAVE_NET_DEVICE_OPS
9907 netdev->netdev_ops = &igb_netdev_ops;
9908#else /* HAVE_NET_DEVICE_OPS */
9909 netdev->open = &igb_open;
9910 netdev->stop = &igb_close;
9911 netdev->get_stats = &igb_get_stats;
9912#ifdef HAVE_SET_RX_MODE
9913 netdev->set_rx_mode = &igb_set_rx_mode;
9914#endif
9915 netdev->set_multicast_list = &igb_set_rx_mode;
9916 netdev->set_mac_address = &igb_set_mac;
9917 netdev->change_mtu = &igb_change_mtu;
9918 netdev->do_ioctl = &igb_ioctl;
9919#ifdef HAVE_TX_TIMEOUT
9920 netdev->tx_timeout = &igb_tx_timeout;
9921#endif
9922 netdev->vlan_rx_register = igb_vlan_mode;
9923 netdev->vlan_rx_add_vid = igb_vlan_rx_add_vid;
9924 netdev->vlan_rx_kill_vid = igb_vlan_rx_kill_vid;
9925#ifdef CONFIG_NET_POLL_CONTROLLER
9926 netdev->poll_controller = igb_netpoll;
9927#endif
9928 netdev->hard_start_xmit = &igb_xmit_frame;
9929#endif /* HAVE_NET_DEVICE_OPS */
9930 igb_set_ethtool_ops(netdev);
9931#ifdef HAVE_TX_TIMEOUT
9932 netdev->watchdog_timeo = 5 * HZ;
9933#endif
9934
9935 strncpy(netdev->name, pci_name(pdev), sizeof(netdev->name) - 1);
9936
9937 adapter->bd_number = cards_found;
9938
9939 /* setup the private structure */
9940 err = igb_sw_init(adapter);
9941 if (err)
9942 goto err_sw_init;
9943
9944 e1000_get_bus_info(hw);
9945
9946 hw->phy.autoneg_wait_to_complete = FALSE;
9947 hw->mac.adaptive_ifs = FALSE;
9948
9949 /* Copper options */
9950 if (hw->phy.media_type == e1000_media_type_copper) {
9951 hw->phy.mdix = AUTO_ALL_MODES;
9952 hw->phy.disable_polarity_correction = FALSE;
9953 hw->phy.ms_type = e1000_ms_hw_default;
9954 }
9955
9956 if (e1000_check_reset_block(hw))
9957 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev),
9958 "PHY reset is blocked due to SOL/IDER session.\n");
9959
9960 /*
9961 * features is initialized to 0 in allocation, it might have bits
9962 * set by igb_sw_init so we should use an or instead of an
9963 * assignment.
9964 */
9965 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_SG |
9966 NETIF_F_IP_CSUM |
9967#ifdef NETIF_F_IPV6_CSUM
9968 NETIF_F_IPV6_CSUM |
9969#endif
9970#ifdef NETIF_F_TSO
9971 NETIF_F_TSO |
9972#ifdef NETIF_F_TSO6
9973 NETIF_F_TSO6 |
9974#endif
9975#endif /* NETIF_F_TSO */
9976#ifdef NETIF_F_RXHASH
9977 NETIF_F_RXHASH |
9978#endif
9979 NETIF_F_RXCSUM |
9980#ifdef NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX
9981 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX |
9982 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_TX;
9983#else
9984 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_RX |
9985 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_TX;
9986#endif
9987
9988 if (hw->mac.type >= e1000_82576)
9989 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_SCTP_CSUM;
9990
9991#ifdef HAVE_NDO_SET_FEATURES
9992 /* copy netdev features into list of user selectable features */
9993 netdev->hw_features |= netdev->features;
9994#ifndef IGB_NO_LRO
9995
9996 /* give us the option of enabling LRO later */
9997 netdev->hw_features |= NETIF_F_LRO;
9998#endif
9999#else
10000#ifdef NETIF_F_GRO
10001
10002 /* this is only needed on kernels prior to 2.6.39 */
10003 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_GRO;
10004#endif
10005#endif
10006
10007 /* set this bit last since it cannot be part of hw_features */
10008#ifdef NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_FILTER
10009 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_FILTER;
10010#else
10011 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_FILTER;
10012#endif
10013
10014#ifdef HAVE_NETDEV_VLAN_FEATURES
10015 netdev->vlan_features |= NETIF_F_TSO |
10016 NETIF_F_TSO6 |
10017 NETIF_F_IP_CSUM |
10018 NETIF_F_IPV6_CSUM |
10019 NETIF_F_SG;
10020
10021#endif
10022 if (pci_using_dac)
10023 netdev->features |= NETIF_F_HIGHDMA;
10024
10025#ifdef NO_KNI
10026 adapter->en_mng_pt = e1000_enable_mng_pass_thru(hw);
10027#ifdef DEBUG
10028 if (adapter->dmac != IGB_DMAC_DISABLE)
10029 printk("%s: DMA Coalescing is enabled..\n", netdev->name);
10030#endif
10031
10032 /* before reading the NVM, reset the controller to put the device in a
10033 * known good starting state */
10034 e1000_reset_hw(hw);
10035#endif /* NO_KNI */
10036
10037 /* make sure the NVM is good */
10038 if (e1000_validate_nvm_checksum(hw) < 0) {
10039 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "The NVM Checksum Is Not"
10040 " Valid\n");
10041 err = -EIO;
10042 goto err_eeprom;
10043 }
10044
10045 /* copy the MAC address out of the NVM */
10046 if (e1000_read_mac_addr(hw))
10047 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "NVM Read Error\n");
10048 memcpy(netdev->dev_addr, hw->mac.addr, netdev->addr_len);
10049#ifdef ETHTOOL_GPERMADDR
10050 memcpy(netdev->perm_addr, hw->mac.addr, netdev->addr_len);
10051
10052 if (!is_valid_ether_addr(netdev->perm_addr)) {
10053#else
10054 if (!is_valid_ether_addr(netdev->dev_addr)) {
10055#endif
10056 dev_err(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "Invalid MAC Address\n");
10057 err = -EIO;
10058 goto err_eeprom;
10059 }
10060
10061 memcpy(&adapter->mac_table[0].addr, hw->mac.addr, netdev->addr_len);
10062 adapter->mac_table[0].queue = adapter->vfs_allocated_count;
10063 adapter->mac_table[0].state = (IGB_MAC_STATE_DEFAULT | IGB_MAC_STATE_IN_USE);
10064 igb_rar_set(adapter, 0);
10065
10066 /* get firmware version for ethtool -i */
10067 igb_set_fw_version(adapter);
10068
10069 /* Check if Media Autosense is enabled */
10070 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_82580)
10071 igb_init_mas(adapter);
10072
10073#ifdef NO_KNI
10074#ifdef HAVE_TIMER_SETUP
10075 timer_setup(&adapter->watchdog_timer, &igb_watchdog, 0);
10076 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_DETECT_BAD_DMA)
10077 timer_setup(&adapter->dma_err_timer, &igb_dma_err_timer, 0);
10078 timer_setup(&adapter->phy_info_timer, &igb_update_phy_info, 0);
10079#else
10080 setup_timer(&adapter->watchdog_timer, &igb_watchdog,
10081 (unsigned long) adapter);
10082 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_DETECT_BAD_DMA)
10083 setup_timer(&adapter->dma_err_timer, &igb_dma_err_timer,
10084 (unsigned long) adapter);
10085 setup_timer(&adapter->phy_info_timer, &igb_update_phy_info,
10086 (unsigned long) adapter);
10087#endif
10088
10089 INIT_WORK(&adapter->reset_task, igb_reset_task);
10090 INIT_WORK(&adapter->watchdog_task, igb_watchdog_task);
10091 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_DETECT_BAD_DMA)
10092 INIT_WORK(&adapter->dma_err_task, igb_dma_err_task);
10093#endif
10094
10095 /* Initialize link properties that are user-changeable */
10096 adapter->fc_autoneg = true;
10097 hw->mac.autoneg = true;
10098 hw->phy.autoneg_advertised = 0x2f;
10099
10100 hw->fc.requested_mode = e1000_fc_default;
10101 hw->fc.current_mode = e1000_fc_default;
10102
10103 e1000_validate_mdi_setting(hw);
10104
10105 /* By default, support wake on port A */
10106 if (hw->bus.func == 0)
10107 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED;
10108
10109 /* Check the NVM for wake support for non-port A ports */
10110 if (hw->mac.type >= e1000_82580)
10111 hw->nvm.ops.read(hw, NVM_INIT_CONTROL3_PORT_A +
10112 NVM_82580_LAN_FUNC_OFFSET(hw->bus.func), 1,
10113 &eeprom_data);
10114 else if (hw->bus.func == 1)
10115 e1000_read_nvm(hw, NVM_INIT_CONTROL3_PORT_B, 1, &eeprom_data);
10116
10117 if (eeprom_data & IGB_EEPROM_APME)
10118 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED;
10119
10120 /* now that we have the eeprom settings, apply the special cases where
10121 * the eeprom may be wrong or the board simply won't support wake on
10122 * lan on a particular port */
10123 switch (pdev->device) {
10124 case E1000_DEV_ID_82575GB_QUAD_COPPER:
10125 adapter->flags &= ~IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED;
10126 break;
10127 case E1000_DEV_ID_82575EB_FIBER_SERDES:
10128 case E1000_DEV_ID_82576_FIBER:
10129 case E1000_DEV_ID_82576_SERDES:
10130 /* Wake events only supported on port A for dual fiber
10131 * regardless of eeprom setting */
10132 if (E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_STATUS) & E1000_STATUS_FUNC_1)
10133 adapter->flags &= ~IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED;
10134 break;
10135 case E1000_DEV_ID_82576_QUAD_COPPER:
10136 case E1000_DEV_ID_82576_QUAD_COPPER_ET2:
10137 /* if quad port adapter, disable WoL on all but port A */
10138 if (global_quad_port_a != 0)
10139 adapter->flags &= ~IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED;
10140 else
10141 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_QUAD_PORT_A;
10142 /* Reset for multiple quad port adapters */
10143 if (++global_quad_port_a == 4)
10144 global_quad_port_a = 0;
10145 break;
10146 default:
10147 /* If the device can't wake, don't set software support */
10148 if (!device_can_wakeup(&adapter->pdev->dev))
10149 adapter->flags &= ~IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED;
10150 break;
10151 }
10152
10153 /* initialize the wol settings based on the eeprom settings */
10154 if (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED)
10155 adapter->wol |= E1000_WUFC_MAG;
10156
10157 /* Some vendors want WoL disabled by default, but still supported */
10158 if ((hw->mac.type == e1000_i350) &&
10159 (pdev->subsystem_vendor == PCI_VENDOR_ID_HP)) {
10160 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED;
10161 adapter->wol = 0;
10162 }
10163
10164#ifdef NO_KNI
10165 device_set_wakeup_enable(pci_dev_to_dev(adapter->pdev),
10166 adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_WOL_SUPPORTED);
10167
10168 /* reset the hardware with the new settings */
10169 igb_reset(adapter);
10170 adapter->devrc = 0;
10171
10172#ifdef HAVE_I2C_SUPPORT
10173 /* Init the I2C interface */
10174 err = igb_init_i2c(adapter);
10175 if (err) {
10176 dev_err(&pdev->dev, "failed to init i2c interface\n");
10177 goto err_eeprom;
10178 }
10179#endif /* HAVE_I2C_SUPPORT */
10180
10181 /* let the f/w know that the h/w is now under the control of the
10182 * driver. */
10183 igb_get_hw_control(adapter);
10184
10185 strncpy(netdev->name, "eth%d", IFNAMSIZ);
10186 err = register_netdev(netdev);
10187 if (err)
10188 goto err_register;
10189
10190#ifdef CONFIG_IGB_VMDQ_NETDEV
10191 err = igb_init_vmdq_netdevs(adapter);
10192 if (err)
10193 goto err_register;
10194#endif
10195 /* carrier off reporting is important to ethtool even BEFORE open */
10196 netif_carrier_off(netdev);
10197
10198#ifdef IGB_DCA
10199 if (dca_add_requester(&pdev->dev) == E1000_SUCCESS) {
10200 adapter->flags |= IGB_FLAG_DCA_ENABLED;
10201 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "DCA enabled\n");
10202 igb_setup_dca(adapter);
10203 }
10204
10205#endif
10206#ifdef HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK
10207 /* do hw tstamp init after resetting */
10208 igb_ptp_init(adapter);
10209#endif /* HAVE_PTP_1588_CLOCK */
10210
10211#endif /* NO_KNI */
10212 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "Intel(R) Gigabit Ethernet Network Connection\n");
10213 /* print bus type/speed/width info */
10214 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "%s: (PCIe:%s:%s) ",
10215 netdev->name,
10216 ((hw->bus.speed == e1000_bus_speed_2500) ? "2.5GT/s" :
10217 (hw->bus.speed == e1000_bus_speed_5000) ? "5.0GT/s" :
10218 (hw->mac.type == e1000_i354) ? "integrated" :
10219 "unknown"),
10220 ((hw->bus.width == e1000_bus_width_pcie_x4) ? "Width x4" :
10221 (hw->bus.width == e1000_bus_width_pcie_x2) ? "Width x2" :
10222 (hw->bus.width == e1000_bus_width_pcie_x1) ? "Width x1" :
10223 (hw->mac.type == e1000_i354) ? "integrated" :
10224 "unknown"));
10225 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "%s: MAC: ", netdev->name);
10226 for (i = 0; i < 6; i++)
10227 printk("%2.2x%c", netdev->dev_addr[i], i == 5 ? '\n' : ':');
10228
10229 ret_val = e1000_read_pba_string(hw, pba_str, E1000_PBANUM_LENGTH);
10230 if (ret_val)
10231 strncpy(pba_str, "Unknown", sizeof(pba_str) - 1);
10232 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "%s: PBA No: %s\n", netdev->name,
10233 pba_str);
10234
10235
10236 /* Initialize the thermal sensor on i350 devices. */
10237 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_i350) {
10238 if (hw->bus.func == 0) {
10239 u16 ets_word;
10240
10241 /*
10242 * Read the NVM to determine if this i350 device
10243 * supports an external thermal sensor.
10244 */
10245 e1000_read_nvm(hw, NVM_ETS_CFG, 1, &ets_word);
10246 if (ets_word != 0x0000 && ets_word != 0xFFFF)
10247 adapter->ets = true;
10248 else
10249 adapter->ets = false;
10250 }
10251#ifdef NO_KNI
10252#ifdef IGB_HWMON
10253
10254 igb_sysfs_init(adapter);
10255#else
10256#ifdef IGB_PROCFS
10257
10258 igb_procfs_init(adapter);
10259#endif /* IGB_PROCFS */
10260#endif /* IGB_HWMON */
10261#endif /* NO_KNI */
10262 } else {
10263 adapter->ets = false;
10264 }
10265
10266 if (hw->phy.media_type == e1000_media_type_copper) {
10267 switch (hw->mac.type) {
10268 case e1000_i350:
10269 case e1000_i210:
10270 case e1000_i211:
10271 /* Enable EEE for internal copper PHY devices */
10272 err = e1000_set_eee_i350(hw);
10273 if ((!err) &&
10274 (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_EEE))
10275 adapter->eee_advert =
10276 MDIO_EEE_100TX | MDIO_EEE_1000T;
10277 break;
10278 case e1000_i354:
10279 if ((E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL_EXT)) &
10280 (E1000_CTRL_EXT_LINK_MODE_SGMII)) {
10281 err = e1000_set_eee_i354(hw);
10282 if ((!err) &&
10283 (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_EEE))
10284 adapter->eee_advert =
10285 MDIO_EEE_100TX | MDIO_EEE_1000T;
10286 }
10287 break;
10288 default:
10289 break;
10290 }
10291 }
10292
10293 /* send driver version info to firmware */
10294 if (hw->mac.type >= e1000_i350)
10295 igb_init_fw(adapter);
10296
10297#ifndef IGB_NO_LRO
10298 if (netdev->features & NETIF_F_LRO)
10299 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "Internal LRO is enabled \n");
10300 else
10301 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev), "LRO is disabled \n");
10302#endif
10303 dev_info(pci_dev_to_dev(pdev),
10304 "Using %s interrupts. %d rx queue(s), %d tx queue(s)\n",
10305 adapter->msix_entries ? "MSI-X" :
10306 (adapter->flags & IGB_FLAG_HAS_MSI) ? "MSI" : "legacy",
10307 adapter->num_rx_queues, adapter->num_tx_queues);
10308
10309 cards_found++;
10310 *lad_dev = netdev;
10311
10312 pm_runtime_put_noidle(&pdev->dev);
10313 return 0;
10314
10315//err_register:
10316// igb_release_hw_control(adapter);
10317#ifdef HAVE_I2C_SUPPORT
10318 memset(&adapter->i2c_adap, 0, sizeof(adapter->i2c_adap));
10319#endif /* HAVE_I2C_SUPPORT */
10320err_eeprom:
10321// if (!e1000_check_reset_block(hw))
10322// e1000_phy_hw_reset(hw);
10323
10324 if (hw->flash_address)
10325 iounmap(hw->flash_address);
10326err_sw_init:
10327// igb_clear_interrupt_scheme(adapter);
10328// igb_reset_sriov_capability(adapter);
10329 iounmap(hw->hw_addr);
10330err_ioremap:
10331 free_netdev(netdev);
10332err_alloc_etherdev:
10333// pci_release_selected_regions(pdev,
10334// pci_select_bars(pdev, IORESOURCE_MEM));
10335//err_pci_reg:
10336//err_dma:
10337 pci_disable_device(pdev);
10338 return err;
10339}
10340
10341
10342void igb_kni_remove(struct pci_dev *pdev)
10343{
10344 pci_disable_device(pdev);
10345}
